title: chicken marsala
directions: Pound chicken breasts to 1/4-inch thickness.
Dip in Egg Beater and then coat with cracker meal; set aside.
In a nonstick skillet, cook minced garlic in liquid Butter Buds for 1 to 2 minutes.
Add chicken and cook for 6 minutes or until done, turning once.
Remove to serving platter; keep warm.

title: hush puppies
directions: Place corn meal, salt, sugar, baking powder and onion into mixing bowl.
Blend ingredients together. Fold in eggs and milk . Continue mixing. Preheat skillet or electric frypan with vegetable oil, about 1-inch deep.
When oil comes to a bubble, drop 1 spoonful of the batter at a time into oil.
Reduce heat to medium and cook until browned. Drain on paper towels and serve with fried or stewed fish, in particular a Catfish Stew.

title: cherry cheese gelatin
directions: Drain cherries and set aside syrup.
Add water to syrup until it amounts to 3/4 cup.
Place in a small pan.
Boil on high.
Pour into blender.
Add gelatin.
Cover and mix at low speed (approximately 1/2 minute).
Add cream cheese and ice.
Blend at high for approximately 1 minute.
Pour into mold or dessert bowls. Add cherries, one at a time, to mix.
Chill until firm, approximately 1 hour.
Unmold and serve chilled.

title: cream cheese cake
directions: Butter glass dish.
Mix all ingredients, adding 1 egg at a time.

title: "whole" lemon pie
directions: Cut lemon in chunks and remove seeds. Place in a food processor and process until finely chopped. Add remaining ingredients and process until well blended. Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 375° for 25 minutes or until set in the middle.

title: chicken paprika
directions: Season chicken with salt and pepper.
Saute onion and green pepper until lightly brown; sprinkle with paprika and stir in sour cream.
Simmer covered until heated through.
Serve over hot noodles.

title: easy cherry dessert
directions: Place cherry pie filling in buttered baking dish.
Sprinkle box of cake mix over cherries and cover with melted stick of butter and pecans.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Any fruit can be used.

title: fruit bars
directions: Grease and flour a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle nuts on bottom of pan.
Cream the butter and sugar.
Add eggs and beat until fluffy.
Add flour.
Spread batter over nuts.
The batter is thick but you can spread it with a spatula.
Sprinkle the fruit over the top.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Cover with foil the last 15 minutes so it won't dry out.

title: bill curry's favorite bama dining barbecue sauce
directions: Saute onion in 1 tablespoon of oil.
Add other ingredients, mixing well.
Simmer for 20 minutes.

title: cream puffs
directions: Add butter to boiling water.
Stir until butter is melted.
Add flour and salt all at once.
Stir vigorously until mixture is smooth and forms a ball that does not separate.
Remove pan from heat.
Cool mixture slightly.
Add eggs, 1 at a time.
Beat with spoon after each egg is added.
Beat until smooth.
Drop batter from tablespoon onto cookie sheet.
Bake in hot oven (450°) for 15 minutes, then in a moderate oven (325°) for 20 minutes.
Remove shells with spatula; cool on cake rack.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Recipe makes 12 large puffs or 14 eclairs.

title: flip-flop salad
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients; cook this but do not let set.
Mix next 5 ingredients together.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan with 1 tablespoon mayonnaise.
Put cream cheese mixture on bottom of pan. Pour jello mixture on top and watch it (flip-flop).

title: baked devil's float(nadean's)
directions: Combine 1 cup of sugar with water in pan.
Boil 10 minutes. Cream butter and sugar together (the remainder of sugar).
Add vanilla and dry ingredients with milk.
Mix well.
Add nuts.
Pour hot syrup into 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Drop batter on top of syrup by spoonful.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Top with whipped cream.

title: cheese rolls
directions: Place 1 package biscuits in 8-inch round greased pan.
Melt 1/2 cube butter and 1/2 container of cheese.
When melted, pour evenly over rolls and bake at 350° until browned.
Serve warm.

title: raspberry muffins
directions: In large bowl, combine flour and sugar. In small bowl, combine half and half, oil, lemon extract and eggs; blend well. Add to dry ingredients, stirring just until moistened. Fold in raspberries and lemon rind. Fill greased muffin tins 3/4 full. Bake at 425° for 18 to 20 minutes, until golden brown. Makes 12 to 16 muffins.

title: breakfast before 6
directions: Cook sausage; drain well.
Cut bread into cubes with crust off.
Beat eggs and seasoning; add milk.
In 9 x 13-inch pan, layer bread, sausage and cheese.
Pour egg mixture over.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: easy refrigerator pickles(good for all those surplus garden cucumbers)
directions: In large saucepan, combine vinegar, water, sugar and seasoning. Bring to a boil, stirring to dissolve sugar.
Meanwhile, place one clove of garlic in each jar (1 quart); pack cukes and onions into jars.
Fill jars with hot vinegar mixture.
Helps to use a funnel and soup ladle.
Replace lid, then cool in refrigerator for at least 24 hours to blend flavors.
Stores in refrigerator up to 3 months.
Give them to your friends.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: For thick pie or 2 pies, double ingredients.

title: homemade beefaroni
directions: Pour 6 cups of water and 1/2 teaspoon of oil into a large pot. Bring to a boil.
Add shells.
Saute ground beef in a skillet on medium flame until brown.
Drain fat from the meat and replace into skillet.
Add whole tomatoes and chop up.
Add mushroom onion soup mix, red pepper, garlic powder and seasoned salt to meat. Cover and simmer.
When shells are cooked, drain, rinse and return to pot.
Add 1 package of MBT beef broth to shells and stir. Spoon ground meat into pot with shells; mix well.
Serves 4.

title: buster bar dessert
directions: Crush cookies and add margarine.
Spread in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Soften ice cream.
Spoon over Oreo mixture and freeze.
Add peanuts over ice cream.

title: lazy lasagne
directions: Cook beef in a large skillet over medium-high heat until meat is brown, stirring to separate meat; drain fat.
Add spaghetti sauce.
Reduce heat to low.
Heat through, stirring occasionally; set aside.

title: fruitsicles
directions: You will also need paper cups and ice cream sticks or straws.

title: easy hollandaise
directions: Melt butter over medium heat and keep hot until used.
Put yolks in blender with lemon juice.
Blend on low speed 10 seconds. Remove bubbling butter from heat and pour in thin stream into blender on low.
Blend 1 minute or more to cook eggs.
Add pepper.

title: buckeyes
directions: Cream together margarine and sugar.
Mix in peanut butter until smooth.
Form into small balls.
Chill 2 hours or more.
In top of double boiler over simmering water, melt chocolate chips and paraffin.
Spear a candy ball with a toothpick and dip in the chocolate, leaving a small area to give the "buckeye" effect.
Dry dipped candies on wax paper.
Store in tightly covered containers in refrigerator or freezer.
Makes about 75.

title: uncle phil's sourdough pancakes
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients until smooth.
Sift salt, soda and sugar directly onto batter.
Mix only until blended.
Set aside for 15 minutes.

title: squash dressing
directions: Saute onion, bell pepper, celery and margarine.
Bake cornbread, following directions on package.
Crumble cornbread and mix all of the ingredients together.
Salt and pepper to taste. Bake at 400° for about 50 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: gorton
directions: Place all ingredients in large saucepan with cover.
Bring to a boil, then simmer for 6 to 8 hours, until all onion is dissolved and water is gone.
Place mixture in bowls and refrigerate until firm.

title: fresh corn pudding
directions: Combine melted margarine, flour, salt and pepper; stir in milk and corn.
Blend eggs into corn mixture.
Pour into 1 1/2 quart baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: potato salad
directions: Peel potatoes and cut into bite-size pieces.
Boil, drain and cool.
Add eggs that are chopped and all other ingredients and mix well.
For best results, make night before and refrigerate.

title: dream cake
directions: Combine
all
ingredients
in large mixing bowl.
Blend with electric mixer until moistened.
Beat at medium speed for 4 minutes.
Pour
into
greased
and
floured 10-inch tube or Bundt pan.
Bake
at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes for tube pan or 40 minutes for Bundt pan.
Cool in pan 15 minutes, then remove from pan
and
cool on rack.
Serve plain or frost with Fluffy Frosting.

title: bachelors breakfast
directions: Take 1 bowl, fill 1/2 full of cereal, add sugar and milk.
If not full, repeat process.

title: whole beef tenderloin
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Bake, uncovered, 40 to 45 minutes. Remove from oven and let sit 15 minutes before carving.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: kentucky pound cake
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients well and then add pineapple and pecans.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Mix into batter.
Cook in a tube pan at 325° for 1 hour.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
With fork, pierce each potato.
Rub potatoes with oil.
Sprinkle with 1/8 teaspoon salt.
Bake 1 hour. Reduce oven to 350° (can be microwaved).
Remove potatoes from oven; with knife, cut an X in top of each, then cool enough to handle.
Fold back skin where X was cut.
With spoon, carefully scoop out the potato into a large bowl, leaving enough flesh to make a potato shell.
With potato masher, mash potatoes.
Add 1 teaspoon chives to mixture.
Add remaining salt, pepper, sour cream, 1/2 cup cheese and butter; mix well.
Stuff each potato shell with mixture.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese and bacon. Place potatoes on baking sheet.
Bake 20 minutes or less.
Sprinkle with remaining chives.

title: baked beans
directions: Put everything together in a large crock-pot and cook slowly for about 2 hours.
Stir occasionally.

title: nacho pie
directions: Mix taco seasoning into beans.
Spread evenly in the bottom of a casserole dish.
Then spread sour cream and sprinkle onion to taste.
Layer cheese, lettuce and tomato.
Serve chilled with chips for dipping.

title: fast and easy ice cream
directions: Beat eggs.
Add milk and sugar; mix well, then add fruit (optional), vanilla and salt.
Pour into cannister; fill to fill line with water and/or milk.

title: mexican hominy
directions: Mix hominy, tomatoes and soup in baking dish.
Grate 4 or 5 ounces mild cheese and bake at 350° until cheese melts.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar well. Add eggs, beating well.
Fold in sour cream and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients which have been sifted together.
Pour half of this batter into a greased and floured tube pan.

title: western lima beans
directions: Cook limas in water until tender.
Drain and save 1/2 cup liquid.
Combine everything in a casserole and season to taste with poultry seasoning.
Bake until bubbly in 350° oven.

title: cherry delight
directions: Grease a casserole dish with oleo.
Pour in pineapple, then spread over with can of cherry pie filling.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Drain canned peaches.
Put in cake pan.
Pour batter over fruit.
Sprinkle 1 cup sugar over batter.
Pour 1/2 cup of water over sugar.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sour cream waffles
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Combine egg yolks, sour cream, milk and butter; add flour mixture and beat smooth.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Bake; makes 8.

title: ham balls
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease cookie sheet.
Mix all ingredients thoroughly (mixture is dry).
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place about 2 inches apart on sheet.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes, until brown.
Immediately remove from pan.
Serve warm.
Makes about 6 dozen.

title: turkey loaf
directions: Mix turkey with everything else in mixing bowl.
Form mixture into a loaf.
Place in a slow cooking pot.
Cover and cook for 5 to 6 hours on low.

title: green pepper dolma with olive oil
directions: Wash and remove the seeds from the peppers.
Simmer onions in a little of the oil until soft.
Add washed rice and the rest of the ingredients, except the tomato sauce.
Mix well.
Fill peppers with rice mixture only 3/4 of the space.
Place peppers upright in a pan big enough to hold the 4 peppers, pour the tomato sauce into each pepper as much as it will hold.
Pour the rest in the bottom of the pan.
Cover and cook on medium fire until rice is tender, about 1 hour.
Serve cold.

title: pearle ramos's onions with sage stuffing
directions: Boil onions for 10 minutes or until almost tender.
Drain and hollow out, leaving a 3/4-inch shell.
Chop pulp and combine remaining ingredients.
Stuff into onions.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes in a small amount of water or in a pot while cooking a roast.

title: meat and bean burritos
directions: Brown meat.
Add seasonings and taco seasoning mix.
Add soup and refried beans to the meat mixture.
Heat tortillas on both sides in a little butter until soft and easy to roll.
Put meat mixture in shell and roll up.
Serve with chili sauce, shredded lettuce, tomatoes, grated Cheddar cheese, sour cream, etc. Burritos are also good topped with Pace picante sauce.

title: pineapple cookies
directions: Cream together shortening, brown sugar, sugar and eggs.
Add flour, soda and salt and mix.
Add pineapple and its juice and vanilla.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: onion soup potatoes
directions: Potatoes may be prepared in the morning if covered with cold water and refrigerated.
Put potatoes in a 1 1/2-quart casserole that has been buttered.
Melt butter and pour over potatoes. Sprinkle onion soup over potatoes and toss.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
If you don't have onion soup, 1/4 cup finely chopped onion works fine.

title: cheese meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Shape in a loaf in a baking pan. Bake at 350° (moderate oven) for about 50 minutes, until well done.
Makes 8 servings.

title: zucchini soup(can use yellow squash)
directions: Combine zucchini or yellow squash, onion, water and 1 1/3 chicken bouillon in container (either microwave or stove).
Cook until it looks soft and well cooked.
Put contents into a blender and puree until it is thick and creamy.
Serve hot or cold.

title: cajun rice
directions: In a large skillet, heat oil. Saute chicken livers with 1/2 teaspoon of salt until done (no pink should remain).
Dice the cooked chicken livers and set aside.
In the same skillet, saute onions, bell peppers and mushrooms in the margarine until soft. Add diced chicken livers and sausage.
Add remaining ingredients to skillet and cook until warmed through.
Makes about 8 cups.

title: italian stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash and rinse mushrooms, remove stems.
Select several stems and chop them finely.
In a mixing bowl, add chopped stems, egg, garlic, parsley and bread crumbs to the ground beef, mixing well. Stuff ground beef into mushroom caps.
Sprinkle olive oil on cookie sheet and stuffed mushrooms.
Sprinkle oregano and bake at 350° until done (approximately 30 to 45 minutes).

title: li'l smoky appetizer
directions: Cut each crescent roll into thirds.
Wrap each around a little smokies from large end to point.
Bake on cookie sheet according to directions on Crescent Roll tube.

title: chicken sesame balls
directions: Combine all ingredients except sesame seed; mix until blended well.
Form into bite-size balls.
Chill about 1 hour.
Roll in toasted sesame seeds.

title: apple-walnut cake
directions: Combine apples and sugar; let stand.
Beat eggs slightly; beat in oil and vanilla.
Mix and sift flour, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
Stir in alternately with apple-sugar mixture.
Stir in walnuts.
Pour into greased and floured oblong pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until cake tests done. Let stand in pan until quite cold; turn out on rack to complete cooling.

title: canadian lemon bread
directions: Cream together Crisco and sugar.
Add lemon rind and eggs; mix.
Add sifted dry ingredients and milk alternately.
Bake at 350° in a greased and floured loaf pan for about 50 minutes. After baking and cooling slightly, spread with glaze.

title: slush
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Freeze for 2 days.
Scoop into glass and pour "Squirt" to fill glass.
Makes 3 1/2 quarts.
Tastes great on a hot summer day.

title: coconut cheese cake
directions: Mix and press in 13 x 9-inch or bigger pan.
Batter will be thick; you may want to thin it by adding a little more milk.

title: bake macaroni and meat sauce(greek style)
directions: Cook macaroni; drain.
Saute onion, meat (salt and pepper to taste) until browned; add tomato paste and water; simmer until thick; add seasonings.
Put half of the macaroni in greased pan; pour meat mixture over; cover with rest of macaroni.
Sprinkle with half of the grated cheese.
Make custard of eggs and milk and pour over top, sprinkling with remaining grated cheese.
Bake at 325 to 350° for 30 minutes.
Can be served hot or cold.

title: orange cider punch
directions: Put all ingredients into large kettle and heat slowly.
Do not boil.
Stir occasionally.
Serve warm.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: baked crab salad
directions: Start by filling a large saucepan with water and spike it with a few splashes of white wine or dry vermouth. Scatter in several onion slices and/or carrot slices, celery leaves and parsley sprigs over the top.
Season with a dash of salt and a grinding of pepper, then add the chicken breasts.
Bring the pan to a full boil, and then turn it off, letting the heat of the liquid finish the cooking process.
This method seems to keep the breasts especially moist and tender.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Combine ground cranberries and chopped apples.
Add sugar. Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Add crushed pineapple.
Chill until partially set, then add to cranberry mixture.
Add seedless grapes.
Chill and serve.

title: donuts
directions: Quite sticky.
Work flour in while cutting out.

title: lola's oil pie crust
directions: Mix the salt and flour together.
Make a well and pour in the milk and oil.
Mix into a ball with as little handling as possible; roll out thin between 2 sheets of waxed paper.
This will make a double crust pie.
Very flaky.

title: cherry pie
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch.
Slowly stir in cherry juice.
Heat to boiling on medium, stirring constantly, and boil gently for 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add butter, lemon juice and drained cherries.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour into baked pie shell.

title: sour cream steak
directions: Place steaks in baking dish. Add water to steak.
Mix sour cream and onion soup mix. Spread on top of steak. Spread mushrooms on top. Cover and bake about 3 hours at 350°.
(May use roast, pork chops or chicken in place of steak.)

title: creamsicle delight
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Reserve 1/4 cup.
Press remainder in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Refrigerate about 15 minutes. Spread vanilla ice cream over crust.
Place spoonfuls of sherbet over ice cream and swirl into ice cream.
Top with Cool Whip and sprinkle with reserved crumbs.

title: fruit punch(4 gallons)
directions: Pour hot water
over
sugar and citric acid.
Add juice from lemons and orange and pineapple juice.
Add 6 quarts cold water, then add 7
more
quarts
of water.
Mix good.
Makes 4 gallons.

title: beef stew
directions: Coat beef
with
flour	and brown in oil in large Dutch oven. Add
onion	and
garlic
and
cook until vegetables are softened. Pour off any fat.
Add water, wine, celery, parsley and all spices.
Cover
and
simmer 1 hour.
Add potatoes and carrots and simmer 45 minutes longer.
Add a little water, if needed.

title: waldorf salad
directions: In a bowl, combine well the celery with apple and lemon juice; add walnuts and mayonnaise and stir until well combined.
Spoon salad into a bowl lined with the lettuce leaves.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chinese "not fried" rice
directions: Coat a medium saucepan with cooking spray.
Place over medium heat until hot.
Add onion and saute 2 minutes or until tender. Add chicken broth and soy sauce, cooking wine, sesame oil and hot sauce; bring to a boil.
Stir in rice, cover, reduce heat and simmer 25 minutes or until rice is tender and liquid is absorbed. Remove from heat.
Stir in green onion and pine nuts.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Cream butter, sugar, vanilla and lemon extract until fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Sift together flour, salt, tartar and soda.
Add jam and sour cream (mixed) alternately with dry ingredients, beating until well combined.
Stir in nuts. Bake at 350° in two greased loaf pans for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: thin and crispy pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place salad shells on ungreased baking sheet and bake in oven for 3 to 4 minutes or until light golden brown.
Let shells cool for 5 minutes.
Reset oven to 400°.
Spread cooked shells with pizza sauce.
Top with Mozzarella cheese and top with desired toppings.
Place pizza back in oven for 10 to 12 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: carrot salad
directions: Take 8 cups of carrots which have been sliced, cooked, drained and cooled.
Add pepper and onion.
Mix together remaining ingredients and add to carrots.
Refrigerate and marinate 1 to 2 days.
Keeps well.
Serves a large crowd.
Recipe can be cut in half.

title: queen elizabeth cake
directions: Pour boiling water over dates and soda.
Let stand while the remaining ingredients are mixed.
Add all to the mixture and bake 35 minutes in a 350° oven in 9 x 12-inch pan.

title: rum chocolate mousse
directions: Mix rum and sugar in small saucepan.
Stir over low heat until sugar dissolves.
Melt chocolate with 2 tablespoons whipping cream.
Whip remaining cream.
Beat egg whites until fluffy.
Mix in chocolate.
Then fold all into whipped cream.
Spoon into 8 serving dishes or for a party, spoon into 10 to 12 five ounce Dixie cups.
Garnish with chocolate slivers.

title: molasses oat muffins
directions: Toast oats.
In a medium bowl stir together the flour, baking powder, salt and cinnamon; then stir in the sugar and toasted oats.
In a small bowl, beat the egg until yolk and white are blended.
Add milk and molasses, beat to blend.
Add these and the oil to the flour mixture and stir until dry ingredients are moistened.
Spray with low-fat cooking spray.
Fill muffin tins 1/3 full.
Bake in preheated oven at 400° until done, about 15 to 18 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: karo frosting
directions: Beat the egg whites and salt until foamy.
Gradually beat in sugar until smooth and glossy.
Boil the Karo a couple of minutes; pour into egg whites in slow, steady stream while beating.
Add vanilla.
This makes a beautiful frosting that is lightly sweetened with a marshmallow texture.
Work fast with frosting as it sets quickly.
Is best when used the same day it's made.

title: skillet red potatoes
directions: Wash the potatoes, then cut into halves and quarters for the larger ones. Smear the olive oil into a large skillet, covering the entire bottom. Using a spoon, smear the garlic into the bottom of the skillet with the oil. Arrange as many of the potatoes as possible in the garlic oil, cut side down, as possible. Season with the salt and pepper. In a small saucepan, bring the 3 cups of water to a boil with the bouillon cubes and cayenne pepper. Pour the broth over the potatoes and boil, uncovered, on medium-high heat until broth is gone and the potatoes start to sizzle in the garlic and oil. Let them brown slightly, then put them in a serving bowl; sprinkle on the green onions and serve.

title: italian salad dressing
directions: Whisk vinegar with mustard, salt and pepper.
Slowly add oil, stirring vigorously.

title: oreo dessert
directions: Combine cookie crumbs and butter in bowl; mix well.
Press into 9 x 14-inch pan.
Then press softened ice cream into cookie mixture; spread with Cool Whip.
Drizzle with the chocolate syrup and top with pecans or peanuts.
Freeze until firm.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown hamburger/turkey in deep dish; drain.
Add the onions and saute.
Add the rest of the ingredients, simmer for an hour. Pour over cooked spaghetti.

title: sauteed mushrooms
directions: Wash
mushrooms and slice large caps.
Place butter and mushrooms in heavy frying pan and cover; cook over medium heat for 15
minutes,
add	B-V
sauce.
Cook
another
15 minutes without cover, add sherry and cook 15 minutes over high heat. Remove and serve.
Excellent over steak or prime rib.

title: tomato basil bisque
directions: Combine chopped tomatoes, broth and tomato sauce in a blender container. Cover and blend until smooth. Stir in basil. Transfer to a container with a tight fitting lid. Chill for 1 to 4 hours. Makes 4 side dish servings.

title: fruit cocktail cake 2
directions: Grease a 10 x 10 x 2-inch pan.
Mix first 6 ingredients in order as listed.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup brown sugar.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: vegetable kabobs
directions: Cut zucchini and yellow squash into 1 1/2-inch slices. Alternate slices on two or three skewers.
Baste with Italian dressing.
On remaining skewers, alternate tomatoes and mushrooms. Baste well.

title: golden punch
directions: Dissolve sugar in hot water; add cold water and juices.
Stir in flavorings; mix well.
Prepare one day ahead and store in refrigerator.
Add sherbet just before serving.
Yields 3 gallons. Excellent for wedding receptions.

title: mounds coconut candy
directions: Heat
margarine
and add milk to melt.	Add coconut and sugar. Pour on cookie sheet and refrigerate until stiff.	Cut into bars and dip in chocolate.

title: dried beef cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese to room temperature. Combine cream cheese with cottage cheese. Add olives, onions and the sauces; mix well. Add 1/3 of snipped beef. Shape into a large ball. Wrap in foil and refrigerate.

title: waldorf astoria cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and beat.
Add vanilla and milk.
Sift baking powder, flour and cocoa and add to mixture. Fold in chopped nuts.
Bake in three 8 or 9-inch pans.

title: payday cakes
directions: Mix together and press in 9 1/2 x 11-inch pan.
Bake about 15 minutes in a 425° oven.
Spread 3 cups marshmallows on top of cake while still hot.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Beat cream cheese until fluffy. Add lemon juice, paprika and garlic salt, then add soup. Mix well, then add shrimp. Chill before service.

title: turkey delight
directions: Saute onion, mushrooms and garlic over low heat in a large, covered skillet, for 20 minutes; don't let the onion or mushrooms brown.
Add turkey and cook, stirring, until the turkey is crumbly.
Stir in wine, lemon juice and chicken broth.
Cook at a low simmer, covered, for 15 minutes; stir occasionally.
Add noodles to mixture, mix well and recover.
Cook for 8 to 10 minutes or until noodles are tender.
Stir in sour cream, just before serving; cook, just until heated through, stirring constantly.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Good with green salad and French bread.
This will satisfy 3 hearty appetites.

title: quick skillet casserole
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet.
Add soups, Veg-All and water. Cook on medium, heating thoroughly.
Will thicken the longer it's cooked.

title: raw vegetable dip
directions: Blend all ingredients together and refrigerate 3 to 4 hours.

title: rice and chicken
directions: Brown chicken in margarine.
Set aside.
Dissolve bouillon cubes in 5 cups hot water.
Pour water in large casserole dish. Stir in brown or white rice.
Place chicken on top.
Cover tightly.
Bake in 325° oven for 2 hours.

title: hershey bar fudge
directions: Boil butter, sugar and milk 5 minutes on low heat.
Add Hershey bar, marshmallow cream and pecans. Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.

title: chocolate coffee cake
directions: Combine ingredients in order given.
Mix well.
Pour into greased and floured pan.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until a toothpick inserted comes out clean.
Tastes great with peanut butter frosting.

title: spaghetti with clam sauce
directions: Start cooking the broccoli in a large covered frying pan in a small amount of water.
When it is half cooked, add the onion and the garlic.
Cook for a few minutes and add the seafood (if using) and cook slowly, stirring often.
Add the clams and their juice and the basil.
Heat thoroughly.
Drain the pasta and add it to the clam sauce.
Add butter to taste; mix thoroughly and serve.

title: salmon patties
directions: Mix and fry in palm size patties. Serve with Kraft macaroni and cheese, green peas and cole slaw.

title: orange salad
directions: Dissolve jello into water. Add remaining ingredients. Mix well. Refrigerate.

title: pot pie
directions: Mix into dough.
Roll over very thin.
Cut into squares.
Cook in favorite meat and broth.
Add onion, celery, potatoes and carrots.
Simmer about 1 hour.

title: apple fritters
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt. Add eggs, milk, oil and apples.
Stir until all ingredients are moistened.
Pour 1/2-inch oil for frying into heavy saucepan.
Heat to frying temperature.
Drop batter by spoonfuls into hot oil. Cook until brown on both sides.
Drain on paper towels and sprinkle with confectioners sugar. Serve warm.
Makes about 3 dozen fritters.

title: dip for fruit
directions: Blend together until creamy.
Good with any kind of fruit.

title: christmas sugarplums
directions: Mix butter, Karo, dates and crumbs by hand until well blended. Pinch off pieces the size of a large olive and wrap each piece around a pecan half.
Roll 30 in sugar, the rest in coconut. Makes 60 sugarplums.

title: homemade dog biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Roll out 1/2 of the dough at a time into 3/8-inch thickness.
Using a pizza cutter, cut to desired shapes.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 20 minutes at 375°.
Turn off oven and leave in oven until cool.
Keeps for weeks in airtight container.
Yields about 1 pound.
Dogs love it.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Cook the first four ingredients until thick.
Set off the stove.
Add the vanilla and butter.
Pour into baked pie shell. Serve when completely cool.

title: coconut pie
directions: Cook until thick all ingredients except coconut.
Add coconut. Pour into baked pie crust.
Top with egg white frosting.
Put in oven and brown.

title: cheese 'n macaroni
directions: Add 2 cups noodles to 3 to 4 quarts boiling water.
Cook approximately 8 to 10 minutes or until noodles are tender.
Drain noodles in colander, then pour into glass baking dish.
Add butter; stir until melted.
Slice Cheddar cheese thinly and place over the noodles.
Put in oven at 400° until cheese is slightly beginning to brown.

title: lemon glaze cake
directions: Put all in large mixing bowl.
Beat 3 minutes.
Oil bottom of pan.
Sprinkle bottom with coconut.
Bake at 350° or 400° for 40 minutes.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook linguine.
Cut onion, tomato and cucumber into bite size pieces.
Add to linguine.
Sprinkle on Salad Supreme.
Pour on Italian dressing.
Mix well.
Marinate overnight.
Serve chilled.

title: banana bread
directions: Dissolve soda in milk.
Bake in greased loaf pan for 1 hour at 350°.
This is easy to make and very good as a treat.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix and put in unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: green chili corn casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except cheese, mixing well.
Spread half of mixture in greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Place slices of cheese over mixture; top with remaining batter.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes, or until golden brown.
Makes 6 generous servings.

title: frozen layered cranberry salad
directions: Mash cranberry sauce with fork.
Mix in lemon juice.
Spread a little of this mixture into individual molds, paper
muffin cups or 1 larger mold.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Spread this on top of cranberry layer.
Freeze.
Unmold red side up on lettuce leaves.
May be served with a dash of mayonnaise on top.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: mexican beans
directions: Cook beans until done.
Brown ground beef, onion, garlic and salt.
Mix meat with the rest of ingredients.
Cook until flavor is blended.
Serve with Mexican cornbread.

title: 7 day pickles
directions: Leave cukes whole and cover with boiling water.
Let stand at room temperature.
Next morning, drain and wipe dry.
Cover with boiling water.
Repeat for 3 more mornings, then cut cukes into 1/2-inch slices.
Mix rest of ingredients and boil.
Pour over cukes, let stand at room temperature for 2 days.
Bring contents to a boil; pack, seal and process 10 minutes in a boiling water bath.

title: honey butter
directions: Cream butter and margarine together with electric mixer at medium speed until well blended.
Beat in honey, 1 tablespoon at a time, then beat in milk in same manner until smooth and fluffy. Keep refrigerated and stir before using.
Yields 1 1/2 cups.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Mix all ingredients, except nutmeg, together with a whisk. Pour into an unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle top with nutmeg.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes, then reduce heat and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until knife comes out clean in middle.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add remaining ingredients in the order listed. Pour into pie shell. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until center is firm.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix and knead well.
Roll into balls (about walnut size). Chill 30 minutes.
Bake on cookie sheet at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: coconut balls
directions: Mix all ingredients and roll into balls. Cover with melted almond bark and place on wax paper until hard. Makes 8 dozen.

title: ratatouille
directions: Cut the eggplant into 1-inch chunks.
Cut zucchini into quarters lengthwise, then into 1-inch lengths.
Put the vegetables into a colander, sprinkle with salt and leave to drain for 30 minutes.

title: creamy rice pudding
directions: Gradually stir milk and egg into pudding mix in saucepan.
Add rice and raisins.
Stir over medium heat until mixture just comes to a boil.
Pour into serving bowl.
Serve cold or warm and sprinkle with cinnamon and nutmeg.

title: meat balls with spaghetti
directions: Brown onion in hot olive oil.
Add tomatoes, tomato paste, water and seasonings.
Cook slowly for 1 hour.
Combine remaining ingredients, except spaghetti; mix thoroughly.
Form into small balls; brown in olive oil.
Add to sauce; cook over low heat for 15 minutes.
Cook spaghetti in boiling, salted water until tender; drain.
Serve sauce over hot spaghetti.
Top with grated Parmesan cheese.
Makes 6 servings.

title: fresh spring rolls
directions: Cook noodles according to package; let cool.
Place all ingredients in an assembly line to construct spring rolls.
Fill a pie plate with very warm but not hot water.
Soak each wrapper just until soft.
Place wrapper on work area and fill with lettuce, carrot, egg and a small amount of noodles, about 1/4 way up from the bottom of the wrapper.
Place 1 to 2 coriander or basil leaves 1/4 of the way down from the top with 3 shrimp halves on top of leaves.
Fold the sides in and tightly roll up like a burrito.

title: pistachio sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Chill and serve over ice cream or cake.
Yields 1 1/2 cups.

title: crazy corn nachos
directions: In a large skillet, heat oil and saut red pepper, onion and corn until soft.
Stir in green chiles.

title: oven rice
directions: Melt margarine in a 9 x 13-inch dish or 2-quart casserole. Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: country pie crust
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Cut in shortening until like coarse cornmeal.
Mix egg, water and vinegar together and pour into flour all at once.
Combine to form dough. Divide into four portions and roll out.
Makes four 9-inch crusts or two double-crusted pies.

title: oriental tuna casserole
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Rinse pea pods under running cold water to separate; drain.
Mix pea pods, soup, milk, tuna, onions, celery and water chestnuts in 3-quart saucepan.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat.
Keep warm.
Mix baking mix, water and soy sauce until soft dough forms; beat vigorously 20 strokes.
Gently smooth dough into balls on well-floured cloth-covered board.
Knead 5 times.
Roll into 5-inch squares. Cut dough into 1-inch squares.
Pour hot tuna mixture into ungreased 1 1/2-quart round casserole.
Top with dough squares; spread dough with melted butter.
Sprinkle with sesame seed.
Bake until golden brown, about 15 minutes.
Makes 5 or 6 servings.

title: salmon stew
directions: Put 2 1/2 cups water in pan.
Add butter, sugar and onion; bring to a boil for a few minutes. Add salmon and boil. Add potato soup.
(Can use instant potatoes instead of potato soup.)
Add milk to achieve desired thickness.

title: stuffed jalapeno pepper dip
directions: Combine all the ingredients listed except the peppers.
Mix well. Chill for 1 hour or longer and serve with chips or stuff into the deseeded jalapeno pepper halves.
Makes 1 1/3 cups of the dip or 30 stuffed jalapeno peppers.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook zucchini until half done (do not overcook) for 5 to 10 minutes.
Salt slightly.
Drain several times.
Saute onions in some of margarine.
Mix onions, carrots, soup, sour cream and zucchini.
Set aside.
Melt rest of margarine and pour over stuffing in separate bowl and mix well.
Butter a 2-quart casserole dish and in layers, start with half of zucchini mixture and then half of stuffing mix.
Repeat, ending with stuffing on top.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°, covered.
Remove lid and bake additional 10 minutes, uncovered.

title: christmas prunes appetizer
directions: Cover with cold water.
Bring to boiling point and simmer about 20 minutes until tender.
Add sugar; cook 5 minutes more. Add 1/2 cup or more sherry, brandy or Port.
Place in a Mason jar. Chill until needed.
Almonds, blanched to stuff prunes before serving and secure with toothpick (wooden and wet).
Broil until bacon is crisp and serve.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mix well and serve.

title: creamy lemon pie
directions: In medium bowl, beat egg yolks; stir in milk, lemon juice and food coloring.
Pour into crust.
Chill 3 hours.
Top with whipped topping.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: risotto milanese
directions: Heat 1/2 butter and oil in deep saute pan and onion over moderate heat until wilted but not brown.
Add unwashed rice and stir until well coated with butter and is golden color.
Add 4 1/2 cups hot broth, stir and cover.
Cook over low heat 20 minutes. Mix saffron powder and 2 tablespons broth.
Add to rice.
Sprinkle with cheese and mix again.
Taste.
Add the 1/2 cup hot broth if not creamy and too dry.
Pass more cheese if you want.

title: zucchini rounds
directions: Stir together Bisquick, cheese and pepper.
Stir in eggs just until mixture is moistened.
Fold in zucchini.
In skillet, melt butter over medium heat.
Drop mixture into skillet by heaping tablespoonfuls for each round.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes on each side until brown.
Makes 12 rounds.

title: 7-layer dip
directions: Spread refried beans on the bottom of the pan.
Next, mix taco seasoning and sour cream and spread over refried beans.
Next, pour 1/2 cup picante sauce, then sprinkle both cheeses over the picante sauce.
Then dice the tomato, olives and green onions and then sprinkle over the cheeses.
Store until ready to serve.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Stir often until hot and butter is melted.
Baste on meat every 10 minutes.

title: french fried onion rings
directions: Sift flour into bowl.
Add milk, cream, oil and egg whites. Beat until smooth.
Cut onions in 1/4-inch slices.
Dip rings into batter and fry in deep fat (365°).
Fry until desired color (2 to 3 minutes).
Drain on paper towels and salt.
This batter clings to the onion rings and does not separate.

title: streusel topped pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425 degrees.
Combine pumpkin, condensed milk, egg, 3/4 tsp. cinnamon, ginger, nutmeg and salt.
Mix well. Pour into pie crust.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Put all ingredients through food chopper.
Measure and add equal amount of sugar.
Put in jars and refrigerate until ready to use.

title: chocolate dream
directions: Press into 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Cool.

title: scotch chocolate cake
directions: Melt oleo, Crisco, cocoa and water in saucepan.
Pour mixture over sugar and flour.
Mix these ingredients and add remaining ingredients.
This mixture will be quite thin.
For thick cake squares, bake in pan approximately 11 x 16-inches at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes.
To make sheet cake or brownie type squares, bake in two pans of approximate size at 350°.
Ice this cake while hot.

title: cheese and sausage biscuits
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together with hands. Roll in small balls and bake at 325° to 350° until brown and crispy.

title: mincemeat
directions: Mix ingredients in order and let simmer over slow fire for 4 hours; stir often.
Pack in hot jars and seal at once.
Process 10 minutes.
Makes 6 quarts.

title: savory snack mix
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
In a large shallow baking pan, mix popped popcorn, pretzel sticks and cheese curls.
Melt butter in small pan. Stir in seasonings.
Pour over dry mixture and mix well.
Bake for about 45 minutes, stirring several times.

title: "great" grandma's dessert
directions: In large pan, boil the can (unopened) of condensed milk for 3 hours.
Make sure can is completely covered with water the entire 3 hours.

title: fruit salad
directions: In a large bowl, mix together the bananas, pineapple, oranges, Eagle Brand milk and cherry pie filling, then add Cool Whip and marshmallows.
Keep in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: apple nut cake
directions: Cream together oil or butter with sugar and eggs; slowly add in flour, soda and salt.
Stir in vanilla.
Fold in apples and nuts. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until toothpick inserted comes out clean.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: In a bowl combine soup, sour cream, chicken, green chilies and 1/2 bunch scallions.
Stir until mixed well.
Put 2 or 3 tablespoons of mixture into a tortilla.
Roll and place in baking dish or pan.
Coat with Pam.
Place the tortillas next to one another so they are touching.
Fill all tortillas and pour any additional mixture over the tortillas.
Top with cheese and 1/2 bunch of scallions.
Cover and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Serve with lettuce, tomato, sour cream, guacamole, etc.
Enjoy!

title: skillet twin loaves
directions: Mix ground beef, bread crumbs, onions, eggs, parsley, 1/2 can tomato sauce, 1 teaspoon salt and pepper.
Form 2 oval loaves about 3 x 5-inch.
Brown on all sides in oil by turning loaves with large spoon and spatula.
When browned, add remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer 1 hour, basting occasionally.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix together with electric beater in large bowl. Divide between 3 loafs (greased and floured). Bake at 350 degrees for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours. Bread freezes well.

title: chinese ramen salad
directions: Brown almonds and sesame seeds in a little oil.
Chop green onions and cabbage.
Just before serving, mix cabbage and green onions.
Add browned sesame seeds and almonds.
Crush Ramen noodles (uncooked).
Discard seasoning package.
Add noodles to cabbage mix.

title: corn fritters
directions: Chop corn.
Add salt and pepper.
Add beaten egg, butter, milk, flour and baking powder.
Fry in much grease in frypan.

title: baked beans supreme
directions: Dice onions and cut up bacon.
Brown slowly until onions are soft.
Drain off fat.
Combine all ingredients.
Bake in 1 1/2-quart casserole slowly (275°) for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: powdered nut balls
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add other ingredients, except powdered sugar.
Mix thoroughly and form into balls.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Cool until warm and roll twice in powdered sugar.

title: pudding cake
directions: Mix flour, nuts and margarine in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Mix 1 cup of Cool Whip, confectioners sugar and Philadelphia cream cheese; spread over first mixture.
Mix instant pudding with milk.
Spread this mixture over cheese mixture, then add remaining Cool Whip over top.
Chill.
Optional: Add nuts on top.

title: macaroni and cheese bake
directions: Melt butter and
mix with flour.
Add milk slowly until sauce thickens.
Cut
cheese
in	cubes.	Add
to sauce.	Stir constantly until cheese melts.
Pour cheese sauce over 1 pound box cooked macaroni.
Stir a little.
Add tomatoes to top; cut in a bit.
Top
with
a	bit
of
cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry pretzel
directions: Crush pretzels and mix with 3 tablespoons sugar and butter. Press into pan and bake 6 minutes at 400°.
Mix Jell-O with 2 cups boiling water.
Let cool a while and slice partially thawed strawberries into Jell-O.
Let set approximately 30 minutes.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Roll biscuits thin.
Put chopped apples in center and pull biscuits up around apples.
Combine remaining ingredients and bring to a boil. Pour over apple dumplings.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: boca rio fish chowder
directions: Place water and fish of choice in heavy pot; simmer no more than 8 minutes, with lid on pot.
Remove fish from water; set aside.
Brown bacon, then add onions to cook until tender.
Add this and remainder of ingredients (do not include tomatoes, only the juice, if used).
Simmer for about 15 minutes.
Do not overcook.
Veggies should be crunchy, not soft.
Remove any skin and bone from fish; break into 1/2 to 1-inch pieces and add with stewed tomatoes (if desired) to chowder.
Simmer only a minute or two to heat.
Tastes better the next day.
Be sure not to recook. Only heat to a nice-and-hot.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.
Serve with French bread heated in oven with Cheddar cheese melted on top.

title: basic butter cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare 2 (8-inch) round cake pans. Mix together flour, baking powder and salt.
Beat butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Blend in eggs one at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Add milk and vanilla alternately with flour mixture, mixing well after each addition.
Pour batter into prepared pans.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes or until cake tester comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes before removing from pans.
Cool completely on wire racks before frosting with Fluffy White Frosting (recipe in this section).

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix together.
Drop by teaspoon in hot oil until golden brown.

title: chess pie
directions: Reserve 1 tablespoon sugar; sprinkle 1/2 on bottom of unbaked 9-inch pie shell.
Cream butter and remaining sugar; add egg yolks. Add flour, milk and vanilla gradually.
Pour into shell and sprinkle top with remaining reserved sugar.
Bake 10 minutes at 450°, then 1 hour at 250°.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Soften cream cheese and spread on flat glass dish, then spread cocktail sauce.
Add shrimp or crab meat on top.
Decorate with Ritz crackers around the cream cheese.

title: pork chops or chicken with rice pilaf
directions: Combine the first 6 ingredients in a 2 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Brush chicken breasts with butter, then season with salt, pepper and paprika.
Place on top of rice.
Cover and bake at 350° to 375° for about 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours, or until meat and rice are tender.

title: mexican wedding cake
directions: Mix everything together thoroughly (I usually beat the egg with a fork before) and place in a 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan.
Put in a 350° oven 40 to 45 minutes.

title: black bean burgers
directions: Place beans in large bowl. Partially mash with a fork. Stir in bread crumbs and next 6 ingredients. Divide mixture into 4 equal portions and shape into patty.

title: rainbow compote
directions: Combine honey, lemon juice, candied ginger and orange peel. Pour dressing over orange slices in bowl; cover and refrigerate for several hours or overnight.
Chill remaining fruits.
Drain oranges, reserving dressing.
Arrange orange slices in bottom of compote.
Top with a layer of blueberries, a layer of melon cubes and a layer of halved strawberries.
Pour reserved dressing over fruit.
Garnish with additional whole strawberries, if desired. Makes 10 servings.

title: orange cloud(diabetic recipe)
directions: Prepare gelatin according to package directions, substituting ginger ale for cold water.
Pour 1 cup gelatin in metal bowl; divide remaining gelatin among four 4-ounce glasses.
Chill bowl and glasses 1 hour.
Set 8 orange segments aside; divide remaining segments between glasses.
Using spoon, poke into gelatin.
Whisk 1/2 cup yogurt into gelatin in bowl until well blended.
Pour over gelatin layer in glasses.
Chill until set, about 1 1/2 hours. Garnish with reserved orange segments and the remaining yogurt.

title: baked apples
directions: In baking dish, put apples, lemon juice and white sugar.
In bowl, stir flour, brown sugar, cinnamon, salt and butter to taste by hand; put over apples.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Add cheese.
Put back in oven for a few minutes to melt cheese. Delicious.

title: east texas mulagan stew
directions: Brown meat in shortening.
Put meat and remaining ingredients into pot.
Add enough water to cover meat and vegetables.
Simmer for 1 hour.
Serve over rice.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook 2 packages frozen chopped broccoli as directed.
Drain off liquid.
Add while hot 1/2 stick margarine, 1/2 pound Velveeta cheese, grated.
Stir and pour into buttered casserole.
Crush with rolling pin 1/4 pound Ritz crackers.
Mix cracker crumbs with 1/2 stick melted butter and sprinkle evenly on top of mixture.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: reese's peanut butter cups
directions: Blend all ingredients except the chocolate morsels; spread in sheet pans. Melt chocolate morsels and spread over peanut butter; chill until firm.

title: polynesian chicken
directions: Salt and pepper skinned chicken.
Place in baking pan.
Mix other ingredients (except pineapple) together.
Pour half of mixture over chicken in baking pan and cover.
Baste several times with remaining mixture while baking.
Add pineapple during the last 15 minutes or so.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: broccoli and cheese casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions; add cooked rice and place in a casserole dish. Mix in Cheez Whiz and soup and stir. Place in oven for 35 Minutes at 325°.

title: shipwreck casserole
directions: Put potatoes in bottom of casserole bowl.
Layer the peppers and onion, then meat over potatoes.
Next layer the pork and beans and finish with the tomato soup.
Cook 1 hour at 350°.

title: sweet potato pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Place in greased round casserole. Bake at 375° for one hour or until brown.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Select a deep bowl.
Cut cake into squares.
Place a layer of cake, then pudding, then Cool Whip and then candy bits.
Repeat layering until all ingredients are used.
Cover and refrigerate until serving time.
Scoop to the bottom when serving.

title: mango yogurt drink
directions: Place all ingredients in blender container.
Cover; process until smooth.
(Add milk, if desired, to obtain preferred consistency.)
Garnish as desired.
Serve immediately.

title: mexican fruit cake
directions: Mix eggs, flour, salt, soda, undrained pineapple, 2 cups granulated sugar and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.
Mix butter, cream cheese and 2 cups of powdered sugar.
Blend well and pour over top of hot cake.
Sprinkle with extra nuts, if desired.

title: white chili
directions: Place beans in large heavy pot.
Add enough cold water to cover by at least 3 inches.
Soak overnight.

title: oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Lightly grease cookie sheets.
Sift flour, baking soda and salt.
In large bowl, with electric mixer at medium speed or wooden spoon, beat shortening, sugars, eggs and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Add flour mixture and oats; beat with wooden spoon until well blended.
Stir in raisins.
With hands, roll into balls using a slightly rounded tablespoonful for each.
Place 2 inches apart on prepared cookie sheets.
Bake for 12 to 14 minutes or until golden brown.
Let stand for 1 minute, then remove to wire rack.
Cool.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: caramel pop corn
directions: Mix together in large bowl.
After the children have washed their hands, give each one a ball of the play dough and a piece of wax paper to roll it on.
After the children make something with the play dough, this is one time they can play with their food, then eat it afterwards!!
It is perfectly okay.

title: british chicken livers
directions: Roll chicken livers into a piece of bacon with toothpick. Season with salt and pepper.
Bake in oven at 375° for 35 minutes or until bacon is crisp.

title: red fish court bouillon
directions: In oil, saut onions and celery about 10 minutes.
Stir in the next 12 ingredients.
Cook loosely covered for about 3 hours, stirring frequently.
Add water in small amounts as needed; simmer and arrange fish steaks in single layer.
Add sugar and salt and continue cooking, covered for 15 to 20 minutes to cook fish. Remove lid and simmer for 15 minutes more.	Serve over hot rice with garlic bread.

title: pet milk salad
directions: Chill Pet milk the night before.
Soften cream cheese and whip together.
Heat pineapple and add pineapple and Jell-O.
Add to cheese mixture.
Add nuts and chill.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Stir cake mix and pudding together.
Add water, oil and eggs and beat well.
Stir in sour cream until mixed and add chips with spoon.
Bake in tube pan at 350° until done (50 to 60 minutes).

title: apple-nut cake
directions: Grease and flour Bundt tube pan.
Combine ingredients; mix well.
Pour into pan.
Bake at 375° for 55 minutes.
Cool about 10 minutes before turning onto plate.

title: microwave cornbread
directions: Sprinkle cornflake crumbs in an oiled 5 1/2 to 6-cup microwave safe ring mold.
Combine flour, cornmeal, baking powder, sugar and salt.
Add eggs, milk and oil; mix well.
Pour into ring mold. Cook, uncovered, in microwave 5 minutes at High or until a cake tester comes out clean; rotate 1/2 turn once.
Immediately invert on serving platter.

title: oven fried haddock
directions: Preheat oven to very hot, 525°.
Add salt to milk.
Cut fillets into serving pieces and dip fish into milk, then crumbs mixed with cheese and thyme.

title: beet salad
directions: Drain juice.
If not enough, add water to make 1 cup.
Put beets in a bowl.
Pour dry jello over beets.
Pour hot liquid over all.
Mix well.
Refrigerate 3 to 4 hours.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions and drain.
In 2-quart casserole, combine all ingredients except Parmesan cheese.
Blend well.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over top.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: In large bowl, combine first 6 ingredients with 3/4 cup of cream.
Shape into 1-inch meatballs.
Coat thoroughly with flour.

title: bird nests
directions: Boil sugar, syrup and peanut butter (easy to stick).
Remove from heat.
Add in order vanilla and stir, noodles and stir, cereal and stir, then add coconut and stir.
Using an ice cream scoop, dip into muffin tin and shape with wet hands.
Decorate with jelly beans or any egg-shaped candy.
May be served on dyed coconut. Serves approximately 20.

title: polish stewed cabbage
directions: Put shredded cabbage in 4 to 5-quart pot.
Pour kraut with juice over cabbage.
Add water to cover 3/4 of the cabbage.
Fry bacon pieces with onion until done and pour over cabbage mixture (grease included).
If using kielbasa, cut into slices.
Cook until tender, then add 1 tablespoon sugar and 2 tablespoons vinegar or to your taste.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken; cut into bite size pieces (save chicken broth to cook spaghetti).
Chop onions in fine pieces and brown in margarine.
Mix chicken, cooked spaghetti, onions, milk and soup in a large bowl.
Add black pepper to taste.
Put into 3 baking dishes (extras can be frozen).
Sprinkle with grated cheese or buttered cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: english toffee
directions: Cook butter, sugar and water to hard crack stage (310°), stirring constantly.
Place pecans on large cookie sheet.
Spread cooked mixture on chopped pecans.
While mixture is still hot, spread 8 ounces Hershey's milk chocolate on top.
(If chocolate is spread on immediately, the mixture will be hot enough to melt the chocolate.)
Let harden overnight.
Then turn entire block of candy over.
Melt 8 ounces Hershey's chocolate and spread over mixture.
Let cool completely.
Break into pieces.

title: greenbrier pumpkin muffins
directions: Combine 1 1/4 cups sugar, pumpkin and butter.
Blend in eggs. Combine flour, baking powder, 1 teaspoon cinnamon, nutmeg and salt.
Add combined dry ingredients alternately with milk, mixing well after each addition.
Stir in raisins and nuts.
Spoon into well-greased miniature muffin pans, filling 2/3 full.
Sprinkle with combined 2 tablespoons sugar and 1/4 teaspoon cinnamon.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: tex-mex dip
directions: Peel, pit and mash avocados in a medium bowl with lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Combine sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning in another bowl.
Spread in the following order on a large shallow platter:
bean dip, seasoned avocado mixture, sour cream mixture, tomatoes, onions, olives and cheese.
Serve with chips.
You may use a 9 x 13-inch pan.
This can be made the day before.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350° in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: molasses sugar cookies
directions: Combine first four ingredients.
Combine flour, soda, salt and spices.
Add to molasses mixture.
Stir until smooth.
Shape into one-inch balls and flatten with fingers dipped in sugar.
Place two inches apart on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 6 to 8 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: eggplant zucchini bake
directions: Coarsely chop eggplant; set aside.
Slice zucchini and mushrooms; set aside.
Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

title: creole shrimp
directions: In large frying pan, brown flour in bacon drippings.
Stir tomatoes, tomato sauce, minced onion, green pepper, parsley, garlic, water, salt and pepper into flour-oil mixture.
Bring sauce to a boil, then reduce to a simmer.
Cook 20 minutes.
Add shrimp to mixture and cook 10 minutes longer.

title: fresh fruit freeze
directions: In a blender combine all ingredients; blend well.
Serve immediately.
Makes 6 servings.

title: tomato-pasta salad
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on package; drain.
Rinse with cold water; drain.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Toss macaroni and tomato mixture.
Cover and refrigerate about 2 hours or until chilled.
Makes 6 servings; contains 185 calories and 5 grams fat per serving.

title: pepper steak
directions: Combine flour and seasonings; pound into meat. Brown meat in shortening. Pour off fat. Add soup and ketchup. Cover; cook over low heat 1 hour. Add green pepper; cook 20 minutes more; stir now and then.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream butter; add sugar and eggs, then dry ingredients.
Add applesauce.
Stir in raisins.
Grease and flour pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: bread pudding
directions: Mix
together eggs, sugar and salt. Add milk, seasoning and then
bread cut in squares. Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for about 3/4 hour or until knife inserted comes out clean.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni in boiling salted water until tender.
Drain. Add oleo and toss lightly.
Add cheese, pickles, onion and peas. Stir in mayonnaise; blend carefully and make sure macaroni is well mixed.

title: banana cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Mix dry ingredients.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased and floured 8 x 8 inch baking pan.
Bake for 30 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean when poked into cakes center.
Set aside to cool before icing.

title: buffalo chip cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars together.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Add the remaining ingredients. Mix until all are moistened.
Chill.
Form into balls, using a heaping teaspoon of dough, and bake on greased cookie sheet at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: texas hash
directions: Brown ground beef; drain off fat.
Add onion, chili powder, salt and pepper.
Cook until onion is tender.
Add tomatoes and rice.
Pour into a casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, covered.

title: potato, cabbage and bacon casserole
directions: Coat 3-quart casserole with nonstick cooking spray.
Layer half of the cabbage and onions.
Sprinkle with half the bacon.
Sprinkle with half of the parsley, thyme, salt and pepper.
Put half of the potatoes on top.
Repeat, ending with potatoes.
Pour broth over. Sprinkle with cheese.
Cover and bake in oven at 350° for 45 minutes.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes more or until top is brown.

title: pickled eggs
directions: Simmer all ingredients, except the eggs, for 8 minutes. Strain and pour over eggs.

title: delicious beans
directions: If desired, add ham, wieners or bacon.
If they are too soupy, more beans may be added.
Put into a 350° oven until hot.

title: orange carrots
directions: Bring water to a boil.
Add carrots.
Cover and cook until tender.
Drain liquid, reserving 1/2 cup.
Add orange juice to reserved liquid.
Add cornstarch and cook over medium heat until thickened and clear.
Add sugar, carrots and orange sections. Heat thoroughly.

title: chicken dressing casserole
directions: In large bowl, mix dressing, celery, onion, melted margarine and chicken broth.
For more moist, may add additional broth.
In large baking dish, place frozen green beans; sprinkle with almonds. Spread chopped chicken over the beans and almonds.
Mix can of cream of chicken soup, 1 can cream of mushroom soup and 1 large can evaporated milk.
Blend well and pour over chicken.
Place dressing over mixture.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 minutes or until mixture bubbles.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion together.
Mix remaining ingredients together to make sauce; add meat and sauce together. Grease casserole and put layer of Fritos, then mixture alternately.
Bake at 350° until thoroughly heated.
If freezing, don't put in Fritos.

title: golden corral blueberry muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in well-greased and floured muffin tins at 375° to 400° until lightly brown on top.

title: cherry cream dessert
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients; stir until thick.
Store in a glass jar in the refrigerator.

title: lemon cheese icing
directions: Mix sugar and soft butter.
Add eggs; beat well and add lemonade slowly.
Continue beating so eggs won't curdle.
Put in top of double boiler; stir until thick enough to spread.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Cream enough
to make a stiff roll.
Work well and roll on board.
Spread with peanut butter.	Make into two rolls and slice.

title: lemon berry pie
directions: Helpful Hint:
Soften cream cheese in microwave on High for 15 to 20 seconds.

title: english toffee
directions: Cook until it hardens in water.
Pour in sheet.
Cut.
Pieces may be covered with grated nuts.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, milk and butter in a pan.
Bring to a full boil over medium heat.
Boil for 3 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in oats, peanut butter, salt and vanilla; mix well. Drop on wax paper.
Cool.

title: egg nog
directions: In a blender, beat the egg yolks until light.
Add the sugar and beat until thick. Stir into a bowl or gallon jug.
Add the milk and rum. Chill for 3 hours.
Pour into punch bowl and fold in the whipped cream.
Chill 1 hour longer.
Before serving, dust with nutmeg.

title: holly's zucchini and corn
directions: Melt butter in 10-inch skillet.
Add zucchini, corn and green pepper.
Sprinkle with salt.
Cover and cook 10 to 12 minutes. Sprinkle with dill.
Serve.

title: aunt doris' salsa
directions: Combine all ingredients in a glass container with a lid.
This salsa keeps well indefinitely stored in the refrigerator. If salsa thickens, add V-8 juice or tomato juice.

title: chinese fried rice
directions: Separate the rice with a fork.
Add a tablespoon or two of water if necessary to moisten and separate; set aside.
Heat the oil in a frypan.
Add the lightly beaten egg whites, ham and peas and cook on medium heat for 1 minute.
Add the rice and stir to combine the ingredients.
Add the scallions, soy sauce and pepper and cook for 1 minute.
Yield:
Makes 8 (1/3 cup) servings.

title: fresh peaches and dumplings
directions: Combine peaches, water, sugar and lemon juice in a 3-quart saucepan with tight-fitting lid.
Bring peach mixture to boil; boil 2 to 3 minutes.
While peaches are boiling, combine pancake mix, brown sugar, nutmeg, milk and margarine.
Stir only until mixed.
Remove peach mixture from heat.
Drop dumpling batter by rounded teaspoons onto hot peach mixture.
Cover pan and return to heat.
Cook over medium heat for 15 minutes.
Do not lift lid! Serve warm with vanilla ice cream.

title: tomato bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add tomatoes, sugar, oil, salt and spices.
Add flour a little at a time, beating with wooden spoon.
Knead on floured board for 6 minutes.
Put in greased pan and cover with plastic wrap for 1 1/2 hours or until doubled. Punch down.
Shape into loaf and put in greased pans.
Cover and let raise 30 to 40 minutes in warm place.
Mix egg with water and brush on top.
Bake 2 loaves at 400° for 15 minutes, then 350° for 25 minutes.

title: quiche
directions: Lightly cook onion and bell pepper in margarine. Mix mushrooms, pimentos, Carnation milk, eggs and cream of chicken soup. Mix well. Cook pie shell (9-inch) for 10 minutes in a preheated oven at 400°. Reduce oven temperature at 350°. Put cheese in the bottom of pie shell, then add all ingredients on top of cheese. Cook for 45 minutes.

title: hot deviled potatoes
directions: Prepare 2 servings according to package directions.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Spoon into 2 foil baking shells. Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° about 20 minutes or until heated.

title: cole slaw dressing
directions: Shred cabbage and carrots.
Mix sugar, vinegar, celery salt, egg and margarine and cook over low heat until thick.
Let cool. Add salad dressing.
Pour mixture over cabbage and refrigerate.

title: chicken with lemon and parmesan
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Dip each breast in milk and dredge and pat in bread crumb mixture.
Arrange in a lightly greased 9x9 inch baking dish.Combine melted butter, garlic, and lemon juice.
Drizzle over chicken.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 325 degrees for about 30 or 40 minutes or until tender.
Yield: 4 servings.

title: garlic cheese biscuits
directions: Beat together in a medium mixing bowl the milk, mayonnaise, sugar and flour.
If needed, add enough flour so that dough can be dropped from a spoon and hold its shape.
Streak dough with powdered cheese food.
Drop dough by spoonfuls onto greased baking sheet into 10 equal mounds.
Spray tops with Pam cooking spray; dust each with garlic salt, plus a little more powdered grated cheese food.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes, or until golden brown.
Makes 10 buns.

title: tropical pear chicken salad
directions: Drain and chill pear halves, reserving 1/4 cup syrup. Combine chicken, celery, green onions, almonds, and pineapple. Blend mayonnaise with reserved pear syrup, parsley, salt, and ginger. Toss gently with chicken mixture.
Chill.
Arrange pear halves on each of 4 lettuce lined salad plates.
Spoon chicken salad over pears.

title: meat and potato casserole
directions: Cook
hamburger
meat
and seasonings in skillet.
Peel potatoes and slice potato chip size.
Slice onion.	Boil until tender.
While
meat is cooking, prepare potatoes and onion in microwave
until tender.
Layer in casserole dish:	hamburger, potatoes, onion and mushroom soup.	Continue until ingredients prepared
are gone.
If desired may add cheese on top (optional). Bake
minutes
in
350° to 400° oven.
Serves 4 to 5 people.

title: quick and easy tasty lima beans
directions: Combine all ingredients in saucepan. Cover and simmer for about 10 minutes.

title: turnip green casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except cracker crumbs.
Pour into a lightly greased 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Top with bread crumbs. Bake in a 325° oven for 30 minutes.

title: sausage quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Fully cook sausage.
Drain very well. Combine sausage, onion, cheese, flour and parsley flakes.
Mix well.
Spread in an unbaked pie crust.
Beat together eggs and evaporated milk.
Slowly pour over sausage mixture.
Bake on preheated cookie sheet 35 to 40 minutes or until filling is set.

title: puff bread
directions: Mix eggs, buttermilk and sugar together and let stand for 10 minutes.
Combine flour, soda, salt and baking powder.
Add to egg mixture and let stand 20 minutes.
Place in well-greased bread pans (7 1/4 x 3 1/2-inch).
Makes 3 loaves.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix all together about 5 minutes.
Preheat oven at 350°.
Bake for 1 hour.

title: nena's cream cheese pound cake
directions: Beat cream cheese and butter until fluffy.
Add flavoring and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add salt and flour; stir gently.
Spoon batter into pan which has been greased and floured. Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: linguini margaretta
directions: Saute olives, tomatoes, basil and mushrooms in butter.
Add cheeses and warm, not cook.
Pour over cooked linguini.

title: peanut butter popcorn
directions: Cook to boiling the sugar and light corn syrup.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter and vanilla.
Pour over popped popcorn, stirring to coat.

title: old fashion peanut butter cookies
directions: Stir in the first 4 ingredients and set aside.
In a large bowl with a mixer at medium speed, beat Crisco and peanut butter until smooth.
Beat in sugars until blended; then eggs and vanilla.
Add flour mixture and beat until well blended.
If necessary, chill dough.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten them with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: steak and onions
directions: Cook onions very slowly in 2 tablespoons oil until golden. Remove to warm platter.
Increase heat.
Add remaining oil and quickly brown steaks.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Arrange on a hot platter.
Stir flour into drippings and add water.
Stir constantly until gravy boils.
Serve onions and gravy over steaks. Makes 4 servings.

title: yankee pound cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add milk.
Add flour, baking powder and salt.
Beat well.
Add eggs and vanilla.
The more you beat, the better the cake.
Grease and flour a tube pan.
Pour batter into pan and bake in a 350° oven for 1 1/4 hours.

title: applesauce brownies
directions: Cream together the sugar and shortening in a bowl. Add the rest of the ingredients and combine thoroughly. Pour into a 10 x 16-inch jelly roll pan.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl. Drop by spoonfuls into deep fryer and cook until golden brown.

title: gourmet german pancakes(method:  dutch oven)
directions: In a medium size bowl, mix eggs, flour, milk and salt.
Melt butter in bottom of pie pan.
Pour batter into pie pan.
Place pie pan in Dutch oven; cook for 15 minutes.
(Batter will rise and spread out over edges of pie pan.) Serve hot with a variety of toppings, such as butter, syrup, powdered sugar, fresh berries or sliced bananas.

title: applesauce cookies
directions: Cream shortening; add sugar.
Add beaten egg and applesauce. Add flour sifted with dry ingredients.
Add raisins and nuts. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: shirley's chocolate cake
directions: In bowl, dump sugar and flour.
In boiler, mix cocoa, margarine, oil and water.
Bring to a boil.
Pour over sugar and flour.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Mix by hand.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: choose a fruit twist
directions: Unroll crescent roll dough.
Seal perforations to form 2 rectangles from each package; pat into an 8 x 4-inch rectangle.

title: cauliflower and broccoli casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Steam cauliflower and broccoli 6 minutes or until tender.
Place cauliflower and broccoli into a greased casserole.
Combine soup, sour cream, milk and pepper. Pour over cauliflower and broccoli.
Combine bread crumbs and butter.
Sprinkle over vegetables.
Bake, uncovered, for 20 minutes.

title: fruited chicken salad
directions: In a large bowl combine first 5 ingredients.
Chill well.
In a small bowl blend together the last 3 ingredients.
Add this to coat all ingredients.
Chill.
Serve in an attractive serving dish, garnished with extra oranges if desired.
Serves 6.

title: sausage and egg casserole
directions: For first layer, put the bread cubes in bottom of dish.

title: seven-layered salad
directions: Layer ingredients as follows:
1/2 lettuce, water chestnuts, chopped celery, frozen peas (thawed) and 1/2 cheese.
Spread with mayonnaise like you are icing a cake.
Add remaining lettuce, mayonnaise, cheese, sliced boiled eggs, bacon bits and tomatoes or pepper.

title: easy lemonade pie
directions: Whip lemonade and Cool Whip together; pour into pie shell. Refrigerate for 2 hours before serving.

title: sausage patties
directions: Combine potatoes and sausage.
Add onion, eggs, parsley, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Shape into 8 patties.
Coat with bread crumbs.
Cook in shortening over low heat for 10 minutes.
Turn and cook 10 to 15 minutes.

title: banana-blueberry bread
directions: Cream shortening.
Gradually add sugar, beating until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in bananas.

title: pie shell
directions: Mix thoroughly the Shredded Wheat, butter and sugar.
Press mixture firmly in an even layer against sides and bottom of a lightly greased 9-inch pie pan.
Bake in a hot oven at 400° for 10 minutes.
Cool and fill with lemon meringue filling.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Pour into a 2-quart baking dish. Top with Cheez Whiz.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cover dish to keep cheese from getting too brown. Serves 6.

title: oriental stir-fry chicken
directions: Put chicken in a
bag.	Combine
teriyaki sauce, ginger root and garlic in small
bowl,	pour
over chicken and shake. Marinate 2	to 4
hours.
Remove
chicken
and
discard
mix. Combine chicken broth, soy	sauce
and cornstarch in bowl, set aside. Using wok or skillet, add half tablespoon oil and heat to medium-high heat.
Cook
chicken until tender, take out and drain on paper towel.
Wipe wok
clean and start fresh.
Add 1 teaspoon oil and heat
to medium, add broccoli, cook 2 minutes until tender.
Add
peppers
and	onions and cook until crisp. Take out and set
aside.
Add
to wok broth mixture.
Stir and cook until it thickens
a little, then add chicken and vegetables.
Cook and stir
until
well
heated and serve over rice. Serves five.

title: best pumpkin pie
directions: Combine all ingredients; blend well.
Bake in 400° oven for 20 minutes.
Lower heat to 350° and continue baking for 40 minutes. Check by putting knife in center of pie.
It is done if it comes out clean.

title: deer barbecue
directions: Put meat in a 2 quart pot and bring to a boil.
After it boils, wash the meat.
Then put it back in pot with water and let cook thoroughly.
When it is done, chop it up very fine.
Set meat aside.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix the first 4 dry ingredients together; set aside.
Whisk oil, buttermilk and eggs until well blended.
Add sugar, carrots, pineapple, coconut, walnuts and flour mixture; mix well.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes until toothpick comes out clean.

title: chocolate pie filling
directions: Mix 1 cup sugar, flour and salt in saucepan.
Add milk.
Beat egg yolks.
Cook over medium heat until thick.
Add vanilla and butter or oleo.
Pour into baked 9-inch pie shell.
Beat egg whites until stiff; add 6 tablespoons sugar.
Spread on pie; bake until brown in a 350° oven.

title: aunt flossie's pickled beets
directions: Combine all ingredients except beets in saucepan.
Bring to a boil over medium heat.
Add beets.
Cover saucepan and simmer 10 minutes.
Pour into jar and refrigerate at least 6 hours.

title: pierogies
directions: Combine cream cheese, sour cream, egg yolks, water and salt; mix well.
Add flour; mix well.
Knead until smooth.
Roll out thin on lightly floured surface.
Cut in circles (soup can works well as a cutter).
Place 1 teaspoon filling in center of each circle.
Dampen edges of dough and fold over filling.
Drop in boiling chicken broth; cook for 5 to 10 minutes.
Remove from broth.
Melt butter in skillet and saute onions until soft.
Place pierogi on platter and spoon onions and butter over.

title: el dorado
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and salt in a skillet.
Add the tomato sauce and black olives.
Remove from heat.
In separate bowl, mix the sour cream, cottage cheese and chilies.
Layer in a 9 x 13-inch casserole in the following order:
1/2 chips, 1/2 meat mixture, 1/2 cottage cheese/sour cream mixture and 1/2 cheese.
Repeat layers. Bake in 350° oven for about 35 minutes.

title: spinach-cheese bread
directions: In a medium bowl, combine spinach, pizza sauce, 1 cup Mozzarella cheese, Parmesan cheese and garlic.
Mix well.
Spread 1 tablespoon of mixture on each baguette slice.
Sprinkle with remaining Mozzarella cheese. Broil 4 to 6-inches from heat on ungreased cookie sheet, 2 to 3 minutes or until appetizers are hot, cheese is melted and edges of bread are toasted.
Makes approximately 32.

title: cinnamon sticks
directions: Mix first four ingredients together.
Add more flour if needed.
Roll out dough and cut into strips.
Place on cookie sheet and sprinkle on sugar and cinnamon.
Bake at 415 degrees for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: sees fudge candy
directions: Put the first five ingredients in a large bowl.
Set this aside for a few minutes.
In a saucepan put sugar and milk.
Bring to a boil.
Boil for 6 minutes. Start counting after a full rolling boil has been reached. Pour over the dry ingredients in a large bowl.
Stir and mix well, then pour into buttered pan. Cool. Store in refrigerator until firm enough to cut.

title: salsa
directions: Chop all vegetables and mix together.
Blend sugar, salt and oil and mix in vegetables.

title: orange rice
directions: Melt butter in pan; add celery, onion and orange peel.
Cook until tender.
Add salt, orange juice and water; bring to boiling. Stir in rice.
Cover and let set for 5 minutes.
Serve with Orange Braised Pork Chops.

title: lentil roast
directions: Blend cheese, walnuts and crumbs* in blender.
Brown celery, onion and lentils in 1/4 cup soy oil.
Add all ingredients together and place in greased loaf pan.
Top with catsup if desired.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hummus
directions: Place chickpeas, garlic, olive oil, salt and pepper in blender; blend until smooth paste.
Cut large pita bread into 6 or 8 pieces.
Dip pita into Hummus.

title: funnel cakes
directions: Sift together dry ingredients; set aside.
Mix together egg and milk.
Mix dry and liquid ingredients together.
Beat until smooth.
Fill a small funnel with batter, holding finger over bottom.
Remove finger and let batter drop in a spiral motion into hot oil.
Fry to a golden brown.
Drain on paper towel, then sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
