title: aunt ann's applesauce fruit cake
directions: Mix together applesauce, cinnamon, nutmeg and baking soda. Cream together sugar, butter and oleo.
Add egg.
Add to applesauce mixture.
Blend remaining ingredients together and add raisins. Bake in tube pans at 300° for 1/2 hour and at 275° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: wilted leaf lettuce
directions: Tear lettuce into bite-sized pieces.
Add onions, including tops.
Fry bacon until crisp; keep grease.
Crumble bacon over lettuce.
Beat egg with vinegar and sugar; pour into bacon grease and stir until thickened.
Pour over lettuce while mixture is still hot.
Serve at once.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Beat eggs; stir in remaining ingredients.
Mix ingredients together.
Pour into a greased jelly roll pan (10 x 15 x 1-inch). Spread to edges so middle is not very thick.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Don't overbake.
Loosen cake from edges of pan and invert onto a towel sprinkled with 10x sugar.
While hot, roll up in a towel and cool at least 1 hour.

title: anita's pie crust
directions: Cut crisco into flour, salt, and sugar.
Slightly beat egg, then add water.
Mix until well moistened.
Do not overwork! Crust will be tough.
Makes four 2 crust pies.

title: seafood salad
directions: Mix lobster or crab, mushrooms, bell pepper, olive oil and seasonings.
Serve on lettuce with a good squeeze of fresh lemon juice.
Top with Parmesan cheese.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind together the cranberries with orange.
I also grind some of the orange peel.
Combine Jell-O with 1 cup of hot water.
Use juice of pineapple to make up 1 cup of cold water to add to the hot water and Jell-O after it is dissolved.
When this is setting, before thick, put in crushed pineapple, sugar, the cranberry mixture and nuts, if you wish.

title: new orleans squash casserole
directions: Cook sliced squash in boiling water for about 8 minutes. Drain. Saute onions and peppers in margarine. Add squash and mayonnaise.
Stir in cheese and chestnuts. Beat egg and add to mixture.
Place in 1 1/2 qt. casserole and top with bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
(May use less mayonnaise and a little less cheese.)

title: raisin sour cream pie
directions: Mix sour cream, salt, cinnamon, egg yolks, milk, cornstarch and sugar. Cook until it begins to thicken. Cook about 2 minutes. Add raisins, which have been soaked in hot water. Pour into pie shell. Make meringue out of egg whites and put on top of filling. Bake at 300° for 30 minutes until nicely browned.

title: cole slaw
directions: Mix sugar and eggs; beat well.
Add cornstarch, vinegar and water and mix, then cook until thick.
Pour over slaw.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer all ingredients, ending with dressing.
You can add any ingredients.
Sometimes I add colored spiral pasta and tomatoes. Layer each item.

title: marinated cucumber salad
directions: In large bowl, combine bottled Italian-style cooking sauce, vinegar, sugar, salad oil, water, salt and pepper.
Stir in carrots, cucumbers, green pepper and onion.
Coat with dressing. Cover; refrigerate several hours or overnight, stirring occasionally.
Drain, refrigerating marinade for use another time. Serve in lettuce-lined bowl.
Makes 8 servings.

title: amish persimmon cookies
directions: Cream margarine, 2 c. sugar, and salt.
Add remaining ingredients, except for cinnamon.
Mix well.
Dough is easier to handle if chilled overnight.
Drop by spoon fulls and roll into a mixture of remaining 2/3 c. sugar and cinnamon.

title: easy creamy pumpkin pie
directions: Combine pumpkin, milk, pudding mix and pumpkin pie spices in a mixing bowl and mix well. Fold in whipped cream. Chill or freeze.

title: carrots
directions: Cook carrots.
Add to cooked carrots the onion, green peppers, salt, black pepper, celery and tomato soup.
Cook just until tomato soup is hot.
Enjoy.

title: quick and easy pepper steak
directions: Cut steak into small chunks.
Slice mushrooms, bell pepper and onions.
Salt and cook steak in oil over medium to high until done.
Add mushrooms, pepper and onion.
Stir-fry for 2 to 3 minutes.
Pour gravy mixture over; stir.
Add water and stir well. Let simmer 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serve with rice.

title: hot doggies
directions: If using Corn Flakes, crush into fine crumbs; set aside. Insert skewers lengthwise into frankfurters, leaving about 2-inches for a handle.
Roll frankfurters in catsup, then coat generously with Corn Flake crumbs.
Place in single layer on greased or foil-lined shallow baking pan.
Do not crowd.
Bake in moderately hot oven at 400° about 12 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Serve with additional catsup and mustard, if desired.

title: merry little cheese cakes
directions: Mix flour and brown sugar.
Add softened butter and mix until fine crumbs.
Add nuts.
Reserve 1 cup.
Pat remaining into 8x8-inch pan.
Bake 350° for 8-10 minutes or brown.

title: sugar-free chocolate fudge
directions: In a small mixing bowl, beat the cream cheese, chocolate, sweetener and vanilla until smooth.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into an 8-inch square baking pan lined with foil.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Cut into 16 squares.
Serve chilled.

title: basmati rice pilaf with peas and cashews
directions: Heat oil in large saucepan over medium heat.
Add onion and saute 3 minutes.
Add rice and saute, stirring 1 minute.
Pour boiling water over rice and stir once.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Bring to boil over high heat.
Reduce heat to low. Cover tightly and simmer, without stirring, 12 minutes.
Scatter peas over top in one layer.
Cover and simmer until rice and peas are tender and liquid is absorbed, 3 to 5 minutes.
Fluffy rice gently with fork.
Taste and adjust seasonings.
Serve garnished with cashews.
Serves 4.

title: cheese cake
directions: Soften cream cheese in mixing bowl.
Add sugar and blend in vanilla.
Stir in eggs, one at a time.
Pour in crust and bake at 350°
for 25 minutes.
Cool 15 minutes.
Mix sour cream with 2 tablespoon sugar.
Spread on cake and sprinkle with nutmeg.
You may use either crumb crust or pastry crust.

title: party potatoes
directions: Place in casserole.
Brush with melted butter.
Sprinkle with paprika and chives.
Bake, uncovered, for 20 minutes at 250°.
Can be made day before.

title: hot reuben sandwiches
directions: For each sandwich, spread one slice of bread with mustard. Top with kraut, then several slices of corned beef.
On another slice of bread, place a slice of Swiss cheese.
Place under broiler until cheese is melted and corned beef is warm.
Assemble sandwich and serve with dill pickle.

title: green lima bean casserole
directions: Blend milk with soup; add celery, parsley and lima beans. Place mixture in a baking dish.
Top with onion rings.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: In 3-quart saucepan, bring to boil margarine, water and cocoa. Remove from heat and add flour, sugar and salt sifted together. Beat in eggs, sour cream and soda.
Mix well.
Pour into 2 greased jelly roll pans.
Bake at 375° for 22 to 25 minutes.
Make icing while cake is baking.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix well.
Pour into an 8-inch square greased pan.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: broccoli cheese rice
directions: Cook broccoli.
Cook rice.
Melt margarine in saucepan.
Add flour.
Gradually add milk.
Stir until thickened.
Cook 1 minute. Remove from heat.
Add cheese.
Stir until melted.
Add rice.
In 13 x 9-inch pan, layer 1/3 rice mixture, 1/2 broccoli, 1/3 rice mixture, 1/2 broccoli and 1/3 rice mixture.
Cover and bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Uncover the last few minutes.

title: russian tea mix
directions: Mix together and place in jar.
Use 2 1/2 teaspoons per cup of boiling water.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together.
Beat eggs until light and add.
Blend mashed bananas with creamed mixture.
Sift dry ingredients together and mix with banana mixture.
Add nuts.
Bake about 1 hour at 375°.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: coffee cake
directions: Mix together nuts, sugar and cinnamon and keep separate.
Mix batter well.
Grease Bundt pan.
Place some of chopped nuts on bottom of pan.
Alternate layers of batter and sugar mixture. Bake 50 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.
Let stand 15 minutes and remove from pan.

title: beef stew and rigatoni
directions: Shake beef in a bag with seasoned salt.
Heat oil in 4-quart Dutch oven.
Brown, a few at a time.
Add onion, garlic, 2 teaspoons salt, pepper, oregano and Tabasco sauce.
Add tomato sauce and enough hot water to keep liquid 1 inch above meat (about 3 cups).
Stir well.
Cover tightly and bake in a slow oven (300°) for 2 hours.

title: nachos casserole
directions: Combine taco sauce and chilies in a small bowl; set aside. Cook and stir ground beef and onion in a large skillet over medium-high heat until meat is no longer pink.
Drain.
Add 1 cup cheese, beans, 1/2 taco sauce mixture, water and cumin.
Pour 2 cups cereal into a lightly buttered 12 x 8-inch glass baking dish. Cover with meat mixture.
Top with remaining taco sauce mixture. Sprinkle with remaining cereal.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until heated through.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake until cheese melts.
Garnish with remaining ingredients.
Serves 6.

title: king ranch casserole
directions: Boil chicken and save broth.
Pull chicken into pieces. Soften tortillas in broth and arrange in baking pan (about 13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Cover with chicken, onion and green pepper.
Blend soups, tomatoes and chilies and seasonings in blender.
Pour over tortillas.
Sprinkle cheese on top and bake 30 minutes at 315°. Serves 6.

title: cathedral windows
directions: Melt margarine and chocolate chips in a double boiler.
Remove from heat.
Butter 3 pieces of foil 16 inches long.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar and coconut.
Add pecans and marshmallows to chocolate mixture.
Blend thoroughly.
Divide mixture into 3 equal portions and shape on foil to approximately 14-inch rolls.
Turn to coat with powdered sugar and coconut.
Roll foil around mixture and chill or freeze until firm.
Slice and serve.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Bring sugar, water and Karo to a boil.
Boil until mixture spins a thread about 5 inches long.
Add peanuts, stirring constantly.
Cook until mixture turns a golden brown.
Remove from fire and add salt and butter.
Stir.
Add soda, stirring hard. Pour immediately into a large ungreased cookie sheet.
Spread thin.
Allow to cool, then break into pieces.
Store in covered containers.

title: nut clusters(bark candy)
directions: Microwave bark pieces in microwavable dish for approximately 3 minutes on 50% power or until melted.
Stir in nuts. Mix	well. Drop
by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper on a cookie sheet. Refrigerate until set.

title: amish friendship bread
directions: Combine starter ingredients and let sit, covered, at room temperature.

title: oatmeal cinnamon drops
directions: Cream together margarine and sugar; add eggs, molasses and vanilla.
Combine flour, cinnamon and soda; gradually add to creamed mixture.
Stir in oats, raisins, nuts and chocolate pieces.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes or until light brown.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: escalloped pineapple
directions: Combine bread cubes and pineapple chunks in 2-quart casserole. Beat remaining ingredients together and pour over bread and pineapple.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix together and pour into a well-buttered casserole dish. Let stand overnight. Bake about 1 hour at 350°. May be frozen and cooked later.

title: spoon bread
directions: Heat milk
until hot.
Stir in cornmeal and salt.
Cook while stirring until thickened.
Add butter.
Let cool slightly and stir in beaten eggs.
Pour into greased 1-quart casserole.	Bake in 375° oven 45 minutes to 1 hour.	Serves 4.

title: command performance pasta
directions: Mix sugar and vinegar in small bowl; stir until dissolved and set aside.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugars, vanilla, and eggs. Add peanut butter and then dry ingredients. Mix well. Make into balls and smash with fork. Bake at 350° for 8-10 minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: Layer ingredients in the order listed, spreading evenly into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Do not stir.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until nicely browned on top.
Serve warm topped with whipped cream.

title: chess pie
directions: Cream softened butter and sugar.
Add beaten egg yolks and flour.
Add milk and vanilla.
Pour mixture into unbaked pie crust.
Cover the edge of the pie crust with foil or it will get too brown.
Bake at 300° until the top of pie is brown, then cover complete pie with foil for 10 minutes.
Pie should be done in 30 to 40 minutes.
Cover with meringue.

title: baked turkey wings
directions: Rub piece of lemon over turkey wing, lightly season with salt and pepper.
Bake in oven for 1 1/2 hours at 350°, the last 1/2 hour, raise temperature to 450° to brown turkey wings.

title: sausage balls
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Roll into small balls.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Place on paper towels to absorb excess grease.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix tuna, cream soups, 1 can milk and 1/2 bag chips.
Add peas. Transfer to shallow baking dish. Top with remaining chips.
Bake 30 minutes, uncovered, or until hot.

title: lemon basil grilled chicken
directions: Combine oil and next 7 ingredients in shallow pan.
Add chicken, turning once to coat both sides.
Refrigerate 30 to 45 minutes, turning once more.
Prepare grill or heat broiler.
Grill or broil until completely cooked through.

title: oatmeal bread
directions: Blend in mixer the above ingredients.
Next, by hand, stir in another 2 1/2 to 3 cups flour.
Knead for 8 to 10 minutes.
Put in greased bowl and cover for 1 hour.
Put in warm place to rise. Knead down; form into loaves.
Allow to rise again and bake in a 375° oven for 30 minutes.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Combine cornmeal and flour.
Mix well.
Add 1/2 to 1 cup onions.
Add creamed corn, sugar, eggs, grated cheese, oil and cayenne pepper.
Add milk.
Mix well with spoon.
Pour into greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until golden brown.
Let set one hour before serving.
(The longer it sets, the better it is.)

title: spinach dip
directions: Combine all ingredients; cover and chill at least 2 hours. Serve with an assortment of fresh vegetables.
Yields 2 cups.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix together the ground beef, egg, onion and bread.
Form into meatballs and then roll in cornflake crumbs.
Brown slowly in large or electric skillet, turning each to brown on other side. Drain excess fat.

title: fruit cocktail pie
directions: Combine in saucepan, cornstarch and salt.
Scald milk and slowly add to saucepan.
Cook slow to thicken, about 3 minutes. Add a little to slightly beaten egg yolks and pour into mixture. Cook 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add margarine and stir until melted.
Add 2/3 cup coconut.
Add vanilla, cinnamon and fruit cocktail.
Cool slightly and pour into graham cracker crust. Sprinkle top with rest of coconut.
Chill.

title: nuts and bolts
directions: Mix together and bake at 200° for 2 hours.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together.
Shape into small balls and chill for 1 hour.
Melt chocolate and wax in double boiler over medium heat until chocolate and wax are completely dissolved.
Dip balls one at a time using a toothpick.
Lay on wax paper to cool. Makes approximately 80 to 100 balls.
They freeze very well.

title: corn o'brian
directions: Fry bacon and drain. Saute pepper and onion in bacon drippings until tender.
Drain off excess fat.
Drain corn and mix with other ingredients.
Heat to serving temperature, stirring constantly.

title: sugar plum pudding
directions: Mix the flour, 1 1/2 cups sugar, raisins and cooked apples (optional), 3/4 cup butter, 1 cup milk, cinnamon, nutmeg, eggs and soda.
Put in a sheet pan and bake 25 minutes at 325°.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Mix
spaghetti,
butter,
Parmesan
cheese and eggs together and make crust (9 x 13-inch pan).
Brown beef, onion and pepper in skillet. Add
other
ingredients.
Pour into crust.
Top with cottage cheese and pepperonies.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: no bake fruit cake
directions: Melt butter and marshmallows over low heat.
Crush crackers and mix into marshmallow mixture.
Add raisins, nuts, cherries and candy.
Mix well.
Mold in stem pan.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into 9-inch unbaked pie shell. Bake 40 minutes at 325°.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease two 8 x 8-inch pans.
Mix all ingredients, except cheeses.
Spread 2 tablespoons chicken mix on tortilla.
Put on some of each cheese, roll up and place seam side down.
Cover with foil and bake for 30 minutes.
Remove foil and bake 10 minutes more.
Serve with cheese and sour cream.

title: no peek beef casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in a crock-pot, mixing together well. Cover and cook on low for 8 to 12 hours.
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl and mix well.
Shape into 2 loaves.
Place in loaf pans that have been greased.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.
Remove from pans and let stand for 10 minutes before serving.

title: cajun fried chicken
directions: Combine red pepper, yellow mustard, Tabasco and water to make a sauce.
Cut up fryer into frying pieces; salt chicken pieces. Dip chicken in sauce and roll in flour.

title: best shortcake
directions: Mix in order
given.
Bake
in
350° oven in 8 x 8-inch pan. Use with any kind of fruit.
Very good!

title: zesty tomato salad
directions: Slice tomatoes, cucumbers and onions.
In a salad bowl, add vinegar, olive oil, basil, oregano and garlic.
Mix.
Add your tomatoes, cucumbers and onions.
Mix together.
Marinate ingredients in refrigerator for 2 to 3 hours, then serve.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Let set until you make crust.
If using bought crust, let mixture set about 20 minutes.
Pour mixture into crust.
Add 1 cup pecans to each pie.
Mix in.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes, then 325° approximately 30 minutes.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Microwave oleo in a 4-quart bowl on High for 1 minute or until blended.
Add sugar and milk; mix well.
Microwave on High for 5 minutes until mixture begins to boil.
Stir after 3 minutes.
Mix well; scrape bowl.
Microwave 5 1/2 minutes; stir after 3 minutes. Stir in chocolate pieces until melted.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool at room temperature.
Cut into squares.

title: cream spinach
directions: Saute the onion, garlic, bacon and condiments in butter.
Add flour and cook until a smooth roux is created.
Gradually add milk and cook for several minutes to the consistency of a medium cream sauce.
Chop the spinach very fine.
Then squeeze all the juice from spinach.
Add spinach to sauce; bring to a slow boil and cook 5 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: pepper bread sticks
directions: Cut hot dog rolls in half lengthwise. Cut each half lengthwise to make sticks. Blend butter with pepper and salt.
Spread butter mixture on cut sides of bread sticks.
If desired, press into grated cheese.
Place on baking sheet. Toast in a 450° oven about 8 minutes or until golden brown. Serve hot.
Makes 24 sticks.

title: people puppy chow
directions: Melt margarine, chocolate and peanut butter in saucepan.
Add cereal, stir gently to coat all pieces.
Cool slightly.
In brown grocery bag, pour in confectioners sugar.
Shake cereal in sugar to dust all pieces.
Serve in large ceramic "dog" dish.
Kids love this.

title: jello salad
directions: Mix Jell-O according to box directions.
Add drained fruit cocktail and bananas and Cool Whip.

title: rhubarb bread
directions: Mix ingredients together, adding rhubarb and nuts last.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: salsa
directions: In a bowl or pan, place peeled tomatoes.
Using 2 knifes, slice until desired consistency.
Add tomato paste, chilies, onion and garlic.
Mix with a spoon until well blended.
Enjoy!

title: hodge-podge
directions: Butter sides of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread cherry pie filling on the bottom.
Add pineapple juice also.
Then, sprinkle cake mix evenly over pineapple.
Melt oleo and slowly pour over the cake mix.
Top with chopped nuts and bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: fried cabbage
directions: Place bacon in a large, deep skillet.
Cook over medium-high heat until evenly brown.
Remove bacon, and set aside.
Cook onion in the hot bacon grease until tender.
Add cabbage, and stir in water, sugar, salt, and pepper.
Cook until cabbage wilts, about 15 minutes.
Stir in bacon.
Splash with vinegar before serving.

title: choco-scotch clusters
directions: Melt morsels and peanut butter in saucepan over low heat. Remove from heat and stir in cereal until well coated.
Drop by spoonful onto waxed paper or buttered baking sheet.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: "spanakoryzo" - spinach and rice
directions: Saute rice and onion in olive oil, stirring occasionally, 15 minutes.
Add boiling water and salt; cover and simmer 10 minutes. Wash spinach; cut in 1/2-inch lengths.
Add to rice.
Mix thoroughly; cover and continue to simmer, stirring occasionally, 15 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: white sugar cookies
directions: Cream powdered sugar, white sugar, butter and vegetable oil. Add eggs, flour, soda, cream of tartar and vanilla.
Chill.
Roll into balls and press down with a glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: salsa
directions: Chop tomatoes, peppers and add remaining ingredients; put in refrigerator 4 hours.

title: biscuits for dixie fried chicken
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and soda.
Stir in butter and fat. Add buttermilk to make a stiff dough.
Knead lightly.
Roll out on floured board.
Cut in to small rounds.
Bake for 20 minutes at 375°.

title: steak and noodles
directions: Put all ingredients into crock-pot.
Cook on high for 3 hours, stirring occasionally.
Serve over hot buttered noodles.
(White rice is good, too.)

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix with electric mixer cream cheese and peanut butter, then add
milk. After it is mixed well add powdered sugar at a slow speed.
Scrape
sides and bottom of bowl to be sure it is mixed well.
Add	Cool Whip.
After it is mixed well, put into chocolate or
graham
cracker
crust.
Top with whipped cream topping. Makes 3 pies.

title: delicious broiled trout
directions: Cover the broiler pan with aluminum foil.
Remove the head of the fish.
Cut down the backbone to open the fish.
Wash and dry the opened trout thoroughly.
Turn the oven to broil and place the trout, skin side down, on the broiler pan.
Season with salt and pepper and broil 5 minutes, 3 inches from the heat.
Baste with melted butter seasoned with salt and pepper.
Broil 10 minutes longer or until trout is dry and flaky.
Serve with tartar sauce or horseradish mixture and ketchup.

title: golden punch
directions: Empty juice and corn syrup in punch bowl.
Add sherbet and ice. Pour ginger ale over mixture.
Allow most of ice to melt.
Garnish with thin slices of orange.
Yields 40 servings.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine first six ingredients in mixing bowl. Chill until firm.
Shape into ball.
Roll in pecans to coat.
Serve with crackers.

title: lemonade concentrate(servings: 24.  preparation time: 1 hour and 15 minutes.)
directions: Combine sugar and water in a small saucepan; bring to a boil and boil for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat; cool slightly.
Reserve one lemon to slice for garnish.
Grate zest of two lemons; juice eight lemons.
Combine juice and zest with warm syrup.
Steep one hour.
Strain.

title: mexican corn casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour in glass 8 x 12-inch pan and bake until golden brown.

title: dutch green beans
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Remove from skillet.
Add onion to 1 tablespoon drippings.
Cook until tender.
Blend in cornstarch, salt and mustard.
Drain beans, reserving 1/2 cup liquid.
Stir in reserved liquid.
(Do not add beans yet.)
Cook and stir constantly until thick and translucent.
Blend in sugar and vinegar.
Add beans and heat thoroughly.
Top with bacon pieces and egg (chopped).
Makes 4 servings.

title: molten chocolate cake
directions: Butter and flour 5 to 6-ounce ovenproof custard cups or ramekins. Melt chocolate and butter over hot water in a double boiler; cool slightly. Beat eggs, yolks and sugar with electric mixer on medium-high until pale yellow (about 10 minutes). Reduce speed and add flour gradually. Add melted chocolate and beat until glossy (5 minutes). Pour mixture evenly into prepared cups. Bake at 325° for 12 minutes or until set around edges but centers still move slightly. While still warm, turn out of custard cups upside down onto plate or serve in ramekins. Dust with confectioners sugar and serve immediately over vanilla custard sauce.

title: snowball cookies
directions: Combine peanut butter, honey, 1/2 cup coconut, vanilla and dry milk. Mix well.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Roll in remaining coconut. Yields 15 to 20 snowballs.

title: frozen peanut butter pie
directions: Cream all together.
Add medium size bowl of Cool Whip. Freeze it.

title: chicken pot dinner
directions: Place chicken in large heavy ovenware pot.
Peel potatoes, slice 1/2-inch thick; place on top of chicken.
Peel and quarter onion.
Peel carrots and cut lengthwise.
Place carrots, beans, parsley flakes and pepper on top of potatoes.
Pour sherry over all.
Cover tightly.
Bake at 300° for 2 hours.

title: beef pot pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together in boiler, then pour into pie crust; use one for top.
Cut 3 or 4 places in crust on top. Press edges together around pan.
Put in oven at 325°.
Cook until brown, then serve.

title: strawberry blossoms
directions: Remove stems from berries, forming a flat base.
Place berries, pointed end up.
With sharp knife, carefully slice berry in half vertically through center to within 1/4 inch of base.
Cut each half into 3 wedges, forming 6 petals (do not slice through base).
Pull petals apart slightly.
In small bowl, beat the cream cheese, powdered sugar and sour cream until light and fluffy. With pastry bag and star tip or small spoon, fill berries with cream cheese mixture.
Use as garnish on cakes or as a mini dessert.

title: cranberry bars
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Stir in butter and mix well.
Reserve 1 cup of flour-oat mixture for the topping.
Pat the remaining oat mixture into an ungreased 12 x 7 x 2-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: korean salad
directions: Wash, dry and remove stems from spinach; tear into pieces into a large bowl.
Add bean sprouts, water chestnuts, eggs and bacon. Toss lightly.
Add dressing and toss again.

title: ice cream salad
directions: Roll Ritz crackers with rolling pin.
Save 1/2 cup aside and put rest in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt oleo and pour over crackers, pat down.

title: oreo cookie cheese cake
directions: Combine cookie crumbs and margarine and press into bottom and 1 1/2 inches up side of 9-inch spring-form pan.
Soften gelatin in water.
Stir over low heat until dissolved.
Combine cream cheese and sugar, mixing at medium speed on electric mixer until well blended.
Gradually add gelatin and milk, mixing until blended. Chill until mixture is thickened but not set.
Fold in Cool Whip. Reserve 1 1/2 cups cream cheese mixture.
Pour over crust remaining cream cheese mixture.
Top with chopped cookies and reserved cream cheese mixture.
Chill until firm.
Sprinkle a bit of crushed cookies on top for decoration.

title: polenta
directions: In a large heavy pot, bring the water to a boil; add salt. Add the cornmeal in a thin stream, stirring all the while with a wooden spoon.
Cook, stirring constantly, over medium heat until the mixture thickens and begins to leave the side of the pan, about 15 to 25 minutes, depending on the coarseness of the cornmeal.
Immediately pour the Polenta onto a lightly oiled wooden board or platter.
Let it cool for 15 minutes, then cut into slices.
Serve with Salsa Fresca de Pomodori.

title: butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat the following:
sugar, butter and eggs.
Beat until fluffy, then add buttermilk, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Add flour to stiffen dough.
Roll and cut out.
Bake for 5 to 10 minutes.

title: german preserve cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, and vanilla. Mix well.
Sift flour and spices together; add alternately with buttermilk to which soda has been added.
Mix well and fold in the preserves and pecans.
Bake in a greased tube pan at 325° for 90 minutes.
This is a moist cake.
Freezes well.

title: low country boil for 10
directions: Using a large pot (such as a turkey fryer), half fill with water.
Bring to the boil and add the bottle of Zatarain's, the artichokes and lemons.
Bring back to the boil and add the potatoes and the sausage.
Wait 10 minutes, then add the first 5 lobsters. For 1 1/4 pounds, cook for 12 minutes.
For a 2 pound lobster, cook for 18 minutes.
Cook the second batch of lobsters, then remove everything from the pot and enjoy.
Melt the butter with the garlic and serve on the side.

title: chili anyone can eat!
directions: Cook beef, onion and green pepper until meat is brown.
Drain. Place all ingredients in large pan and simmer for 1 to 2 hours.

title: cheese ball
directions: First: Chop 3/4 cup olives coarsely. Soften cream cheese. Add Blue cheese, grated Cheddar cheese, Worcestershire sauce and liquid pepper seasoning, beat until smooth. Mix chopped olives with cheeses.

title: egg rolls
directions: Saute beef and onions in skillet until cooked. Add sprouts, chestnuts and drained mushrooms.
Stir-fry for 2 minutes.
Roll out crescent rolls, flattening with rolling pin. Cut each square in half.
Place 2 or 3 teaspoons of mixture in each half and seal by folding ends of dough together. Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: orange sherbet
directions: Mix all together and pour in ice cream churn.
Churn until hard.

title: vidalia onion bake
directions: Mix together and put into 2 qt. greased casserole.

title: wild rice casserole
directions: Fry bacon and reserve a little grease to fry chopped onion and celery.
Add mushrooms.
Combine these with wild rice.
Mix together with mushroom soup.
Bake in greased casserole.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: mushroom canapes
directions: Chop mushrooms fine.
Saute 5 minutes in butter.
Blend in flour and salt.
Stir in light cream (or milk).
Cook until thick. Add chives and lemon juice.
Spread mixture on lightly buttered triangles of Melba thin bread.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes.
Can freeze before baking, if desired.
Makes approximately 36 triangles.

title: super easy peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix
all
ingredients except peanut butter.
Cook until forms firm
ball	when
dropped in cup of cold water.
Remove from heat and beat until it starts to get thicker.
Add peanut butter
and beat until blended.
Pour into buttered pan.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: hungarian goulash
directions: Brown steak in fat; cook in water until done.
Add onions and spices.
Add potatoes and cook until done.
Thicken with flour.

title: apple crisp
directions: Arrange apples in greased 8 x 8 x 2 pan. Mix remaining ingredients with fork. Sprinkle over apples. Bake at 375° until apples are tender and topping is golden brown, about 30 minutes. Serve with cream, ice cream or hard sauce, if desired. Yields 6 servings.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook butternut squash.
Drain and mash.
Add all other ingredients.
Pour in casserole dish and bake in 350° oven until bubbly and brown.

title: coconut-pineapple pie
directions: Mix and pour into 2 uncooked pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: ham and cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients in a mixing bowl.
Thoroughly mix and roll into a ball.
Chill and serve with your favorite crackers.

title: richard's delight
directions: Combine ingredients and spread a rounded teaspoon on rye bread slices. Bake at 325° for 10 minutes or until cheeses are melted and bread toasted. Can be made ahead and baked when ready. Makes 35 to 40 appetizers.

title: spicy trail bologna
directions: Mix all together.
Knead well.
Shape into 5 rolls and wrap in wax paper.
Refrigerate 24 hours.
Remove wax paper.
Bake on a slotted rack at 300° for 1 hour or at 200° for 3 1/2 to 4 hours.

title: holiday fruit cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and eggs.
Add milk.
Sift flour, soda and salt and add to sugar mixture.
Add fruit and nuts.
Drop by spoonful on ungreased cookie sheet and bake for 8 to 10 minutes at 400°.

title: pastry for pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients and shortening.
In separate dish, mix egg, vinegar and water. Mix all together with fork (real sticky). Chill 15 minutes.
Yields crust for 2 double crust pies.

title: creole onions
directions: Place onions in baking dish.
Add green pepper, celery, tomatoes and seasonings.
Cover and bake until tender, about 1 hour, at 350°.
Serves 4.

title: best pumpkin pie
directions: Mix first eight ingredients and pour into pie shell.
Bake 1 hour at 350° or until firm in middle.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and taco sauce together until smooth. Put shredded cheese on top of mixture. Top off with sliced olives.

title: quick chili
directions: Brown hamburger meat in skillet. Pour pork and beans in saucepan. Add all ingredients. Bring to boil. Add hamburger meat and let simmer for at least 30 minutes. Serve with or without noodles.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix all together and store in airtight jar.
Use amount per cup to taste.

title: jello waldorf salad
directions: Bring 1 cup apple juice to a boil. Dissolve Jell-O.
Add ice cubes to 1/2 cup juice to make 1 cup.
Mix into Jell-O.
Add all the rest of the ingredients to make salad.
(Strawberry flavor is good also.)

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers and onions; cut peppers in strips.
Soak overnight in 1/2 cup canning salt.
Drain well.
Bring vinegar, sugar and spices to a boil.
Add vegetables and let it come to a boil for 15 minutes.
Pack in hot jars and seal.

title: sorry cookies
directions: Mix ingredients, stirring well. Drop by teaspoon on lightly greased cookie sheet at least 2-inches apart.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: watergate cake
directions: Beat all together until smooth. Bake 40 minutes at 350° in a long pan or in layers.
Ovens vary.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Simmer onion in margarine until brown.
Add water, milk and cheese and stir until melted.
Add broccoli, rice, soup and mix.
Pour in 1 1/2-quart dish and bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti; put in large bowl and add all ingredients. Toss. Refrigerate overnight or all day.

title: sausage bake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Take a 13 x 9 baking pan.
I use my cookie sheet.

Layer out and cover bottom of pan with 1 can crescent rolls, tucking all spaces together around edge; pinch up. Spread sausage and cream cheese mixture; top with second can of crescent rolls around edge.
Pinch together the two crusts.
Bake at 375° until rolls are lightly browned, about 10 to 15 minutes.

title: veal piccatta
directions: With meat mallet, pound cutlets to 1/8 inch thickness. Sprinkle with salt and pepper and coat with flour.
In skillet, over medium-high heat, in olive oil and butter, cook veal until lightly browned on both sides.
Reduce heat to low.

title: sausage sandwich spread
directions: Saute sausage and hamburger;
drain.
Mix with remaining ingredients.
Heat to serve.
Spread
on rye bread or crackers. Excellent for hors d'oeuvres.

title: cinnamon sticky buns
directions: Cut biscuits in half.
Roll in mixture of cinnamon and sugar. Put in greased Bundt pan.
Layer biscuits.
Melt butter, brown sugar and water.
Boil 2 minutes.
Pour over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: jello gelatin rainbow cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on package.
Bake in a greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool cake in pan 15 minutes; then prick with a utility fork at 1/2-inch intervals.
Meanwhile, dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add orange juice and pour carefully over warm cake.
Chill at least 2 hours.
Garnish as desired.

title: dream rolls
directions: Scald milk.
Let cool until lukewarm. Add sugar, shortening, yeast and flour.
Beat until smooth.
Let rise until double in bulk.
Work down. Roll out and double back.
Re-roll and cut with biscuit cutter.
Let rise and bake at 425°.

title: hot cheese dip
directions: Brown sausage with hamburger.
Put in crock-pot, then add Velveeta (cubed) and rest of ingredients.
Set temperature to medium.
Stir until cheese melts and serve warm with Doritos.

title: deep dish pie
directions: Melt butter in baking dish.
Blend flour, sugar and milk and pour over butter.
Add fruit on top of mixture.
Crust will form on top.
Bake in 300° oven until brown.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into a large Pyrex dish.
Chill 3 to 4 hours.
This can be frozen.

title: church women united vegetable soup(recipes from hunger slide show)
directions: Cook 1 1/2 hours.
Makes 14 cups or 10 large servings.

title: delicious fruit salad
directions: Mix undrained pineapple and lemon pudding; let set.
Drain fruit cocktail and oranges and mix with pineapple/pudding.
Fold whipped topping into fruit.
Chill.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute first 3 ingredients in oleo.
Add pepper.
Cook broccoli; drain.
Add rice, soup, Cheez Whiz and hot sauce.
Mix and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook ingredients in Dutch oven on top of stove for 1/2 hour.

title: barbecue beef shortribs
directions: In a Dutch oven, brown ribs in oil.
Add 2 cups water; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 1 1/2 hours. Drain.
Combine the tomato paste, ketchup, garlic, brown sugar, onion, vinegar, mustard, salt and remaining water; mix well.
Pour over the ribs.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 1 hour or until meat is tender.
Serve over noodles, if desired.
Yield:
4 to 6 servings.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Melt chocolate and butter in saucepan.
Add sugar and milk. Cook until boiling.
Boil for 3-4 minutes, stirring constantly. Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Drizzle on your favorite ice cream.

title: beef and potato loaf
directions: Arrange sliced potatoes and onion in greased 2 quart dish. Sprinkle salt, pepper and parsley flakes.
Combine meat, milk, cracker crumbs, catsup/chili.
Spread over sliced potatoes.
Bake in the oven at 350° for 1 hour.
Decorate with catsup, if desired.

title: "old fashioned" sugar cookies
directions: Thoroughly cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg and beat well. Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with milk and vanilla. Mix thoroughly.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs and sugar well.
Add next 5 ingredients in order given.
Pour into pie crusts.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: crock-pot baked beans
directions: Fry bacon (cut up) and onion in skillet.
Mix with remaining ingredients.
Cook in crock-pot on low, covered for 6 hours and uncovered for 45 minutes.

title: peanut butter bonbons
directions: In 3-quart saucepan, over low heat, melt butter.
Stir in milk, vanilla and salt.
Mix well.
Remove from heat.
Gradually add 1 1/2 cups confectioners sugar, stirring until mixture is thick and smooth.
Add peanut butter and corn syrup; mix well.
Turn out onto board lightly sprinkled with remaining confectioners sugar.
Knead until consistency of fondant.
Form slightly rounded teaspoon of dough into balls.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cook frozen vegetables in butter.
Drain.
Combine remaining filling ingredients with vegetables and mix well.
Set aside.

title: lite fruit salad
directions: Note:
Any fresh or canned fruit can be added.

title: soft sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add vanilla and eggs.
Add oil; mix well.
Add dry ingredients.
Roll into balls and dip in sugar or sugar and cinnamon.
Press with glass.
Bake at 325° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Make good sized batch.

title: salmon party log
directions: Drain and flake salmon.
Remove skin and bones.
Combine salmon with next 6 ingredients; mix well and chill.
Form into a log; roll in pecans and parsley.
Serve chilled with a variety of crackers or vegetables (raw).

title: stuffed pepper soup
directions: Brown ground beef - Drain.
Add rest of the ingredients. Bring to boil.
Reduce Heat.
Cover and simmer for 15-20 minutes or until peppers are tender.

title: salsa #2
directions: Cook vegetables, vinegar, sugar, salt and seasonings for 40 minutes.
Thicken with cornstarch.
Ladle into pint jars.
Process 20 minutes at 10 pounds pressure.
Yields approximately 18 pints.

title: baker's icing
directions: In a saucepan, combine the milk and cornstarch.
Cook until thick and set aside to cool.
In a bowl, cream the shortening, butter and sugar with an electric mixer for about 10 minutes.
Add the creamed mixture to the milk mixture.
Add the salt and vanilla.
Beat together with the mixer until creamy like whipped cream.

title: pecan balls
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients except confectioners sugar. With hands, mix thoroughly.
Refrigerate 30 minutes. Preheat oven to 375°.
Using hands, roll dough into balls 1 1/4-inches thick. Pat 1-inch apart on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until cookies are set, but not brown.
Let stand 1 minute before removing from cookie sheet.
Cool slightly. Roll in confectioners sugar while still warm. Cool completely. Roll in sugar before serving.

title: microwave sweet and sour chicken
directions: Cut chicken in 1/2-inch cubes.
Coat with flour, sugar and salt mixture and place in 1 1/2 to 2-quart dish.
Mix soy sauce, vinegar and water and pour over chicken.
Top with sliced onions and bell pepper.
Microwave 6 minutes.
Stir and cook 6 minutes more.
Check chicken for doneness.
If not done, microwave for 1 to 2 minutes more and check again.

title: oil pie crust
directions: Stir flour, salt and sugar together. Add oil and milk; mix well.
Press into pan. Bake at 400° until brown.
This fits a 9-inch pan.

title: pork chops in sour cream
directions: Brown chops in shortening.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Drain off excess fat and add onions.
Dissolve bouillon cube in water and pour over chops.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Add more water if necessary.
Remove chops from broth.
Combine sour cream and flour; stir slowly into broth.
Serve gravy with onions; garnish with parsley.

title: slime
directions: Mix together.
This is a fun "toy" for children.

title: turkey sausage succotash
directions: Heat the oil in a 12-inch skillet over moderate high heat for 1 minute.
Add the sausage and saute, stirring occasionally for 5 minutes.
Drain on paper towel.

title: oreo cookie ice cream
directions: Beat egg yolks, stir in milk, water and vanilla. Fold in cookies and cream. Place in freezer safe container and freeze for six hours or until firm.

title: pumpkin soup with cheddar and parmesan(great for the holidays)
directions: Saut bacon in heavy large pan over medium heat until brown, about 8 minutes.
Pour off drippings.
Add onions, carrots and celery and saut until vegetables begin to soften, about 15 minutes.

title: cranberry two-tone salad
directions: In a medium saucepan, stir together the sugar and unflavored gelatin.
Add the cranberry juice cocktail; heat and stir until gelatin is completely dissolved.
Stir in ginger ale, the 3/4 cup chopped cranberries and the cranberry liqueur.
Turn into a 6 to 7 cup mold (cranberries will float).
Cover; chill until almost set, about 60 minutes.

title: cocoa syrup
directions: Mix all ingredients together and boil 3 minutes.
Makes 2 cups.
Store in refrigerator.
Use to make chocolate milk.

title: libby burgers
directions: Mix all together, except soup and mushrooms; form patties.
Brown well.
Pour off any fat accumulation.
Add soup (add very small amount of water) and mushrooms.
Simmer 15 minutes, stirring occasionally to prevent sticking or until done. Serve with mashed potatoes, green beans, hot rolls and salad.
Mmm good.

title: applesauce nut bread
directions: Mix sifted dry ingredients and nuts together.
Combine egg, applesauce and oil; add to the dry ingredients and stir until blended.
Pour into a 5 x 9-inch greased loaf pan.
Bake in a moderate oven, at 350°, for 50 minutes.

title: toad-in-the-hole
directions: Brown the sausage (loose sausage also works); drain.
Mix the flour, baking powder and salt.
Add the milk and beaten eggs; beat until smooth.
Place sausage in greased 10 x 6 x 2-inch dish; sprinkle with bacon.
Pour batter over.
Bake at 400° until set, approximately 30 to 35 minutes.
Serve with maple syrup.

title: pasta fagioli (beans)
directions: Sear bacon, until most of the fat has melted.
Discard all melted fat and put bacon aside.
Sear onion in olive oil, until slightly brown.
Put in Del Monte sauce, allow to cook about 5 minutes.
Stir in bacon and pork and beans.
Sprinkle sweet basil. Heat 2 more minutes.
In a large pot, cook ditalini as directed. Add salt to water.
Drain and add mixture, mixing it very well. Heat together 3 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: beet pickles
directions: Add sugar and spice to vinegar and water; simmer for 15 minutes, then add prepared beets in jar and fill with liquid to cover beets and seal.

title: party meatballs
directions: Combine meat, onion, egg, crumbs, salt, pepper, Accent, water and catsup.
Mix well.
Shape into meatballs.
Brown in small amount of fat.
Combine chili sauce, jelly, lemon and Tabasco.
Add meatballs and cook 10 minutes over medium heat.

title: cheesy dog
directions: Combine cheese, chili sauce and pickle relish; mix well. Spread cheese mixture over inside of bun.
Place hot dog on top of cheese mixture.
Wrap filled bun in paper towel.
Microwave on High (100%) 1 minute or until cheese is melted and hot dog is warm.
Serve immediately.
Makes 1 serving.

title: grilled teriyaki corn on the cob(china)
directions: Remove husk from corn.
Lay each ear of corn on a piece of foil large enough to wrap around it.
Brush lightly with teriyaki baste and glaze.
Wrap foil around corn and seal edges.
Cook on a grill for 20-30 minutes or until corn is tender.
Turn frequently.
(Or bake on a baking sheet at 325F for 30 minutes, turn 1 time.)

title: pea salad
directions: This recipe tastes best if prepared at least a couple of hours ahead of serving time.
Pour baby peas into bowl large enough to allow mixing of other ingredients.
Cook bacon until crisp, then crumble to fairly small bits.
Chop onion finely.
When peas are unfrozen but still quite cold, add onion and bacon.
Add enough mayonnaise to suit your taste.
Add salt and pepper.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Brown ground beef, onions and bell pepper.
Add salt and pepper.
Drain off excess fat, add tomatoes, mushroom soup and mushrooms.
Cook noodles in salty water until tender and drain. Add to beef mixture.
Pour into 9-inch baking dish.
Bake at 450° for 25 minutes.
Sprinkle cheese over casserole and return to oven for 5 minutes.

title: tapioca peach cobbler
directions: Put
undrained	peaches
in
12-inch
Dutch
oven
with tapioca and stir.
Mix cake according to directions in another bowl.
Pour
evenly over peaches.
Cook for 25 minutes with 14 coals on top and 8 on bottom.

title: homemade salsa
directions: Mix together and use wherever salsa is needed.

title: granny's cherry pie
directions: Heat oven to 425°.

title: date balls
directions: Melt margarine; add dates and sugar.
Cook over low heat until dates are melted.
Add coconut, nuts and Rice Krispies.
Mix well. Form into small balls.
Dip in powdered sugar.

title: old fashioned sour cream cookies
directions: Sift together the flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt. Cream shortening with sugar.
Add eggs; beat well.
Add cream alternately with flour mixture.
Add vanilla.
Chill at least 1 hour.
Drop by spoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes at 400°.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: butter scotch candy
directions: Melt morsels; stir in peanuts and noodles.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper.
Makes about 5 dozen pieces.

title: cheese bread
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes. Saute onion in 1 tablespoon butter until golden.
Mix egg and milk; blend in Bisquick.
Add onion and half of cheese.
Spread dough in greased 8 x 11-inch round glass baking dish.
Sprinkle top with remaining cheese and sesame seed.
Sprinkle melted butter over all.

title: butter caramel popcorn
directions: Place popped corn in large shallow roasting pan.
In heavy 2-quart saucepan, stir brown sugar, corn syrup, butter and salt. Stir constantly and bring to boil over medium heat.
Without stirring, boil 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla and baking soda.
Pour over popcorn and stir to coat well.
Bake in a 250° oven, stirring once every 15 minutes.
Pour popcorn out on large piece of aluminum foil sprayed with vegetable spray.
Break apart as it cools and store in airtight container.

title: diabetic pound cake
directions: Sift flour and soda.
Add oil and sugar substitute; mix well until light.
Beat eggs.
Add rest.
Beat until well mixed.
Pour into 2 layer pans or pour into 1 long loaf pan (greased and floured).
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: crustless crab quiche
directions: Heat oven to 350 degrees.
Lightly coat a 10 inch glass pie pan with cooking spray.
Set aside.
In large nonstick skillet heat olive oil over medium low heat.
Add onion and saute 2 to 3 minutes until soft.
Add tomatoes and green onion.
Cook 3-4 minutes until tomatoes give up moisture but not until soupy. Remove from heat and cool slightly.
In medium bowl combine crab, salt, white pepper, dill and parsley.
Stir in tomato and onion mixture.
Toss to mix evenly.
Pour egg substitute on top, stir well.
Transfer to pie pan.
Sprinkle parmesan cheese on top. Bake for 30 to 35 minutes or until set.
Cool 10 - 15 minutes before cutting.

title: potato soup
directions: Mix butter, milk, water, celery and onions; cook until celery and onions are tender.
Add potatoes and a little bit of water. Add milk-flour mixture and mushrooms.
Stir until thickened.
Keep on warm stove until served.
You can add 2 slices of cooked, crumbled bacon for extra flavor.
Serves 6.

title: prune bread(low-fat)
directions: Grease and flour 2 loaf pans.
Process prunes in boiling water in blender or processor 10 seconds.
Add sugar and eggs, process 1 minute.
Add oil and process one minute.
Add orange juice and flour; beat well.
Bake 1 hour until brown.
Cool before removing from pans.
(1 1/2 inch slice = 92 calories.
Leave off 1 starch and 1 bread.)

title: cheese ball
directions: Warm ingredients at room temperature.
Roll in nuts and parsley. Butter hands!

title: slow cooker punch
directions: Steep tea bags in boiling water 5 minutes.
Discard bags.
Put tea in slow cooker. Wrap all spices in spice ball (cheesecloth) and add to tea.
Stir in sugar and cranberry juice.
Cover cooker and cook on high for 1 hour.
Add wine and cook on low for 4 to 8 hours.

title: cider salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 2 cups hot apple cider; stir in raisins. Let cool.
Add remaining cider and chill until consistency of unbeaten egg white.
Stir in apples, celery, lemon rind and juice. Pour into lightly oiled 6-cup mold.
Chill until set.
Unmold onto lettuce leaves.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: rice pilaf
directions: Brown ground chuck. Drain. Add onions, peppers and garlic; saute. Add mushrooms and tomatoes. Let simmer on low in a large skillet. Add salt, pepper and ketchup to taste. Add cooked rice. Heat thoroughly.

title: easy beef stew
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in ovenproof pot with lid.
Cook at 350° for 3 hours.

title: lemon cake top pudding
directions: Cream the butter. Add sugar gradually and cream together until light and fluffy. Add egg yolks and beat well. Add flour, lemon juice, rind and salt.
Mix well. Stir in milk.
Blend in 1/4 cup almonds. Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into mixture.
Pour into loaf baking dish, 9 x 5-inches.
Set in pan of hot water and bake in a slow oven at 325° for 40 minutes. Turn thermostat to 350° and continue baking until brown, about 10 minutes. Sprinkle with remaining almonds.
May be served either warm or chilled.

title: hamburger surprise
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on box; drain.
Saute hamburger, onion and pepper in large skillet until done.
Drain well in large pan.
Combine hamburger, macaroni, cheese packet, tomato soup and mushrooms if desired.
Heat over medium heat until bubbly.
Serves 4.

title: shoepeg corn salad
directions: Combine salt, sugar, mustard, vinegar and oil.
Add rest of ingredients and marinate
in refrigerator overnight.
This is a very good keeper.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Cut up vegetables in small pieces. Add meat, bones and tomato paste. Cover vegetables and meat with water. Season to taste and simmer about 2 hours. Add water as needed.

title: pioneer bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water in large mixing bowl.
Add sugar, salt, egg, shortening, 1/3 cup cornmeal and 1 cup flour.
Blend 1/2 minute on low speed, scraping bowl constantly.
Beat 2 minutes on medium speed, scraping bowl occasionally.
Stir in enough remaining flour to make dough easy to handle.
Turn dough onto lightly floured surface; knead until smooth and elastic, about 5 minutes.
Place in greased bowl; turn greased side up.
Cover; let rise in warm place until double, 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: mock apple pie
directions: Mix water, sugar and cream of tartar; bring to a rolling boil. Let cool.
Pour into pie crust and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Dot with butter and bake 30 to 35 minutes at 450°.

title: a vegetarian's delight
directions: Combine ingredients in wok or frying pan.
Add salt to taste.

title: homemade noodles
directions: Beat eggs; add salt.
Add flour until you can work it into a ball.
On floured breadboard, roll out dough until very thin.
Use lots of flour.
Cover with tea towel and let dry.
Roll up as a jelly roll and slice into 1/4-inch noodles.
Sprinkle with flour. Bring broth (2 quarts) to rolling boil.
Add noodles; cover and cook on low for 30 minutes.
Good with beef or chicken.

title: mocha frosting
directions: Mix ingredients together, adding enough milk to make of spreading consistency.

title: quick sauteed scallops
directions: Soak scallops in milk briefly.
Drain scallops; dredge them in seasoned flour.
Place in large sieve and shake to remove excess flour.
Scatter on waxed paper to dry slightly.
Cook scallops over high heat without crowding.
Heat 3 tablespoons oil and 1 tablespoon butter in skillet until quite hot.
Cook half of scallops, shaking and tossing until golden brown on all sides. Transfer to hot platter.
Add 1 tablespoon oil to pan and cook remainder of scallops.
Wipe out pan and cook remaining butter until brown.
Sprinkle over scallops with lemon juice and chopped parsley.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: knoephla soup
directions: Put all ingredients except milk and chives in a kettle and cook until tender. Add milk and chives and bring to a boil. Add Knoepla, then reduce heat to simmer for 10 minutes.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and sour cream.
Spread in 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Mix shrimp and cocktail sauce, spread over cream cheese mixture and chill.
Serve with crackers or tortilla chips.

title: coconut custard impossible pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in a 10-inch pie pan at 300° until filling leaves a knife inserted in center.

title: alex's beet soup
directions: Peel, seed and slice cucumbers.
Peel and slice lemons.
Bring stock to a boil and pour over cucumbers, lemon slices and julienne beets.
Add sherry and garlic to taste.
Let steep for 2 hours. Strain and reheat.
Garnish with sliced beets.
Do not let the soup boil for it will cloud.
It should be clear, ruby red.

title: cowboy casserole
directions: Fry hamburger meat.
In casserole dish, put layer of chips (crushed), layer of hamburger meat, layer of beans and layer of rice.
Repeat until all is used.
Put layer of crushed tortilla chips on top and cover with layer of grated cheese on top.
Bake at 350° until brown on top.

title: persimmon cake
directions: Cream margarine, eggs, soda, sugar, persimmon pulp and vanilla.
Add flour, cinnamon, nutmeg, cloves and allspice.
Mix together with nuts and raisins.
Bake in tube pan at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: cherry supreme cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Pour pineapple (with juice) into pan; spread evenly.
Pour cherries into pan; spread evenly.
Pour cake mix into pan and spread evenly.
Place pecans into pan and spread.
Slice butter into pat-size pieces and place on top of other ingredients.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes.
Enjoy!

title: mexican wedding cake
directions: Beat eggs until light.
Add dry ingredients and beat.
Add nuts, pineapple and vanilla and beat.
Bake in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch greased pan at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: big plain apple cake
directions: Mix sugar and eggs until good and creamy; add oil and vanilla. Mix well and add flour, salt, soda and cinnamon (sift all this together and then add to creamy mix).
Add nuts and raisins.
Stir raisins in dry flour until will not stick together as bad before putting in mix.
Add apples to batter.
Put into large bread pan or Bundt pan.	Even out batter; cook 1 hour at 350°.
Cake will rise pretty high.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: homemade yeast rolls
directions: Mix water, yeast and sugar together, then add oil and eggs. Then add the flour. Mix well. Set in refrigerator overnight. Roll out and cut like biscuits. Bake at 400° until done.

title: fudge
directions: Melt oleo and cheese together.
Pour into sugar, cocoa and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add nuts if you want.
Mix well. Pour into 8 x 8-inch ungreased pan.
Chill for 15 minutes.
Cut in squares and serve.

title: white bread
directions: Scald milk.
Add sugar, salt and Crisco.
Stir.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add yeast to lukewarm water; stir until dissolved.
Mix all together and gradually add flour until it's stiff enough to knead.
Knead until smooth and elastic.
Place in large greased bowl, turning to coat dough.
Let rise 1 hour in warm place.

title: au gratin potatoes and peas
directions: Slice potatoes as to fry and place into oblong pan or glass baking dish.
Spread peas over potatoes.
Pour milk over peas. Sprinkle cheese over top.
Cover and bake until potatoes are soft and tender.
If sauce dries up before potatoes are done add 1 cup of milk.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
In large bowl, combine bananas, eggs, milk, baking soda and salt.
Mix well.
Add creamed sugar to banana mixture.
Blend well.
Add flour; add finely chopped nuts, if desired.
Pour in greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Makes 1 large loaf.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix together in 2-quart casserole with only half of onions. Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Cover casserole with remaining onions when done.
Simple and good.

title: baked "crispy chicken"
directions: Crush Waverly crackers to make dish of crumbs.
Add milk to beaten egg.
Dip chicken in egg mixture and roll in crumbs.
Dip again in mixture and roll a second time in crumb mixture.
Place chicken in
glass oven pan.
Pour melted butter over chicken and sprinkle with pepper.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake 2 hours at 325°.

title: class recipie
directions: Combine brils and boys.
Season lightly with the knowledge. Simmer for 7 1/2 hours.
Next throw in the teacher with A's and A+'s.
Cook for 30 minutes.
Put on desk platter.
And now you have a Class Delight.
Eat after 180 days.

title: rumford salad sticks
directions: Pour boiling water over the cornmeal, salt and shortening; stirring to make sure cornmeal is all moistened.
Cover and set aside to cool.
Sift and add flour and baking powder.
Knead slightly, onto a floured board, divide into portions the size of walnut and roll with the hand into sticks a little thicker than a pencil.
Lay side by side on well-greased baking sheet and bake ten to fifteen minutes in hot oven.

title: apple cheese crumble
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Butter an 8-inch glass baking dish.
Mix apples, lemon juice and 1/3 cup sugar lightly and spread in baking dish. Sift flour, 3/4 cup sugar, salt and cinnamon together in bowl.
Add butter and blend first with fork, then with fingers to make crumbly mixture.
Mix in cheese and sprinkle over apples. Bake about 40 minutes until apples are tender.
Serve warm with cream.

title: buttercream frosting
directions: Combine all ingredients in mixing bowl.
Beat until smooth and creamy.
(If too stiff to spread easily, add a few drops more milk).
Makes about 2 cups of frosting.
Frosts tops and sides of two 8 or 9-inch layers.

title: eggplant*
directions: Peel eggplant in thin slices.
Dip in egg, then in cracker crumbs.
Fry in hot fat until golden brown.

title: fruity smoothie
directions: Prepare soft drink mix. Place soft drink, yogurt, strawberries and banana in blender container. Blend until smooth. Makes 5 servings.

title: sausage surprise pie
directions: Set aside after mixing by hand. Brown 1 1/2
pound hamburger in skillet along with a large chopped onion, drain salt and pepper to taste.
Grate 1/2-1 pound, cheddar cheese.
Chop 4 or 5 jalapeno peppers (or green chilies). Grease heavy skillet and sprinkle with corn meal and let brown in oven.
Put half of corn mixture, then layer half cheese, meat and onions, pepper, remaining cheese and rest of corn mixture.
Cover bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour.

title: sunday dinner roast(crock-pot)
directions: Peel potatoes and carrots and cut in chunks.
Place in crock-pot.
Season meat well with seasoned salt, garlic powder, salt and pepper.
Place roast on top of potatoes and carrots. Pour 1 can consomme soup over top and cook on low all night until Sunday dinner.
Remove roast, potatoes and carrots.
Pour liquid in skillet and bring to boil.
Thicken with 2 tablespoons cornstarch, dissolved in small amount of water.
Serve gravy with roast and vegetables.

title: low country shrimp & grits
directions: Bring water to a boil. Add salt and pepper. Add grits and cook 20-25 minutes. Remove from heat; add butter and cheese. Fry bacon until browned; drain well. In bacon grease, add shrimp and cook until pink. Add lemon juice, chopped bacon, parsley and garlic. Saute for 3 minutes. Spoon grits into a serving bowl. Add shrimp mixture.

title: basil tomato salad
directions: In small bowl whisk together oil, vinegar, basil, salt and pepper.
Add rice, tomatoes, cucumbers and onion.
Toss.
Serve chilled.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together except cheese.
Pour half into hot greased pan.
Add cheese and pour remaining bread mixture over cheese.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: tutt's toffee
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (I reduce my heat to 325`).
Line a cookie sheet with foil.
Line 7 crackers across and 5 crackers down.
Melt butter and 1 cup of brown sugar in the microwave for 4 minutes. Remove, stir a little, and pour over crackers.
(The brown sugar will not pour evenly; not to worry.
When you bake it, it will spread.)
Bake for 20 minutes.

title: peanut butter ball
directions: Melt margarine; add confectioners sugar and mix well (medium heat).
Add crumbs and vanilla; mix well.
Add peanut butter; mix well and form small balls.
Melt wax and chocolate in double boiler until smooth.
Dip each ball into chocolate; place on plate sprayed with Pam or use wax paper.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Beat together shortening, sugar and eggs.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix to creamed mixture.
Chill dough 1 hour.
Make into 18 marble size balls.
Dip one side in a mixture of 2 tablespoons cinnamon and 2 tablespoons sugar.
Bake at 300°.

title: sweet and sour cabbage
directions: Heat water, vinegar, lemon juice and salt in a 3-quart saucepan until boiling. Add cabbage and return to boil. Reduce heat. Cover and simmer for 10 minutes until tender. While cabbage is cooking, saute onion in margarine. Add to cabbage. Add preserves and mix well.

title: diabetic sugarless pie
directions: Thaw apple juice and combine with flour and cinnamon; mix well.
Pour into a saucepan and cook over medium heat until mixture boils and thickens.
Remove from heat. Add apples to hot mixture and stir to coat. Spoon into pie shell.
Cover apples with second pie shell and prick well.
Bake in a preheated oven until done, approximately 35 to 45 minutes.

title: sausage spinach loaf
directions: In
a medium skillet, cook sausage until no longer pink; drain.
On lightly floured surface, roll bread dough into a 15
x 18-inch rectangle. Sprinkle cheese over dough, leaving 1-inch around edges. Top with sausage, spinach, onions and mushrooms. Roll to meet long edges.
Place loaf, seam side down, on greased baking sheet. Brush loaf with egg white combined with water and caraway seed. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until golden brown.
Let stand 8 to 10 minutes before cutting.

title: animal cookies
directions: Grind 1 cup oatmeal in blender until fine.
Add 4 tablespoons honey, salt, flour and soda.
Cut in butter.
Add milk and vanilla.
Roll very thin.
Cut out with animal cookie cutters. Top each cookie with cinnamon-sugar.
Bake at 400° until lightly browned (approximately 10 minutes).
Serves 8.

title: garlic string beans
directions: In large heavy saucepan, heat oil, garlic and beans.
Saute over high heat to sear beans, stirring frequently so they do not burn.
Add thyme, sea salt and pepper to taste.
Add water to bouillon.
Bring to boil; cover tightly.
Reduce heat to medium and simmer for 20 to 30 minutes or until tender.
Add more water when necessary.
Add squeeze of lemon juice and toss well.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Add cold water.
Mix well.
Add pineapple, pie filling and pecans.
Mix well.
Congeal.
Blend cream cheese, sour cream, sugar and vanilla well.
Spread over congealed salad.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight before serving.

title: chocolate peanut clusters
directions: Melt almond bark in microwave (stir every 1 minute until melted), approximately 3 minutes. Stir in chocolate morsels until melted (do not put back in the microwave). Stir in peanuts. Drop by tablespoon onto long sheets of wax paper. As candy begins to harden (after about 15 minutes), gently move wax paper backward and forward a couple of times, so the moisture will not allow the paper to stick to the countertop. Candy is ready when it can be removed from wax paper and it is not sticky on the bottom.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Mix Jell-O and hot water, then add cold water.
Stir in blueberry pie filling, pineapple and nuts. Refrigerate until firm.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease two 14-inch aluminum pizza pans. Combine dry ingredients; set aside.
Mix margarine and brown sugar; beat until fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat until creamy and fluffy.
Add dry ingredients; mix well.
Stir in chips and nuts.
Divide batter between 2 pans.
Spread and bake for 15 to 20 minutes.
Decorate with chocolate frosting, if desired.

title: orange julius
directions: Blend until like an icee.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Put into baked pie crust.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Combine green onions, green pepper, celery, garlic, and butter in 2 quart microproof casserole. Cover and place in oven. Cook on high 3 minutes. Pause, add remaining ingredients except shrimp; blend well. Cover. Cook on medium-high, (80%) for 5 minutes. Pause; add shrimp, blend well. Cover. Cook on medium-high (80%) for 3 minutes. Pause and stir. Cover. Cook on medium-high (80%), 4 minutes. Stir before serving over hot rice. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: creamy fruit dip
directions: In a small mixing bowl, beat the cream cheese and brown sugar until smooth. Beat in the sour cream, extracts and cinnamon until smooth. Add milk and mix well. Add pudding mix; beat on low speed for 2 minutes. Cover and refrigerate for at least 1 hour. Serve with the chilled fruit.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Boil eggs.
Half the eggs, separating the yolks from the whites.
To yolks, add mustard and sugar; mix.
Add 1 or 2 serving spoons of salad dressing.
Add butter and vinegar; salt and pepper to taste.
Mix all ingredients real good and spoon back into egg whites.
Chill before serving.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Beat eggs until foamy.
Mix in flour, sugar and brown sugar; beat.
Blend in butter.
Add chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Add chili and soup to browned hamburger and onion; heat. Layer chips, meat mixture and top with cheese.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: steak casserole
directions: Brown steak in butter. Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: sausage balls
directions: For easier mixing, heat sausage in microwave for 3 to 5 minutes, until warm.
Blend ingredients in bowl.
Shape into balls 1-inch in diameter.
Bake in oven at 350° for 15 minutes.
Makes 40 to 50 balls, depending on size.

title: tomato and cream sauce
directions: Put all the ingredients except the heavy cream in a saucepan and cook at the merest simmer for 1 hour, uncovered.
Stir from time to time with wooden spoon.
Puree the contents through a food mill.
Add heavy cream; stir-cook for 1 minute more.
Good on veal and spaghetti.
Can be frozen.
Do not boil when reheating.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pink fluff salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water. Cool until it begins to congeal. Whip or stir softened cream cheese and add pineapple. Whip the cream until stiff and stir in nuts. Fold all together and pour into mold. Serves 8.

title: cherry dump cake
directions: Layer ingredients in greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan in the order listed above.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: mexicali rice
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet.
Drain.
Add broth, tomato sauce, and chili seasoning mix.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Stir in rice and green pepper; cover and remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Fluff with fork.
Garnish with lettuce, tomato, sour cream, and cheese.

title: kuzu shiitake salad
directions: Slice
cucumber in half; cut into thin slices.	Squeeze liquid from
cucumber.
Add
shoyu, vinegar, sugar, ajinomoto and
oils. Boil
kuzu shiitake until tender; rinse and drain. Add
to cucumber
mixture.	Add
remaining	ingredients
just before serving.
Sprinkle with sliced scrambled eggs, kamaboko and onion.

title: wilma's peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine in a bowl and set aside the peanut butter, marshmallow cream and vanilla. Grease a 9x9 pan. In a heavy saucepan mix sugar, milk and butter. Bring to a rolling boil and boil for 5 minutes. Remove from heat and quickly beat in
the reserved peanut butter mixture. Pour into greased 9x9 pan and cool at room temperature.

title: orange pineapple punch
directions: In punch bowl, combine orange sherbet, ice milk and can of pineapple.
Add half and half, ginger ale and club soda; mix well. (Have all ingredients cold.)
Serve.
This is great with salty nuts.
A wonderful punch for weddings.

title: texas fudge
directions: Grease a square pan.
Put jalapeno peppers on the bottom of the pan.
Put grated cheese over the peppers.
Pour the beaten eggs over cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cookie sheet cake
directions: Bring to a boil the margarine, shortening, water and cocoa. Add the flour, sugar, salt and soda.
Mix together the eggs, vanilla and buttermilk and add to other mixture.
Pour into cookie sheet.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Frost when removed immediately from oven.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix the ingredients, alternately adding 1 large can of evaporated milk and 1 (2 ounce) jar poppy seed.
Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes in an ungreased pan (Bundt or loaf) in 325° oven.

title: baked apple dumplings
directions: Cut shortening into flour, then add salt.
Add cold water; mix. Add more water if needed.
Divide pastry into 2 balls.
Roll pastry about 1/8-inch thick.
Cut into squares.
Place a cored, pared apple in center of each square.
Fill each apple with 1 teaspoon sugar and 1 teaspoon lemon juice.
Top the apple with a piece of butter and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Pinch edge of dough together on top.
Place in well-greased pan, a few inches apart.
Bake in a 450° oven for 10 minutes.

title: puppy chow
directions: Pour cereal in large bowl and set aside.
Combine chocolate chips, peanut butter and margarine together.
Melt over low heat on top of stove.
Or can use microwave, 1 to 2 minutes or until smooth.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour chocolate mixture over cereal, stirring until pieces of cereal are evenly coated.
Then pour cereal mixture in large resealable plastic bag with powdered sugar.
Seal the bag and shake until all pieces are well coated. Spread on waxed paper to cool.
Store in airtight container. Makes 9 cups.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Cut the chicken in half.
Mix rest of ingredients and marinate the chicken overnight.
Remove the chicken pieces one at a time from the marinade, taking care to reserve as much marinade as possible.
Roll the chicken pieces in the cornflake crumbs. Arrange in a shallow baking dish and dribble with 1 cup melted butter or margarine.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: broccoli souffle
directions: Grease casserole.
Squeeze water out of frozen, thawed broccoli.
Saute onion in butter; add flour, water and Cheez Whiz until mixture is thick.
Place broccoli in shallow baking dish. Pour over cheese mixture.
Beat eggs and pour over broccoli and cheese mixture.
Cover with cracker crumbs.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: astonishment
directions: Crush 1 generous cup of peaches in saucepan, extracting as much juice as possible.
Stir in cornstarch, lemon juice and sugar; simmer briefly over medium heat until clear gelatinous mixture is formed.
Let cool.
Spread into pan crust base and press, then press rest of peaches into it.
Dust with confectioners sugar and refrigerate.

title: old fashioned potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes in salted water until fork-tender.
Cut potatoes into cubes.
Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Cover; refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Garnish with additional boiled egg, if desired.
Yields 6 servings.

title: bacon and cauliflower salad
directions: Cover bowl with Saran Wrap.
Set overnight or 24 hours.
Stir together and serve.

title: milk potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes and cut in small cubes.
Place in a saucepan and cover with water.
Bring to boil and turn down heat to low. Simmer for 15 to 20 minutes, until potatoes are tender.
Add salt, margarine and milk and heat to bubbling (do not boil).

title: spam brunch pie
directions: In a large frying pan, heat oil on medium heat.
Add potatoes and cook until brown on one side.
Turn over.
Layer Spam, onion and chilies.
Pour eggs over all and cook until set.
Sprinkle with cheese and cook until cheese melts.
Slide onto tray.
Slice and serve.

title: cheese scalloped potatoes and ham
directions: Cook onion in large saucepan until tender.
Blend in flour, mustard, salt and pepper; gradually stir in milk.
Cook and stir over medium heat until sauce thickens.
Add cheese.
Arrange potatoes in greased 8 x 12 x 2-inch baking dish.
Top with ham. Pour sauce over all.
Cover with foil; bake at 350° for 44 minutes.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes longer.
Serves 4.

title: macaroni casserole
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions; drain.
Combine with next 4 ingredients.
Blend mushroom soup, milk and 1/2 cup cheese; stir into macaroni.
Place in casserole dish; top with remaining cheese.
Bake uncovered at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: stuffed breast of veal
directions: Have pocket cut in breast of veal.
Wipe meat with damp cloth. Combine Season-All and 1 teaspoon salt.
Lightly rub inside of meat with half of this mixture.
Toss together remaining 1/2 teaspoon salt, bread cubes, 1 cup water and seasonings.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix well and chill overnight.

title: crawfish fettucini
directions: Saute Chef's Blend until soft.
Add boiled and peeled crawfish tails.
Cook for 15 minutes on low heat.
Add Velveeta and milk. Cook for 15 minutes on low heat.
Boil noodles until tender; drain and rinse with cold tap water.
Stir in noodles to sauce.
Pour into casserole dishes.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.
Heat in oven 15 minutes at 350°.
Makes 3 (13 x 9-inch) casserole dishes.

title: pineapple zucchini cake
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, salt, vanilla, zucchini and soda.
Add flour and baking powder and oil and pineapple alternately to the mixture.
Add raisins and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in a 9 x 12-inch pan.

title: hot fudge topping
directions: Cook chocolate, water, sugar and white Karo to soft ball stage.
Remove from heat and add Eagle Brand and vanilla.
Keep in refrigerator.
Reheat only what you need each time.

title: zucchini 'n' carrot coins
directions: In a large skillet, saute carrots in butter for 4-5 minutes. Add the onion: cook for 1 minute.
Stir in the remaining ingredients.
Cover and cook for 4-5 minutes or until vegetables are crisp-tender. Yields: 4 servings.

title: aloha chicken salad
directions: Mix and serve on lettuce leaves.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: In a bowl, cream butter with peanut butter.
Add sugars and beat until fluffy.
Add eggs and beat.
Mix in flour and baking soda.
Drop by rounded tablespoonful onto greased baking sheet. Flatten slightly with palm of hand.
Bake at 350° until light golden brown, about 15 minutes.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Separate cauliflower and layer into a large container.
Next shred lettuce and spread on top of cauliflower, then chop onion and put on top of lettuce.
Sprinkle 1 cup of Parmesan cheese over all layers and top with mayonnaise.
Do not mix!
Cover and put in refrigerator overnight, then mix the next day before serving.

title: asparagus with mushrooms and cilantro
directions: Cut asparagus on a diagonal into 1-inch pieces. Lightly coat the bottom of a nonstick pan with vegetable spray. Preheat the pan over medium-high heat for 30 seconds. Add the mushrooms and cook, tossing and shaking until they are lightly browned. Add asparagus and shallots and continue tossing for about 1 minute. Season with salt, pepper and cilantro. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: baked eggplant casserole
directions: Peel eggplant and soak in salted water for several hours in refrigerator.
Soak bread crumbs in milk.
Saute vegetables in butter. Boil eggplant until nearly tender and then drain well. Mix eggplant, crumbs, veggies and seasoning.
Place in greased casserole dish. Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° 1 hour or until golden brown.

title: hickory nut cake
directions: Cream together sugar and butter.
Add eggs and beat on medium speed for 2 minutes.
Mix dry ingredients together lightly with fork.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Mix well.
Stir in vanilla and nuts, saving some nuts for top of cake.
Pour mixture into greased and floured cake pans.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Let cool.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Place popcorn in a lightly greased 4-quart casserole dish; set aside.
Place butter in a 1 1/2-quart dish, microwave on High for one minute or until melted.
Stir in sugar, syrup and salt; cover and microwave at High for 4 minutes.
