Remove from microwave oven; stir in soda and vanilla.
Pour over popcorn; mix until well coated and no sugar mixture remains in bottom of dish.
Microwave popcorn mixture on High for 2 1/2 to 3 minutes.
Remove.
Spread in a lightly buttered cookie sheet.
Cool.
Break in pieces; store in airtight container.

title: apple pandowdy
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix sugars, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt in large bowl.
Stir in apples.
Put into ungreased 2-quart casserole.
Dot with oleo.
Cover apples with pastry, placing inside of dish.
Bake 30 minutes.
Cut crust into small pieces into apple filling.
Bake longer until apples are tender and pieces of crust are golden.
Serve warm.

title: kidney bean sauce
directions: Wash and soak beans overnight.
In a medium size pot, add 4 cups water, oil, onion, garlic and salt.
Mix in a bowl the tomato paste, tomato sauce and 1/2 cup water until smooth.
Add to other ingredients that are in pot and cook under flame, about 1 1/2 hours, until beans are tender.
Cut up green pepper and thyme.
Let simmer in the pot.
Add a pinch of sugar, if desired.
When done, serve over rice.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown ground beef; drain. Add tomatoes, corn, Ro-Tel with chilies, pinto beans, kidney beans, taco seasoning, Ranch dressing mix and 1 onion, chopped fine. Mix well. Simmer 30 to 40 minutes.

title: orange pancakes
directions: Spray griddle with vegetable oil.
Mix dry ingredients.
Beat eggs and oil; add to dry ingredients.
Gradually add orange juice. Cook until pancake forms bubbles on top side.
Turn over and brown other side.
Serve with slice of orange or other fruit and enjoy.

title: coconut cream cake
directions: Combine cake mix, 1 cup coconut, water and egg whites and beat 2 minutes at high speed of electric mixer.
Reduce speed to low; beat 1 minute.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool cake in pan for 10 minutes.
Punch holes in top of cake with a toothpick. Pour cream of coconut over cake while still warm.
Spread whipped topping over cake; sprinkle with remaining coconut.
Cover and chill at least 4 hours.
Cut cake into squares to serve.
Yield: 15 to 18 servings.

title: halloween grease paint
directions: Mix all together.
Easy to take off.
Kids love this on their faces for Halloween.
To make the color brown, add 2 1/2 teaspoons cocoa.
Refrigerate.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli.
Mix with other ingredients.
Place in buttered casserole with noodles on top with chopped chicken (fine) on noodles.
Cover with butter.
Bake at 350° until very hot. If casserole for more than 8 add 1 package broccoli, 2 breasts, 1/2 cup rice and 1/2 can soup.

title: fancy potatoes
directions: Melt 1/2 stick of butter and saute onion in it.
Mix with all other ingredients except corn flakes.
Spray pan with Pam.
Pour ingredients into a large baking pan and spread corn flakes on top. Drizzle with last 1/2 stick of melted butter.
Cook in oven for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: easy fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well, adding dry Jell-O last (other fruit and different flavors of Jell-O may be used).
Keeps well for several days in refrigerator.

title: spinach dip in french bread bowl
directions: Cook spinach; cool and drain.
Mix with all other ingredients. Cut off top of French bread and hollow out the inside to use as a bowl.
Cut the top and bread removed from the inside into pieces that are the right size for dipping.
Stuff the hollow bread bowl with dip.

title: apple cinnamon muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Lightly spray 12 medium muffin cups with no stick cooking spray or line with paper baking cups.
Combine flour, wheat germ, 1/4 cup sugar, baking powder, 1 teaspoon cinnamon and salt.
Add combined milk, oil, egg whites and apples. Mix just until moistened.
Fill muffin cups almost full.
Combine remaining 1 tablespoon sugar and 1/4 teaspoon cinnamon.
Sprinkle over muffins.
Bake 18 to 20 minutes or until brown.

title: old south cucumber lime pickles
directions: Soak cucumbers in water and lime mixture in crockery or enamel ware for 12 hours or overnight.
Do not use aluminum ware.
Remove sliced cucumbers from lime water.
Discard lime water.
Rinse three times in fresh cold water.
Soak 3 hours in fresh ice water. Combine vinegar, sugar, salt and mixed pickling spices in a large pot.
Bring to a low boil, stirring until sugar dissolves.
Remove syrup from heat.
Add sliced cucumbers.
Soak 5 to 6 hours or overnight.
Boil slices 35 minutes.
Fill sterilized jars, leaving 1/2-inch headspace.
Cap each jar.
Process pints 10 minutes, quarts 15 minutes in a boiling water bath.
If pickles, jars and tops are boiling hot, they will seal without processing.

title: barbecue sandwiches
directions: Mix all ingredients and cook until thick.

title: iced tea and lemon
directions: Place tea bag in boiling water and let remain for 6 minutes. Add 1/2 cup sugar and stir.
Add juice and rind of 1 lemon. Remove rind after 7 or 8 minutes.
Pour over ice cubes in tall glasses and garnish with mint.

title: old fashioned rice pudding
directions: Scald milk in heavy saucepan with rice.
Beat eggs slightly in buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Stir in sugar and salt.
Add hot milk mixture slowly to eggs, stirring.
Stir in raisins and vanilla and sprinkle on nutmeg.
Place in pan of hot water and bake in slow oven at 325° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until knife inserted in middle comes out clean.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: white frosting
directions: Stir first 3 ingredients until blended.
Boil rapidly until mixture spins 6 to 8-inch thread.
Beat egg whites until stiff and pour hot syrup over egg whites in thin stream, beating constantly. Add vanilla.

title: chicken breast bake
directions: Mix and heat over low flame soups, sour cream and cheese.
Mix well.
Place chicken in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Pour mixture over.
Cover.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Uncover and bake 1/2 hour at 350°.
Serve over cooked white rice.

title: orange squares
directions: Blend gelatin and boiling water.
Set in refrigerator until thickened.
Beat chilled milk until it holds shape and add sugar and orange juice.
Continue blending until mixed well.
Add thickened gelatin mixture and beat until mixture will not rise further.
Pour into 9 x 14 x 2-inch cake pan (or Bundt pan lined with nuts) lined with graham cracker crumbs.
Keep refrigerated. Makes 12 servings.

title: pecan cheddar log
directions: In skillet, melt butter and add pecans.
Saute over low heat until lightly browned.
Cool and chop fine.
Stir in salt and parsley.
Set aside.

title: baked beans with sausage
directions: In large skillet, brown the sausage and onion; drain.
Spread pork and beans, brown sugar, barbecue sauce and cooked sausage-onion mixture in a 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: quick and moist bread(1-6-86)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, combine flour and sugar.
Add sour cream and beer alternately; mix well.
Pour batter into greased 2-quart round baking dish.
Bake 45 minutes; brush top with butter.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes longer or until cake tester inserted completely into center comes out clean.
Cool slightly.
Serve warm, cool or toasted.
Ooh it's so good!!!

title: almond joys
directions: Cream the butter; add the sugar and mix well.
Add the egg, nuts and flour; add the vanilla.
Chill dough.
Cut off small bits of dough and roll into finger thick pieces, about 1 1/2 inches long.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for about 8 minutes at 375°. Remove the cookies and roll in a mixture of 1/4 cup sugar and 1/2 teaspoon of cinnamon.

title: senate bean soup
directions: Put all ingredients in heavy soup pot.
Cook slowly until beans are tender.

title: bread crab salad
directions: Cut crusts off bread.
Spread with melted butter.
Cut each slice into small cubes.
Add onion, celery and eggs.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Melt oleo and add onion; saute.
Add broccoli; stir thoroughly, adding mushroom soup.
Simmer 1 minute.
Add cooked rice and Cheez Whiz.
Put in buttered casserole dish.
Bake at 350°
for 20 to 30 minutes or you can prepare in a microwave.

title: fruit dip
directions: Whip all ingredients.
Chill until ready to serve with fresh fruit.

title: easy sweet potato cake
directions: Mash the sweet potatoes.
Combine the cake mix with the eggs. Add potatoes, nuts, raisins and cinnamon.
Pour into a greased baking pan.
Bake until a toothpick inserted comes out clean.
Let cool; then add the icing.

title: easy egg custard(makes its own crust)
directions: Mix together and place in 9-inch pie plate.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: hungarian cabbage and noodles
directions: In skillet, heat oil.
Saute cabbage until wilted and tender. Mix and stir in cooked noodles.
Add sugar and other spices.
Top with poppy seed and serve as side dish with pork chops, pork roast and sausages.

title: scalloped carrots
directions: Cook carrots in salted water until tender; drain.
Cook onion in 3 tablespoons butter until soft.
Stir soup, salt, pepper and cheese.
Add carrots and put in a 2-quart dish.
Toss bread stuffing with 1/3 cup melted butter.
Spoon over carrot mixture. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: corn salad
directions: In small saucepan, combine sugar, vinegar and oil. Season to taste with salt and pepper. Add celery seeds. Heat until hot, but not boiling. Cool.

title: mud pie
directions: Mash bag of Oreo cookies up.
Put 1/2 in bottom of large bowl.
Set 1/2 aside.
Mix Cool Whip, cream cheese, powdered sugar and butter.
Add more powdered sugar if needed until smooth.

title: best ever chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix next 5 ingredients.
Mix all mixtures together.
Add chocolate chips, Hershey bar and nuts.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet.
Make golf-ball size cookies 2 inches apart.
Bake at 375° for 6 minutes.
Yields 8 to 10 dozen.
tags: make powder by using food processor

title: mango bread
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add lemon juice.
Fold in flour.
Fold in mango and nuts.
Grease and flour loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Cool before slicing.
Oh!
So good!

title: broccoli tomato salad
directions: Place broccoli and
water in a 2 qt microwave safe bowl. Cover and microwave on high for 2-3 minutes, or until crisp/tender.
Stir once.
Drain.
Let cool completely.
Place broccoli in a serving bowl.
Gently stir in tomato and onion.
In a small bowl combine the mayo, sour cream, lemon juice, salt and pepper. Pour over veggies and stir gently.
Cover and refrigerate for 1 hour.
Serves 6.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Combine corn, milk, salt and pepper; place in greased casserole.
Melt butter and add bread cubes.
Blend but do not brown.
Sprinkle cubes over corn mixture and bake for 30 minutes in 350° oven.
Serve at once.

title: pea pods with onion
directions: Place pea pods and water in microwave safe bowl, cover and cook on high for 3-5 minutes (until crisp-tender). Meanwhile in a small skillet cook onion in 2 Tbsp. butter, heat until crisp-tender. Drain peas and add to onion mixture. Add salt and pepper and remaining butter, toss to coat. Cook and stir until heated through.

title: green tomato jam
directions: Boil tomatoes and sugar 15 minutes.
Add jello.
Red flavor works best (raspberry).
Cool and can.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix together flour, butter and pecans and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan; bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.

title: quick and easy cabbage rolls
directions: Brown turkey, onion and celery in cooking spray.
Add remaining ingredients, except cabbage.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Spray casserole dish with cooking spray and place shredded cabbage in dish.
Top with meat mixture.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour. Serves 4. Each serving contains 158 calories, 18.9 g protein, 8.7 g fat, 60 mg chol. and 106.5 mg sodium.

title: clam chowder
directions: Make a roux of the flour and margarine, cooking for approximately 5 minutes.
(Make a roux by melting margarine.
Add the flour and cook on high flame, stirring with rubber spatula. Make sure to scrape the flour off the bottom constantly to stop from burning.)
Add water, clams with juice, onions, celery and carrots.
Cook for 40 minutes at a slow simmer.
During the last 15 minutes, add all the spices.
Continue to simmer.
Bring to a boil. Add cream, the last ingredient.
Bring to a boil again, then immediately turn off the heat.
Serve to a large crowd.

title: lean beef 'n' vegetables
directions: In a 12-inch skillet, cook ground beef until well-browned. Using slotted spoon, remove beef to bowl and set aside.
Add oil to drippings in skillet.
Heat over medium heat.
Add cabbage and onion.
Cook for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally, until vegetables are softened.
Add mushrooms, red bell peppers, sage and black pepper.
Cook for 5 minutes longer, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat.
Stir in Swiss cheese, reserved beef and salt.

title: beef and potato casserole
directions: Brown ground beef in a skillet with onion and green pepper. Add salt and pepper to taste.
Drain.
Place in a casserole dish. Pour tomato sauce over beef mixture and cover with mashed potatoes.
Cut butter into small pieces and place on potatoes. Sprinkle with paprika and brown in oven at 350°.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Combine confectioners sugar, peanut butter and a little milk. Mix; make into small balls.
Melt paraffin wax and chocolate chips in double boiler, stirring constantly.
Dip
balls in chocolate mixture (use toothpick to hold balls).
Put on wax paper to cool. Delicious!

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Grease 13 x 9-inch baking dish, layer meat, cheese and bread. Drizzle melted butter over top.
Combine flour and dry mustard; sprinkle over ham and cheese bread mixture.
Beat eggs; add milk and pour over mixture in pan.
Cover and put in the refrigerator for at least 4 hours or up to 24 hours.
Bake for about 1 hour or until puffy in 350° oven.

title: chow mein
directions: Melt butter in skillet or wok.
Add meat, celery, onion, pepper and chicken broth.
Cover and cook until tender.
Add can Chinese vegetables and mushrooms.
Mix cornstarch and soy sauce together.
Add to rest of the ingredients.
Serve on Chinese noodles or rice.
Yum, Yum.

title: winter salad
directions: Shred
lettuce;
add rest of ingredients, except dressing. Toss
well.
Add
dressing	of
choice.
One small can of mandarin oranges may be used instead of orange.

title: pea salad
directions: Heat peas 10 minutes.
Cool.
Cut up eggs.
Add eggs, pickles, celery, onions, and Velveeta to peas.
Stir in enough Miracle Whip to cover all.
Chill.

title: barbecue brisket
directions: Rub salt all over meat.
Place on heavy foil.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over brisket.
Wrap airtight in foil. Cook on medium coals on grill for about 2 hours.
Turn once.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Boil and debone chicken and cut in chunks. Cut cheese in chunks.
Place chicken in a 13 x 9-inch casserole dish and top with chopped onion, salt and pepper.
Add cheese chunks and top with half the bag of taco chips.
Mix soups and tomatoes in a bowl and pour over chicken. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, then sprinkle remainder of chips on top. Bake an additional 5 to 10 minutes.

title: white salad
directions: Beat milk and lemon juice. Add Cool Whip and beat. Add pineapple, marshmallows and bananas. Refrigerate.

title: creamy strawberry dessert
directions: Crust: Melt 1/2 cup butter and combine with crushed vanilla wafers. Press into 9 x 12-inch pan. Refrigerate while making filling.

title: date balls
directions: Cook over low heat the margarine, sugar and dates until sugar melts and mixture is thick.
Remove and let cool.
Add Rice Krispies, pecans and vanilla.
Shape into balls.
Roll in confectioners sugar.
Yields 20 small balls.

title: fruit cake
directions: Crush vanilla wafers.
Mix all ingredients together well. Pack into a tube pan.
Freeze for 24 hours.

title: meat loaf-a-la-sheila
directions: Combine all ingredients until it takes form and is holding together.
Divide into 3 loaf pans.
Cover the top of the meat loaf with catsup.
Bake in 350° oven in a pan with water in bottom, about 1 cup.
Cover with Reynold's Wrap for the first hour and cook 30 minutes, uncovered, to allow it to brown.

title: irene salad
directions: Mix and jell lightly the first 4 ingredients.
Take out of refrigerator and add remaining ingredients. Chill.

title: ham balls
directions: Mix together all ingredients and roll into balls.
Makes 15 ham balls.

title: dirt cake
directions: Cream confectioners sugar, cream cheese and butter.
In separate bowl, combine milk and pudding, then add Cool Whip, cream cheese mixture and pudding together.
Set aside.
Crush Oreos into a fine crumb mixture.
Layer crushed Oreos and creamed mixture, ending with Oreos.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Coat baking sheets with nonstick cooking spray.
In medium bowl, with wire whisk, combine cake flour, baking soda and salt; set aside.
In large bowl, with an electric mixer on medium speed, beat together prune puree, butter, sugar, brown sugar, egg, egg whites and vanilla for 2 minutes or until creamy.
With mixer on low speed, beat in dry ingredients until incorporated.
By hand, stir in chocolate chips.

title: swiss steak
directions: Salt, pepper and flour steak. (Have it tenderized at the butcher shop); cut steak into pieces and brown on both sides. Place in roaster pan. Mix onions, oregano, sweet pepper and tomatoes together and pour over the steak. Cover and place in 375° oven for 2 hours.

title: super spinach squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put butter in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking pan; melt in oven.
Remove.
Beat eggs well in large bowl.
Add flour, milk, salt and baking powder; mix well.
Add cheese, spinach and onion; mix well.
Spoon into baking pan; level off. Sprinkle with seasoned salt.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Remove and let cool 45 minutes, then cut into bite size squares (3/4 to 1-inch each).
Makes about 40 squares.

title: baked egg custard
directions: Scald milk and cool slightly. Combine beaten eggs and sugar. Stir in vanilla.
Pour in baking dish and bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until knife inserted comes out clean.

title: sweet and sour salad
directions: Mix well and chill overnight before serving.

title: boston cream candy
directions: Cook sugar, milk, and syrup until it forms a soft ball in cold water.
Then add vanilla and oleo.
Beat a few minutes, and pour into a buttered pan.
Nuts may be added before you beat, if desired.

title: spaghetti sauce and meatballs
directions: Put paste in pan with oil and garlic.
Stir until it beads up; add tomatoes.
Add 2 tomato paste cans of water.
Add salt, black pepper, sweet basil and mint leaves.
Add small, diced onion and sugar.
Cook slowly for approximately 2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Remove the garlic after cooked.

title: mama's icebox cookies
directions: Mix
as
given (butter or shortening, brown sugar, egg, flour, cream
of tartar, soda, salt, nuts and vanilla).
Make into 2 small
rolls.
Wrap
in
waxed paper.
Place in icebox (can be frozen for later).	Slice and bake when needed.
Bake at 350° about 12 minutes.

title: savory venison stew
directions: Brown venison and garlic in oil.
Pour off drippings.
Stir in water, wine, tomato paste, brown sugar, cumin, salt, cinnamon sticks and bay leaves.
Cover tightly and cook slowly for 1 1/2 hours.
Add onions; continue cooking, covered, for 25 minutes. Stir in raisins and cook 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and discard cinnamon sticks and bay leaves.
Serve over noodles or orzo. Makes 8 servings.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Mix pineapple, milk, juice and nuts.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Refrigerate before serving.

title: hot beef dip
directions: Saute onions in margarine.
Add milk and cream cheese.
Stir over low heat until cheese is melted.
Add rest of the ingredients and heat thoroughly, stirring now and then.
Serve with Bugles or sliced French bread.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw and drain spinach.
Mix Ranch dressing with sour cream and mayonnaise.
Stir in rest of ingredients, then add the spinach.
Chill.
Serve with raw veggies or crackers.

title: cheese toasts
directions: Mix cheese and mayonnaise; spread approximately 1/2 teaspoon on each slice of bread.
Place in one layer on broiler pan.
Broil 1 to 2 minutes until topping bubbles and edges are toasted.
Serve hot or at room temperature.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Heat oven at 350°.
Grease bottom of 9 x 13 pan.
Prepare cake mix as directed on package.
Pour into prepared pan.
After 10 minutes of baking, sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Continue baking until done.
Cool 15 minutes.
Poke top of cake every 1/2-inch with handle of wooden spoon.
Drizzle sweetened condensed milk over top of cake.
Let stand until milk has absorbed into cake.
Drizzle with caramel topping.
Cover and refrigerate about 2 hours until chilled.
Spread whipped topping over top of cake. Sprinkle with crushed Heath bars.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Melt margarine, add sugar and let cool.
Add egg and vanilla; mix.
Mix together the dry ingredients and add to sugar mixture. Pour into greased pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: quiche
directions: Bake shell at 400° for 8 minutes.
Cook meat or vegetable. Sprinkle 1/2 of the cheese on bottom of cooked pastry shell.
Beat eggs and cream together and pour over cheese.
Sprinkle top with meat or vegetable and remaining cheese.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes or until set.

title: baked stuffed flounder
directions: Saute celery, onion and garlic in melted butter over low heat. Add bread, crab, shrimp, parsley and egg; mix well.
Season with salt and pepper.
Split thick side of flounder lengthwise and crosswise; loosen meat from bone of fish to form a pocket for stuffing.
Place in pan.
Place in 350° oven for 30 to 45 minutes. Baste frequently with lemon and melted butter.

title: homemade tomato ketchup
directions: In a 6-quart, stainless-steel or enamelled pot, combine all ingredients.
Bring to a boil over high heat.
Stir until sugar dissolves.
Reduce heat to low.
Simmer 30 to 40 minutes or until mixture is thick enough to hold its shape in a spoon.
Stir often to prevent scorching.

title: apple custard pie
directions: Combine cornstarch with sugar. Beat all together. Line a 10 x 15 pan with pastry. Put a solid layer (or two) of apples over pastry and pour the cream mixture on top. Bake as you would apple pie. Sprinkle small amount of sugar on top when removed from oven. Best when eaten slightly warm or on same day made. Refrigeration will cause moisture to form on custard.

title: cheesy vegetable stir-fry
directions: In large skillet, stir-fry vegetables in margarine until crisp-tender.
Reduce heat.
Add process cheese spread, milk and marjoram.
Stir over low heat until process cheese spread is melted.
Serve over rice.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: gallets
directions: Separate eggs; beat yolks.
Add sugar, brown sugar, honey and melted butter.
Sift flour, salt and soda together.
Add to sugar mixture.
Fold in egg whites.
Bake on gallet iron or waffle iron.

title: marvelous macaroni salad
directions: Whole tomatoes may be used in place of cherry tomatoes.

title: bean dip
directions: Combine all ingredients except Cheddar cheese in crock-pot. Mix well; top with grated Cheddar cheese.
Cook on high for about 1 hour, or until cooked through.
Serve with chips.

title: small shells with mushroom and pea sauce
directions: In large saucepan, cook shells until tender.
Drain. Meanwhile, in skillet, saute mushrooms in melted butter for one minute.
Add the peas, cheese and cream.
Stir until sauce bubbles.
Combine in cooked shells and toss until coated.
Serves 4.

title: beef porcupine
directions: Combine beef Rice-A-Roni with ground beef and egg.
Shape into small meatballs (approximately 20) and brown on all sides in skillet.
Combine contents of beef seasonings packet with 2 1/2 cups hot water.
Pour over meat.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes. Thicken gravy if desired.

title: pound cake
directions: Beat margarine very hard.
Add sugar and eggs one at a time. Add flour and vanilla.
Put in Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Use toothpick to test.
Should be nice and brown on top.

title: nanny rasco's easy fruit salad(kelley jo's great grandmother)
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and refrigerate overnight.
Just before serving, add sliced bananas and stir slightly.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together (except vanilla) in heavy saucepan. Cook until thick, stirring to prevent scorching.
Take off heat and add vanilla.
Have pie shell browned ahead of time. Pour mixture into shell and make meringue.

title: baked sweet potatoes
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Place the first 3 ingredients in dish in layers.
Add enough water to pineapple juice to make 1 full cup.
Bring remaining ingredients to boil. Pour over potatoes, etc. in dish.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: 7 layer casserole
directions: Place rice and corn in layers in greased 2-quart casserole. Pour over 1 can of tomato sauce and 1/2 can water.
Add onions, green pepper, uncooked beef and seasonings.
Add second can of tomato sauce and 1/2 can of water.
Cover meat with the bacon, cut in halves.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Uncover and bake 30 minutes more or until done.

title: lime steamed fish fillets
directions: Arrange fillets on a steamer rack over boiling water.
Squeeze the lime juice over them and top with shallots and black pepper. Cover and steam for about 5 minutes, until fish flakes easily with a fork.

title: mother's raisin-oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix together thoroughly shortening, sugar, eggs and milk. Blend in flour sifted with soda, salt and cinnamon.
Stir in raisins and oats.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto a greased baking sheet.
Bake in a moderately hot 375° oven about 12 minutes. Makes about 3 dozen cookies.

title: dessert salad
directions: Mix together and chill after preparing jello as directed.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: passover mocha nut torte
directions: Have eggs at room temperature.
Heat oven to moderate 350° oven.
Grease two 9-inch layer pans.
Line with wax paper.
Grease again.
Beat egg yolks and 1/2 cup of sugar until thick and lemon colored.
Stir in rind and juice, nuts, cinnamon and matzo meal. Beat egg whites until stiff but not dry.
Beat in remaining sugar. Fold into mixture.
Put into pans.
Bake 35 minutes or until cake springs back to touch.
Invert on cooling rack and cool in pans. Remove from pans and peel paper.
Whip cream and flavor with sugar and instant coffee.
Spread half cream on one layer.
Top with second layer.
Spread rest of cream.
Garnish with shaved chocolate bar.
Chill.

title: raspberry sauce
directions: Reserve 1/4 cup raspberries for garnish.
Puree remaining raspberries and honey together in blender or food processor, about one minute, so that berries retain some of their texture.
Makes about 2 cups.

title: o'henry bars
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together.
Spread on cookie sheet, 11 x 17-inch.
Bake 15 minutes at 375°.
Cool.
Melt chips and peanut butter and pour on cooked bars.
Cut into squares.

title: neiman marcus brownies
directions: Mix the cake mix, egg and 1 stick butter and press into a buttered Pyrex dish.
Mix the cream cheese, confectioners sugar, eggs and 1 stick of butter and pour over cake mixture.
Top with chopped pecans.
Bake for 1 hour at 300°.
Wait 1 hour before cutting, but better if left sitting overnight.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Slice potatoes.
In roaster, put a layer of potatoes and cheese on top.
Make another layer.
Put cheese on top.
Pour can of Cheddar cheese on top; mix can with a little water.
Put in oven at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: seafood tortellini
directions: Put the garlic, 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese, cream, chicken broth and flour in a blender and blend until smooth.
Set aside.
Cook the tortellini in 1 1/2 to 2 quarts boiling water 5 to 8 minutes or until just tender.
Drain and return to the pan.
Add the bell pepper and blender mixture and cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until the
sauce begins to thicken.
Add the peas, Prosciutto and shrimp and cook to heat through and further thicken the sauce.
Season to taste with salt and pepper; stir in the 2 tablespoons basil just before serving.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Blend all together in large bowl.
Beat 4 minutes on medium speed.
Pour into 2 greased 9-inch round cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Frost with Pina Colada Frosting.

title: country fried apples
directions: Core and thinly slice apples.
In a 12-inch skillet, melt butter.
Add apples; saute 10 minutes.
Combine sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle over apples.
Cook, stirring occasionally, until tender, about 5 minutes more.
Makes 4 servings.

title: mozzarella chicken
directions: In shallow bowl, combine egg and milk.
In another bowl combine bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese and seasonings.
Dip each chicken piece in egg mixture, then crumb mixture.
Brown chicken in skillet with oleo, until no longer pink in middle.
Heat sauce in saucepan with basil until warm.
When chicken is done, sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.
Remove from heat.
Cover and let set 2 to 3 minutes, until cheese melts.
Serve with sauce.

title: cinnamon dream bars!
directions: Mix together until pasty.
Bake for 12 to 14 minutes. Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar mixture.
Brush with butter and sprinkle again.
Cool to eat!

title: tempura
directions: Remove the head and shell of the prawns, leaving the tails on. Slit the front with a knife in order to prevent shrinking in oil. Wash and cut parsley. Cut a NORI sheet into four rectangles.

title: lemon dessert
directions: Mix flour, oleo and pecans (if desired).
Press in pan and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Let cool.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat egg whites until peaks form.
Add salt and sugar.
Beat until very stiff.
Fold in nuts and chips. Place in oven. Turn off oven and leave overnight.

title: 5 hour beef stew
directions: Do not brown meat.
Mix together and bake in 250° oven for 5 hours in covered pan.

title: duffie's deer stew
directions: We own a
permanent deer camp with log cabin consisting of sleeping quarters,	fireplace,
cooking
facilities
(both inside and outside of cabin).
Each year we invite 200 friends and neighbors to our camp for a
cookout
the night before the deer season opens.
We have a
very
large
outdoor
charcoal grill with covered shed for barbecuing.
We
cook 80 pounds of boneless pork butts in an old
time	cast-iron wash pot heated by a LP gas burner.

title: cheesy vegetable sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in a 1 quart glass bowl.
Microwave at medium-high 2 minutes or until cheese melts, stirring at 1 minute intervals with a wire whisk.
Serve sauce over baked potatoes or other vegetables.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Immediately after removing cake from oven, use handle of a wooden spoon to poke holes 1/2-inch evenly all over cake.

title: mexican tequitos
directions: Bake potatoes.
Scrape meat from potatoes.
Spoon into fajita. Roll up fajita, edge down.
Cook in oil, on medium heat, until crisp.
Drain on paper towel for 5 minutes.

title: marian's moss cheese ball
directions: Put cheese in bowl until room temperature.
Beat at medium speed until mixed.
Add onion and sauce.
Stir in nuts.
Chill 3 to 4 hours.
Roll into ball.
Chill 3 to 4 more hours.
Roll in chopped parsley.
Refrigerate.

title: do nothing cake
directions: Mix together with spoon (no mixer) in a sheet cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes, or until done.
After cake has cooled, ice.

title: suckers
directions: Combine sugar, water and corn syrup.
Cook to hard crack stage (300°).
Remove from heat.
Add coloring and stir approximately 2 to 3 minutes until it begins to thicken.
Stir in flavoring.
Pour into molds arranged on a greased cookie sheet.
Yield:

title: au gratin potatoes
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan.
Add flour and cook until thickened.
Slowly add milk, stirring constantly.
Add salt and pepper.
Stir in 1 cup grated cheese and cook until melted. Arrange potatoes and diced onion in baking dish.
Pour cheese sauce over potatoes and sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: four-grain cornbread
directions: Place millet in a small bowl.
Cover with 3/4 cup hot tap water. Set aside until millet softens and absorbs water, about 15 minutes.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown hamburger; set aside.
Saute onion in pan with butter. Add hamburger juices to onion and simmer.
Cook remaining ingredients 15 to 20 minutes, then add hamburger and onion.
Cook sauce at least 30 additional minutes.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown together the hamburger, onion and bacon; drain.
Mix remaining ingredients with hamburger mixture.
Put in casserole and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: australian chocolate pudding cake(self saucing)
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add beaten egg and mix.
Add flour (self-rising) and cocoa with milk.
Mix well and pour into a Bundt pan.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup of sugar and 1 dessert spoon of cocoa over the top of the mixture.
Add 1 1/2 cups of hot water.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serve with ice cream.

title: zesty tomato sauce
directions: Saute garlic in olive oil until soft (do not brown), about 5 minutes.
Brown sausages in garlic and oil over medium flame. Cook about 20 minutes.
Add tomatoes, wine, salt, Tabasco and basil; simmer for 2 hours to desired thickness.
Stir frequently. Serve over spaghetti.

title: birthday cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add milk with vanilla alternately with sifted dry ingredients.
Beat egg whites and add the 1/4 cup of sugar.
Fold into the batter last.
Pour into 2 greased pans. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: pineapple surprise
directions: Place crumbled loaf bread in a baking dish; pour pineapple on top.
Beat eggs, sugar and butter together.
Pour over crumbs and pineapple.
Bake at 350° until brown on top.

title: deluxe chocolate marshmallow bars
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat until fluffy.
Combine flour, baking powder, salt and cocoa and add to creamed mixture.
Stir in nuts, if desired.

title: pineapple cookies
directions: Cream together sugar and shortening.
Add eggs.
Dissolve baking soda in pineapple.
Stir in vanilla, flour and salt.
Drop cookies on greased sheet and sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 375° for 7 to 10 minutes.

title: homemade banana nut ice cream
directions: Mix together and pour into freezer and finish filling with milk and freeze according to your freezer.

title: marilyn's chili(trouble, but worth it!)
directions: Cook onion in skillet slightly and transfer to a large pot. Add beans, chili style tomatoes and juice from whole tomatoes. Remove and discard seeds from tomatoes; chop and add to pot.
Add sugar and stir.
Brown beef; drain off grease (rinse off under hot water).
Add beef to pot.
Add chili powder and chili sauce. Squeeze generous amount of ketchup into pot.
Stir.
Cook on high enough temperature for mixture to bubble.
Turn heat down and simmer 1 hour.
Stir occasionally.
Salt to taste.

title: yogurt biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll out on floured board to about 3/4 to 1-inch thickness.
Cut out biscuits and place on ungreased pan and bake at 425° until browned to desired texture. These are low-fat and taste wonderful!

title: ice cream balls
directions: Soften ice cream into small balls.
Mix other ingredients well. Roll ice cream balls in mixture.
Place in fluted paper cups and freeze.

title: mushroom appetizers
directions: Trim crust from thin bread, roll flat with rolling pin.
Saute mushrooms and onion.
Chip cream cheese into this mixture.
Add other seasonings and mix well.
Spread on bread and roll up like jelly roll.
Freeze on cookie sheet with seam being on bottom. Slice into 3 pieces.
Roll in melted butter and bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes or until lightly browned.
Good for several days in freezer.
Dip and cook the day you plan to eat them.

title: apple bread
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour in greased and floured pan or muffin tin.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix picante sauce and cream cheese together; pour in pan.
Top with chopped onion, lettuce, tomato and shredded cheese.

title: layered salad
directions: In large flat cake pan, layer bite sized pieces of lettuce, cauliflower buds, thin slices of purple onion and crisp bacon (cooled and broken up).
Mix mayonnaise and sugar and spread over top.
Sprinkle rather heavily with grated Parmesan cheese. Refrigerate eight hours or overnight.
Toss just before serving.

title: oyster stew
directions: Add oysters to hot milk.
Add butter and seasoning.
Simmer until oysters curl and are tender, approximately 3 hours.

title: judy caine's cheesy new potatoes
directions: Cut in cubes, unpeeled potatoes.
Cover potatoes with salted water, bring to a boil; reduce heat and cook about 15 minutes or until tender.
Drain potatoes and cool slightly.
Stir in butter and pepper, toss lightly.

title: chocolate chip candy
directions: Melt chips over low heat with sweetened condensed milk. Remove from heat and stir in nuts and vanilla.
Spread onto wax paper lined 8 x 8-inch pan.
Chill 2 hours or until firm.
Cut into squares.

title: pot pie dumplings
directions: Beat with a fork.
Add enough flour to make a soft dough. Roll on a floured board to about 1-inch thick.
Cut in 1-inch squares.
Freeze on a cookie sheet, then bag and put in plastic bags and keep in the freezer until needed.
Good in beef and chicken broth.

title: hamburger cheese bake
directions: In a large skillet cook meat and onion.
Stir in tomato sauce, sugar, salt, garlic salt and pepper.
Remove from heat.

title: chicken and rice enchiladas
directions: Chop cooked chicken and onions in butter.
Add soup, broth, chili powder or green chillies, pimentos and rice.
Simmer and mix well for 5 minutes.
Butter a 9 x 13-inch glass pan.
Line with 1/2 Doritos and alternate with chicken mixture and cheese.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cream coconut pie
directions: Blend sugar and flour with cold milk.
Add to scalded milk, stirring constantly.
Cook over low heat until thickened.
Add beaten egg yolks.
Stir thoroughly.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and coconut.
Cool.
Pour into baked pastry crust.
Cover with meringue.

title: grandma's sugar cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll out on floured board and cut thick.
Sprinkle with sugar and bake in 350° oven.

title: chicken marsala
directions: Arrange chicken in shallow casserole dish, 9 x 13 Pyrex. Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Combine sour cream, mayo and wine. Mix ingredients well and pour over chicken breasts.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 1 hour.
Serve with white rice.
The chicken and sauce over the rice is delicious.
Serves 4.

title: taco soup to fill a big roaster
directions: This will feed 50 hungry folks!

title: polish stuffed cabbage
directions: Cover cabbage leaves with cool water, and let stand 5 minutes until limp.
Drain.
Combine first ingredients.
Place equal portions of meat in center of leaves.
Fasten sides after folding over and secure with toothpicks.
Place in large pan and combine sauce mixture and taste.
May need more brown sugar.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Baste occasionally.
Makes 5 servings.

title: dried beef noodle casserole
directions: Heat soup.
Add milk and cheese.
Stir until dissolved.
Add pimento, beef and noodles.
Season to taste.
Pour into greased casserole.
Top with buttered crumbs.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: quick red beans and rice
directions: Prepare rice, set aside.

title: creamy chocolate layered pie
directions: *Helpful Hints:
Soften cream cheese in microwave on High for 15 to 20 seconds.

title: pineapple banana milkshake
directions: Combine all ingredients except ice cubes in blender.
Blend. Add ice cubes 2 at a time.
Shake should be thick and smooth.

title: saffron buns
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup warm water; add sugar and 1/2 cup flour and let rise.
Put saffron in 1 cup water; simmer and cool to lukewarm.
Sift flour, 2 cups sugar and salt and cut in shortening.
Add currants and nutmeg.
Add saffron that has been cooled.
Add lukewarm water (at least 2 cups); let rise until double.
Form into buns; let rise.
All ingredients should be room temperature.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 2 (9 x 13-inch ) pans.

title: tuna ball
directions: Mix tuna and cream cheese together.
Form into ball.
Serve on Ritz crackers.

title: creole english peas
directions: Saute green pepper, onion and celery in oleo.
Mix with other ingredients and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Mix sugars, eggs and shortening.
Sift flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt; add to first mixture.
Blend well.
Add oats, chips and nuts.
Roll batter into small balls size of walnuts and bake 10 to 12 minutes at 325° or 350° (according to oven).
Makes 6 to 7 dozen.

title: corn bread
directions: Combine in medium size bowl the first 5 ingredients.
Beat in rest of ingredients until smooth.
Pour into a greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake in 425° oven for 20 minutes or until top springs back when lightly touched.
Cool in pan on wire rack only!

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Mix cucumbers, onions and salt.
Cover with ice.
Let set for 2 hours.

title: flaky pastry(for one 2-crust pie or two 8 to 9-inch)
directions: In a medium bowl, with a fork, stir flour and salt.
With pastry blender or two knives used scissor fashion, cut shortening into flour until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.

title: spinach dip
directions: Chop green onions and add to soup mix, chopped spinach and sour cream.
Mix thoroughly.
Remove center of bread and place dip mixture in center.
May use crackers or pieces of bread for dip. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: crackletop ginger cookies
directions: Thoroughly cream sugar and shortening.
Add egg; mix well. Stir in molasses.
Sift dry ingredients and add to molasses mixture.
Chill.
Roll into balls, about 1-inch in diameter.
Roll in sugar.
Bake in 350° oven 18 to 20 minutes.

title: chocolate pudding cake
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, cocoa, baking powder and salt. Add butter, milk, nuts and vanilla and beat about 2 minutes.
Add topping before baking.

title: reese's peanut butter cookies
directions: Lightly grease miniature muffin tins.
Slice cookie dough 1-inch thick then quarter each slice.
Place each quarter into miniature muffin tins.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and while still hot push a Reese's cup into each cookie puff.
Let cool in the tins before removing.

title: grandma's potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes in salt water and drain.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Add green beans and tomato soup.
Top with mashed potatoes.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes or until potatoes brown.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Boil macaroni 8 minutes; drain.
Add all ingredients together. Stir well. Refrigerate until cool.

title: aunt mary's best oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine butter, sugars, eggs and vanilla.
Beat about 2 minutes, until fluffy.
Add the rolled oats, flour, baking soda and salt to beaten mixture.
Mix well. Stir in nuts, chocolate chips and/or raisins.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls about 2 inches apart on greased sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Cook spaghetti noodles; drain.
Brown meat in a skillet; drain off grease.
Mix noodles and meat with all other ingredients. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.
May be prepared ahead and frozen.

title: maple drop cookies
directions: Mix ingredients and add nuts and/or chocolate chips if you prefer.
Bake at 400° for 12 minutes.

title: snickers salad
directions: Whisk together buttermilk, Cool Whip and pudding with a wire whip.
Fold in apples cut in bite-size pieces and Snickers bars, cut in bite-size pieces.
This can be made the night before.

title: steamed fish
directions: Clean fish and lightly sprinkle with salt in stomach.
Boil water in pan big enough for fish.
Use enough water to just cover fish.
When water boils, add fish and ginger.
Turn heat off, cover and let stand 30 minutes.
Take fish out on platter.

title: beef brisket roast
directions: Mix together ingredients.
Line a baking pan with heavy-duty foil.
Pour mixture over roast.
Bake in 325° oven for 1 hour per pound.
Thicken gravy by mixing a little flour with water and bring to a boil.

title: good stuff
directions: Finely chop tomatoes, cucumber, onion, bell pepper and celery. Drain vegetables and add salt to mayonnaise. Combine with vegetables. Stir gelatin into 1/4 cup water. Add 4 tablespoons hot water. Stir until gelatin is dissolved and add to vegetable mixture. Pour into mold and chill overnight. Serve with crackers.

title: warm broccoli cheese dip
directions: Thaw broccoli and squeeze out all excess water.
Mix all ingredients in baking bowl and bake for 25 minutes at 375° or until golden brown.

title: vanilla chewies
directions: Make dough out of cake mix, margarine and 1 egg.
Spread in bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Then sprinkle with chopped pecans.

title: curry dip
directions: Mash garlic button in mixing bowl, then remove it.
Add all other ingredients and mix together.
Store in refrigerator.

title: zucchini and tomato casserole
directions: Season the flour with salt and pepper.
Dredge the zucchini in the flour.
In a large skillet, saute in oil until browned (add more oil if needed).
Transfer to paper towel and drain.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Boil shrimp until it turns pink (approximately 5 to 10 minutes); devein and de-shell.
Cook onions and celery in bacon drippings.
Add flour and seasonings and blend.
Slowly add water. Add everything else except shrimp.
Cook for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat all ingredients together and pour into prepared pan.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool and frost.

title: toffee bars
directions: Combine and boil for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and add 1 cup chopped nuts.
Line a large cookie sheet with foil, then lay graham crackers on the foil until pan is completely covered. Spread mixture over graham crackers.
Bake at 350° for 7 to 8 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Let cool.
Break into bite-size pieces and store in airtight container.

title: sausage-n-cheese strata
directions: Brown sausage, drain.
Add vegetables and cook 5 minutes.
Let cool 10 minutes.
Stir into sausage mixture cheese and croutons. Pour into 8-inch square casserole dish.
Beat eggs and milk.
Pour over sausage mixture.
Cover and let set in refrigerator awhile. Take from refrigerator and bake 350° for 45 to 50 minutes until brown.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chicken broccoli
directions: Cook broccoli and spread in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix chicken, soup, mayonnaise, mushrooms and curry powder in bowl. Spread over broccoli.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Cover dish with foil. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
This can be frozen and cooked later.
Can be microwaved. Yields 6 servings.

title: prism cake
directions: Mix each box of jello (cherry, orange and lime) with 1 1/2 cups hot water; let set until firm.
Heat pineapple juice and sugar until dissolved.
Add lemon jello; cool until syrupy.
Add lemon mixture to whipped cream; fold in cubed jello (the 3 boxes which have been cubed).
Make a graham cracker crust.
Press into bottom of spring-form pan.
Pour mixture into pan.
Top with some of the graham cracker crust.
Let chill 24 hours.

title: chocolate cream cheese bars("brenda's delight")
directions: Mix flour, pecans and butter until crumbly.
Pat into a 9 x 11-inch pan.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 350° or until edges start to brown.
Let crust cool.
Mix cream cheese, Cool Whip and powdered sugar together.
Spread on crust.
Mix 3 cups cold milk with packages of instant pudding.
Mix together at low speed for approximately 2 minutes.
Pour over cream cheese mixture.
Let pudding set about 5 minutes; then spread Cool Whip over pudding. Add shavings of 1 Hershey bar for decorative touch.
Refrigerate.

title: potato puppies
directions: Mix paprika and meal together in a bowl; set aside.
Cook potatoes in boiling water until tender.
Drain water off potatoes. Mash potatoes together with a fork.
Add onion, eggs, salt and pepper.
Form small balls and roll in meal mixture.
Drop balls in a deep fryer and cook until golden brown.

title: ice cream jello mold
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 1 cup hot fruit juice; let cool a little. Add ice cream and stir until dissolved.
Add fruit and put in oiled mold.

title: hoppin john
directions: Cut bacon in small pieces and fry with onions until onions are golden brown.
Cook rice in 2 cups water; cook black-eyed peas according to directions on package.
Combine all.
Add butter, salt and pepper and mix well.
Makes 6 servings.

title: breezy brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream together oleo, sugar, eggs and salt.
Beat well.
Blend in chocolate syrup.
Add flour.
Pour into greased and floured 10 1/2 x 15 1/2-inch baking pan.
Bake for 22 minutes, or 18 or 19 minutes here (Port Charlotte).

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Separate eggs. Put egg yolks in a heavy pan. Add brown sugar, flour, milk, water, Crisco, salt and vanilla. Stir over low heat until thick. Let mixture cool slightly. Then pour into pie shell. Beat the egg whites until stiff. Add 4 to 5 tablespoons sugar. Spread over pie, being careful to put the meringue all the way to the edge of the shell. Bake in a 350° oven until browned.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Grease baking pan, then flour.
Beat eggs, oil and sugar.
Add grated zucchini and vanilla.
Mix well.
Sift flour, salt, baking powder, baking soda and cinnamon.
Beat all well.
Pour into pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: quick and easy dressing
directions: Melt butter in skillet with onion and celery.
Cook until tender.
Prepare chicken bouillon cube with 3 or 4 cups water. Add all ingredients together; bake 35 to 40 minutes at 400°.

title: brown rice
directions: Melt butter in casserole dish.
Stir uncooked rice in butter until coated.
Add the soups and water.
Cook for 1 hour in oven at 325°, covered.
After an hour, remove cover and stir.
If rice is not soft (done) let cook uncovered a little longer.

title: never fail cupcakes
directions: Put in bowl in order given.
Do not mix until last item has been added, then beat well. Bake in moderate oven in baking cups.

title: honey nut granola
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine all ingredients, except raisins; mix well.
Bake in lightly greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in raisins.
Spread mixture onto ungreased cookie sheet; cool.
Store in cool dry place or in refrigerator.
Makes about 6 cups.

title: easy cheese potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine all ingredients except 1/2 cup Colby cheese.
Mix well.
Turn into greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Bake 55 to 60 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake 3 to 5 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Brown onion in butter until transparent.
Then add flour; stir until thickened.
Add warm milk and broccoli and cook until tender.
Add grated cheese and serve.

title: hot spiced cider
directions: Add the sugar and spices to the cider in a large saucepan. Simmer for 15 minutes; don't boil.
Strain and serve in small glasses or mugs.

title: french toast
directions: Mix all ingredients except the bread in mixing bowl.
Melt butter in skillet or frying pan and heat to 350°.
Dip your bread in eggs and milk.
Place in hot frying pan.
Brown on one side and flip over.
Serve with warm butter, syrup or sugar and cinnamon.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix potatoes, sugar and margarine until blended.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie shells.
Makes 2 pies.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: red lobster clam chowder
directions: In soup pot, melt butter over medium heat.
Add onion, celery, leeks and garlic.
Saute for 3 minutes, mixing often. Remove from heat and add flour, mixing well.
Add milk and whisk vigorously.
Drain clams and add juice to soup.
Slowly bring to a boil, mixing often.
reduce heat to a simmer.
Add potatoes and seasonings; simmer 10 minutes.
Add clams and simmer 5-8 minutes. Finish with heavy cream.
Serve.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix flour, sugar, salt and shortening with pastry blender. Mix beaten egg, water and vinegar in a smaller bowl.
Combine the two mixtures until wet.
Divide into five equal balls and wrap in aluminum foil.
Freeze until ready to use.

title: spoon bread
directions: Heat 2 cups milk over low heat.
Stir in corn meal and bring to boil.
Cook until thick (about 5 minutes).
Add 1 more cup of milk.
Beat in eggs and beat thoroughly.
Add baking powder, salt and butter or oil.
Beat well.
Turn into a greased 2-quart baking dish.
Bake 30 minutes at 350° or until firmly set.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix together eggs, mayonnaise, grated cheese, soup and onion. Layer broccoli in casserole dish, 9 x 13 x 2-inch.
Layer cheese mixture.
Cook Stove Top stuffing as directed.
Add more water. Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Spread stuffing over top of mixture.
tags: cream of mushroom soup or celery

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until fluffy.
Add sugar and beat together.
Add 1 vanilla, zucchini and vegetable oil.

title: guacamole
directions: Mix well all ingredients.
Adjust seasonings.
Serve with corn chips.
Makes 1 3/4 cups.

title: fudge pie
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients. Pour mixture into pastry shell. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until set. Serve with ice cream, if desired.

title: coconut pie(makes 2 pies)
directions: Mix and put into 2 pie shells.
Bake at 325° for approximately 1 hour or until lightly browned on top.

title: baked pumpkin seeds
directions: Lay a single layer of seeds on a baking pan.
Sprinkle with salt.
Cook at 425° until dry and toasted, about 10 minutes.
Stir after 5 minutes.
Salt to taste.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti according to package directions.
Drain, rinse and
set
aside.
In
a medium saucepan, add soup, milk, onion, garlic salt
and
1/4 cup of the cheese.
Heat over low heat, stirring
until smooth; add chicken.
Put spaghetti in a 10 x 6-inch
Pyrex
dish
and pour sauce over spaghetti.
Mix well and top
with remaining cheese and the parsley.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken squares
directions: Blend cream cheese and margarine until smooth (reserve 1 tablespoon margarine).
Add next 6 ingredients; mix well. Separate crescent dough into 4 rectangles and roll each one a little larger.
Firmly press perforations to seal.
Spoon 1/2 cup chicken mixture in center.
Pull 4 corners to center.
Slightly twist to seal edges.
Brush tops with reserved margarine.
Dip into crushed croutons.
Bake in ungreased cookie sheet 20 to 25 minutes in a 350° oven until golden brown.

title: applesauce puffs(sure to be a favorite)
directions: Combine biscuit mix, 1/4 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon ground cinnamon.
Combine 1 slightly beaten egg, 1/2 cup applesauce and nonfat dry milk.
Add to dry mixture and beat vigorously for 30 seconds.
Fill greased muffin pans 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool slightly and remove from pans.

title: easy fruit cobbler
directions: Melt butter in ovenproof pan.
Add rest of ingredients.
Bake in a 350° oven until brown, about 1 hour.

title: sauerbraten (sweet and sour beef)
directions: Rub meat with pepper; place in large glass dish.
Add onion and all the spices.
Heat vinegar and water to boiling.
Pour over meat and spices.
Cover dish with foil; marinate in refrigerator 12 to 36 hours.
Turn occasionally.
Strain and reserve liquid. Wipe roast dry.

title: reuben casserole
directions: Mix together sauerkraut, sour cream, onion and garlic. Spread in buttered 9 by 9 casserole dish.
Crumble meat over top. Sprinkle cheese over meat layer.
Spread bread cubes or crumbs over cheese layer.	Pour melted butter over all.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
If you like Reuben sandwiches, you will like this!
6 to 8 servings.

title: christmas balls
directions: Cream butter, sugar, vanilla, water and salt.
Sift flour.
Add pecans and flour to butter mixture.
Roll batter into small balls. Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar while hot. Cool and store in airtight containers.
Freezes very well.

title: chocolate drop cookies
directions: Mix in a 2-quart bowl the shortening, water and egg.
Sift together the flour, sugar, cocoa, dry milk, soda and salt.
Add to first mixture and mix well.
Stir in nuts.
Drop about 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake near center of oven about 10 minutes or until springs back.
Cool and frost with 1 tablespoon of frosting for each cookie.
Fudge frosting is best.

title: rotini salad
directions: Cut all vegetables up in bite size pieces.
Add cooked and drained rotini and red onion.
Prepare dressing according to package directions.
Add to vegetables and toss.

title: coffee king
directions: Spray Bundt pan with Pam; put marmalade and nuts in bottom. Mix brown sugar and cinnamon and melt margarine.
Dip biscuits in margarine and in brown sugar.
Stand up in marmalade around pan. Bake at 350° until brown.

title: bran applesauce bread or muffins
directions: Combine first 9 ingredients.
Add applesauce, oil and eggs; mix well.
Stir in raisins and nuts.
Bake in loaf pan, 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 3-inch at 350° for 40 minutes or 12 large muffins at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes.

title: vidalia onion casserole
directions: Melt stick of butter in a large pot with oil.
Add onions, finely chopped.
Saute until onions are tender.
Add chicken broth and let simmer for a few minutes, then add box of Ritz crackers. Add enough crackers to make the mixture very thick and stiff. Grate the cheese.
Layer casserole dish with a layer of mixture, then a layer of cheese, alternating until finished.
Put some cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, just before serving.

title: rice with butter and sage leaves
directions: Bring about 3-quarts salted water to boil in a large saucepan. Add rice and boil over high heat for 16 minutes.
Drain the rice, turn it onto a serving dish and sprinkle with cheese.
When rice is almost ready, heat butter with sage leaves in a skillet until butter turns chestnut brown.
Pour over the rice and serve.

title: golden chicken nuggets
directions: Debone and cut chicken breasts into 1-inch squares.
Combine all ingredients, except butter.
Dip in butter, then in crumb mixture.
Put in single layer on foil-lined sheet.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.

title: apple butter
directions: Cook apples
and cider 2 to 3 hours or until apples are thick and mushy, then put through food mill or strainer.
Pour back into
roaster;
add
sugar,
spices
and
salt.
Stir to distribute
the
sugar.
Return
to stove and continue cooking until
butter is thick as desired.
Pour hot apple butter into glass jars.
Fill
to
1/8 inch top of jars.
Put dome lids on jars; screw bands tight.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cut cabbage in bite size pieces; cook in saltwater until soft. Drain and put in baking dish. Heat soup (do not add water to soup). Chop sweet pepper and onion with dash of black pepper. Pour over cabbage. Top with Mozzarella cheese. Bake in 350° oven until it bubbles.

title: cheese dip
directions: Let cream cheese soften at room temperature.
Mix all ingredients together, blending well.
Serve with fresh vegetables. (I use broccoli, cauliflower, carrot sticks and celery sticks.)

title: ice cream dessert
directions: Melt chocolate in milk.
Boil gently uncovered for 4 minutes (thickens), stirring constantly.
Add marshmallows.
Heat and stir until melted.
Chill.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together and form into 1-inch balls. Place on an ungreased baking sheet 1-inch apart.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: easy, delicious chicken and dumplings
directions: Put about 3 quarts of hot water in a large, heavy pot.
Open soup and stir into water until it is well mixed.
Dissolve bouillon cubes and onion soup mix in mixture.
Boil until it begins to thicken, about 10 to 15 minutes.
Open cans of chicken and add to the rest of the ingredients.
Open biscuits and pinch into small balls, about 5 per biscuit.
Drop into boiling broth. Stir until well coated with the broth.
Cover with lid and simmer 20 minutes.

title: peanut butter brownies
directions: Combine sugar, flour, cocoa and baking powder.
In medium size bowl, beat together butter and peanut butter, until fluffy.
Now, beat in eggs and milk.
Add peanut butter mixture to flour mixture.
Stir until smooth and well combined.
Spread evenly into 13 x 9 x 2-inch sprayed pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Cool and cut into squares.

title: marinated turkey
directions: Mix together and marinate in a trash bag to thaw in fridge for a couple of days.
Rotate a couple of times a day.
Cook regular, but cover.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Pour off salmon liquid.
Combine all ingredients plus 3 tablespoons salad oil.
Shape into loaf and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except chips.
Crush chips on top of casserole and bake at 350° until thoroughly heated.

title: corn bread stuffing side dish
directions: Prepare stuffing mix according to directions on package. Substitute beer for the water if you prefer.
Place half the stuffing in a large greased baking pan (11 x 14-inch).
Add half of other ingredients in rows, alternating colors or keeping all the fruit on one side.
Place the remaining stuffing over the layer of other ingredients.
Keeping the pattern, place remaining fruit, nuts and oysters on top layer.
This can be prepared several hours before needed.
Warm in oven, uncovered, just before serving.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve blackberry gelatin in 2 cups boiling water in large bowl.
Soften unflavored gelatin in 3/4 cup cold water.
Combine with blackberry gelatin; mix well.
Stir in blueberries and pineapple.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch dish.
Chill until set.
Combine cream cheese with next three ingredients in mixer bowl.
Beat until well blended.
Stir in pecans.
Spread over congealed layer.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Beat eggs slightly with fork.
Beat in remaining ingredients.
Place pastry lined pie plate on oven rack; pour in filling.
Bake 15 minutes.
Reduce oven temperature to 350°.
Bake until knife inserted in center comes out clean, approximately 1 hour.
Cool.

title: spoon rolls
directions: Mix together dissolved yeast, egg, sugar and margarine.
Add all of flour and stir.
Cover in glass bowl.
Can be used immediately or placed in refrigerator and used as needed.
Will keep up to 2 weeks.
To bake:
Drop by spoonfuls into greased muffin tins.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: party buffet chicken
directions: Line shallow casserole with dried beef.
Brown chicken in butter and place on beef.
Mix soup, half and half, poultry seasoning and 2 tablespoons white wine or vermouth until smooth. Pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until tender. Sprinkle with cheese and bake 10 minutes longer.

title: "whipped cream" icing
directions: Mix the milk and the flour and cook over low heat, stirring constantly until it becomes very thick.
Cool.
In large mixing bowl, beat until fluffy the margarine, sugar and vanilla.
Add white sauce mixture to this and continue beating until it is the consistency of whipped cream.
Icing will stay soft as whipped cream as long as the cake lasts.
Great on your favorite chocolate cake!

title: lite chocolate sauce
directions: In small saucepan over low heat, melt margarine.
Remove from heat; stir in sugar, cocoa and corn syrup.
Add evaporated skim milk.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, just until mixture begins to boil and is smooth.
Remove from heat; stir in vanilla. Cool slightly.
Spoon 1 tablespoon warm sauce over 1/2 cup vanilla ice milk for each serving.
Makes 3/4 cup sauce.

title: frozen vegetable dish
directions: Mix all together and put into a Pyrex dish.
Cover with crushed Ritz crackers.
Bake at 350°
for 30 minutes.

title: carrot salad
directions: Cook carrots until almost done.
Drain and place in a bowl with pepper and onion.
In a saucepan, place soup, sugar, vinegar, salt, pepper and oil.
Bring to a full boil and pour over carrot mixture.
Refrigerate overnight.
Ready to serve. Good.

title: trail jambalaya
directions: Combine rice and next 9 ingredients with 2 cups water and tomato sauce in Dutch oven.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat, cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Stir in sausage and cook until mixture is thoroughly heated. Yield: 4 servings.

title: carl's camp stove pork chops
directions: In a very large bowl, put in the pork chops.
Add the salt, pepper and parsley flakes to the buttermilk.
Pour over the pork chops, making sure liquid covers all the chops.
Marinate for at least 8 hours.

title: frog's eye salad
directions: Combine sugar, flour and salt.
Stir in pineapple juice and eggs. Cook, stirring constantly until thickened.
Add lemon juice. Cool to room temperature.
Prepare Acini De Pepe according to package directions, drain.
Combine egg mixture and Acini De Pepe. Mix well and refrigerate over night in air-tight container.
Add remaining ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Refrigerate in air-tight container until thoroughly chilled.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: apple salad
directions: Cook juice, sugar, flour and oleo together.
When cool, pour over apple mixture (cut up apples and add next 3 ingredients) and stir until fruit is coated.
When ready to serve, add Cool Whip.

title: cavetini
directions: Brown ground chuck and drain well.
Pour into a large bowl. Cook pasta.
Drain.
Pour into bowl with meat.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Add chunks of cheese and pour into a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Top with shredded Mozzarella cheese and pepperoni.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Yields 10 servings.

title: porcupine balls
directions: Combine rice, meat, onion, salt and pepper.
Mix well and form into small balls.
Brown all sides in a skillet with small amount of Crisco.
Heat soup and water, mixed in bottom of pressure cooker.
Place meatballs in boiling soup mixture and let come to boil.
Place pressure cooker lid on pan and cook for 10 minutes at 15 pounds pressure.
Let pressure drop before removing lid or meatballs may be placed in a casserole dish.
Cover with the soup and bake, covered at 350° for about 1 1/2 hours.
Remove cover last 15 minutes.

title: creamy swiss spinach dip
directions: In a small microwave-safe mixing bowl, beat cream cheese and garlic powder until smooth. Stir in spinach and Swiss cheese. Cover and microwave on High for 5 to 8 minutes or until cheese is melted, stirring occasionally.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter or margarine in a 3-quart ovenproof dish.
Mix flour and sugar together and stir into melted butter.
Add milk and peaches and stir together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, until crust is golden brown.

title: beer bread
directions: Grease a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Combine flour, beer and honey in large bowl.
Stir together until well mixed.
Spread batter in prepared pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until browned and a wooden pick comes out clean.
Turn out on rack. Cool before slicing.
Yield:
1 loaf.

title: flower pot dirt cake
directions: Will need 1 new flower pot (8 x 10-inches), silk flowers and candy gummy worms.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Pour rice over bottom of roasting pan.
Place chicken parts over rice.
Mix cans of soup and water and distribute evenly over chicken slowly.
Sprinkle with salt and dry onion mix.
Cover; cook for 1 hour and 30 minutes (don't peek) at 350°.

title: cathy's seven layer salad
directions: Layer the ingredients, beginning with the lettuce.
Let sit for several hours.
Toss prior to serving.
You need to mix the salad well so it is not gritty from the sugar.

title: easy fruit dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill. Serve with assortment of cut up fruits.

title: it's better than potato salad
directions: Cook rice according to package directions; chill.
Add mayonnaise, celery, onion, mustard and salt.
Mix well and chill. Stir in eggs, carrots and cucumber before serving.
(Can use 2 cups Minute Rice.)

title: jalapeno cornbreadgroves, texas
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Bake in three well greased (8 X 8-inch) pans at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown. Serves 12.

title: lepp cookies
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco
together.
Combine
buttermilk and soda. Add alternately with flour.
Roll thick
and
cut out.
Bake at 325° to 350°.
Brush with beaten egg or decorate as desired.

title: meal in a dish
directions: Brown meat; add onion, celery and pepper.
Cook slowly for several minutes.
Drain off fat.
Add cooked noodles, tomato sauce, corn and chili powder. Turn into a baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Top with cheese and bake about 10 minutes to melt cheese. Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: banana pudding cake
directions: Put bananas in mixing bowl and beat well. Add remaining ingredients. Blend, then beat at medium speed with mixer for 2 minutes.
Pour into a well-greased and floured 10-inch tube or Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 65 minutes.
Cool in pan 15 minutes. Remove from pan and cool on rack.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar, if desired. Very moist cake.

title: celestial chicken salad - mom's
directions: Mix the chicken, celery, mushrooms, pecans and bacon together and set aside.
In separate bowl, mix salad dressing, sour cream, salt and lemon juice together.
Combine both bowls and mix thoroughly.
Chill well before serving.

title: spanish tomato rice
directions: Cook bacon until crisp; remove.
Pour off half the fat.
In remaining fat, cook onion and green pepper until tender, but not brown.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer 45 minutes. Crumble bacon on top.

title: cranberry cookies
directions: Beat margarine for 30 seconds. Add one cup of the flour, brown sugar, sugar, egg, baking powder, cinnamon, vanilla and baking soda. Beat until thoroughly combined then beat in the remaining flour. Stir in oats, cranberries and nuts. Drop by teaspoons 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 375 degrees for 9-11 minutes or until edges are golden. Cool on wire rack.

title: pumpkin muffins
directions: Sift together flour, soda, cinnamon and salt.
Beat eggs, sugar and oil until fluffy.
Add dry ingredients to egg mixture and beat well.
Add pumpkin; beat well.
Pour into muffin tins paper liners.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: one pot pot roast
directions: Brown roast on both sides in large pan; add enough water to almost cover.
Add soup and mix.
Let cook until inside is pink. Add potatoes and carrots; cook until tender.
Serve with salad and tea.

title: crabwiches
directions: Combine all.
Add extra mayonnaise to make it spreadable. Toast one side of bread.
Spread crab on untoasted side, all the way to the edges. Broil until golden and bubbly.
Serves 8.

title: pickled peppers
directions: Sprinkle a bit of red pepper if peppers are sweet.
Mix brine, add chopped sliced peppers.
Stir every couple hours. After 8 hours, can peppers in jars.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Fry pork chops only until browned.
Cook rice.
Add onions, sliced mushrooms, parsley flakes and mushroom soup.
Put cooked rice in, after adding other ingredients in a baking dish.
Arrange pork chops (cooked) over rice.
Pour over chops and rice, the soup. Add water to moisten.
Bake about 1 hour at 325°.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Split loaf of bread lengthwise; butter both sides and then sprinkle with desired amount of garlic powder and Parmesan cheese. Clean broccoli and onion; dice and steam until tender-crisp.
Top half of the bread with Mozzarella cheese, then arrange broccoli-onion mixture over top.
Lay Cheddar cheese over top. Place other slice of bread on top to make sandwich.
Wrap in aluminum foil and bake at 300° for 30 minutes.
Slice and serve warm.

title: apple crisp delight
directions: Arrange apple slices in buttered 2 quart baking dish. Sift flour and measure. Add salt, cinnamon and sugar. Mix well with a fork. Cut in butter until mixture is crumbly and evenly mixed. Set this mixture aside. Add two or three tsp. of water to the apples in the dish. Then closely pack the cinnamon, sugar and flour mixture over the apple slices. Bake at 375° for 30 to 45 minutes. Check it in about 20 minutes. If topping is browning too fast, reduce temperature to 350°. Place on a rack to cool slightly. Serve warm as is or add ice cream.

title: john clapham's antipasto rolls
directions: Drain the olives and peppers.
Cut the peppers into 1-inch strips.
Center a strip of pepper on each slice of meat.
Put an olive at one end of the meat and roll jelly roll style.
Use toothpicks to secure them.

title: french toast custard
directions: Brush both sides of bread with butter. Place in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.

title: easy banana bread
directions: Mix oil and sugar well.
Add mashed bananas and eggs.
Add dry ingredients.
Bake in Bundt or tube cake pan at 350° for 30 minutes or until cake tests done.

title: tangy meatballs
directions: Combine beef, egg, chili sauce, onion, salt and pepper with 1 cup cracker crumbs.
Mix well.
Shape into tiny meatballs and roll in remaining 1/2 cup cracker crumbs.
Saute meatballs for 5 minutes in 1/2 inch hot oil, turning to brown all sides.
Remove to chafing dish and serve with toothpicks.
Yields about 30 meatballs.

title: fluffy cocoa frosting
directions: Mix cocoa and sugar mixture with the butter.
Blend in vanilla and half of milk.
Add remaining cocoa/sugar mixture and blend well.
Add remaining milk and beat to desired spreading consistency.
Additional milk may be added, if required.
Frosts two 9-inch layers.

title: cheese pudding
directions: Melt butter; add bread crumbs.
Add beaten egg yolks, milk and cheese.
Add dry ingredients.
Beat egg whites.
Fold into egg and milk mixture.
Let set 12 hours in refrigerator.
Bake in a 350° to 375° oven for 45 minutes or until set.

title: applesauce spice bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease an oblong pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inch. Mix all ingredients.
Spread in pan.
Bake about 25 minutes.
Cool and frost with browned butter frosting.
Yield:
32 bars.

title: hamburgers ranchero
directions: Mix ground beef, onion, oregano, salt and pepper.
Shape into 6 patties.
Broil until done.
Heat tortillas.
Top each tortilla with 1/2 cup lettuce and 1 patty.
Spoon salsa over each patty. These burgers can also be served in hamburger buns with shredded lettuce and salsa.

title: fresh spinach salad
directions: Mix sugar, ketchup, Worcestershire sauce and Mazola oil. Marinate fresh mushrooms in this mixture overnight.
Pour over spinach.
Sprinkle with bacon chips and hard-boiled eggs.

title: pineapple cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: pumpkin dip
directions: Cream powdered sugar and powdered sugar together. Add remaining ingredients and mix well. Chill. Dip ginger snaps in pumpkin dip. Deli snaps are best.

title: sausage cacciatore
directions: Boil the sausages for 20 minutes, then poke a hole in them so that they drain.

Slice the sausages. Saute the onions and peppers until the onions are translucent, then add the zucchini and mushrooms. Combine the sausages, chicken, vegetables and sauce in a large pot and simmer for about 1 hour.

title: clam chowder
directions: Chop bacon.
Fry until crisp.
Remove bacon from skillet. Drain on paper towel.
Add pepper, water, onion, potatoes and salt to grease in skillet.
Cook for 10 minutes, then add both milks and clams.
Cook 10 more minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Add bacon and sprinkle with parsley.
Serve hot.
Serves 4.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Combine sour cream with cream cheese.
Add celery, onion, salt, pepper and lemon juice.
Flake shrimp and add to cheese mixture. Serve on favorite crackers.

title: christmas bread without yeast(julekake uten gjar-soster kake)
directions: Blend eggs and sugar together.
Do not use mixer.
Add flour, baking powder, cardamom, milk and raisins.
Mix well and add melted butter.
Place in greased loaf pans and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Mix and pour into a greased 2-quart casserole.
Bake uncovered for 1 hour at 350°.

title: pan-fried chicken(100 portions)
directions: Roll chicken in flour mixed with salt, pepper and paprika. Pan-fry until brown in 1/2 melted shortening and 1/2 melted margarine.
Then put in oven and bake until done.

title: lite lemon cheesecake
directions: Spread an 8 or 9-inch spring-form pan or 9-inch pie plate with nonstick cooking spray.
Sprinkle bottom and side with graham cracker crumbs.
Completely dissolve gelatin in boiling water; pour into blender container.
Add cottage cheese and cream cheese; cover.
Blend at medium speed about 2 minutes.
Pour into a large bowl.
Gently stir in whipped topping.
Pour into prepared pan. Smooth top.
Chill until set, about 4 hours.
When ready to serve, remove side of pan.
Top cheesecake with pie filling.
Makes 8 servings.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cream the cream cheese. Blend with a small amount of milk until soft enough to spread over bottom of pie shell.
Put 1/2 of berries over cheese.
Crush remaining berries; mix along with juice, 1 cup sugar and cornstarch.
Cook this slowly until boiling point.
Allow to cool; pour over berries in the pie shell.
Chill. Spread whipped cream on top.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown bacon and onion.
Chop up.
Drain grease and add to beans, brown sugar and catsup mixture.
Bake until bubbles through or add bean mixture to bacon and onion in frypan and heat until tender and bubbly, approximately 10 minutes.

title: holly farms potatoes
directions: Mix ingredients and roll potatoes to cover.
Place in casserole and top with 1/2 stick of margarine.
Bake at 400° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: monster food potatoes
directions: Tear 1 piece of aluminum foil 1 1/2-foot long for each person. Slice potatoes "scallop style" on each foil. Add butter and thinly sliced onion to each. Add moderate salt, pepper and garlic salt to each. Fold tinfoil over potatoes to cover. Cook at 400° for 1 hour. Open and serve in foil.

title: old-fashioned corn bread
directions: Mix ingredients carefully.
Pour batter into greased pan. Bake in oven at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chicken fettuccine supreme
directions: Cook fettuccine according to package directions. Drain. Set aside and keep warm.

title: peach batter cobbler
directions: Line a pan with sliced peaches.
Make a batter using oleo, flour, baking powder, salt, sugar, milk and vanilla.
Pour over peaches.
Mix 1 cup sugar and water and pour over batter.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
If you use self-rising flour, omit baking powder and salt.

title: baked beans
directions: Drain fried bacon.
Saute onion and bell pepper in bacon drippings.
Add remaining ingredients, including crumbled bacon. Bake at 350° for 1 hour in a covered casserole.
Serves 4 to 6.
