title: party sandwich rolls
directions: Dump rolls out of pan and slice the rolls in half.
Place ham and cheese on one half.
Brush other half with sauce.
Put halves back together and place back in pans.
Bake about 20 minutes until heated and cheese melts.

title: apricot bars
directions: Place apricots in 2-quart saucepan.
Add enough water to cover.
Heat to boiling; reduce to simmer.
Simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes.
Drain.
Cool, chop and reserve.

title: corn chowder
directions: Lightly saute bacon and onions in Dutch oven or heavy skillet; drain off fat.
Add boiling water, salt and potatoes; bring to rolling boil.
Simmer until potatoes are done.
Add corn and milk; heat thoroughly.

title: swedish tascos
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter and sugar together, blend in flour.
Divide into 12 ungreased muffin tins.
Press with fingers to bottom and a short way up sides.
Bake 10 minutes.

title: mom's no-fat bread
directions: Combine water, yeast, salt, 2 cups white and 1 cup wheat flour. Mix 10 minutes with whisk or mixer.
Cover and let stand for 20 minutes.
Add 2 cups wheat flour and 1 cup white flour, mixing in as much as possible.
Knead in remaining flour as needed.
Divide in 2 parts.
Shape and put int two greased bread pans.
Cover and let rise until doubled in size.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Grease or Pam spray tin or bowl.
Heat soup, milk and cheese all together to just melt.
Pour over rice, broccoli and onion. Can top with crushed crackers.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: green pepper jelly
directions: In a large saucepan, combine green pepper, jalapeno peppers, sugar and vinegar.
Heat to boiling.
Boil 1 minute, stirring to prevent boiling over.
Remove from heat.
Stir in pectin, mixing well.
Let stand for 5 minutes.
Skim off white film which forms on top.
Mix in food coloring.
Strain if you prefer a clear jelly.
Pour into hot sterilized jars.
Top with sterilized 2 part lids and tighten bands.
(Do not double recipe.)

title: zonti
directions: Mix all together.
Cook slow for 2 hours.
Feeds 24 people. Put on top of spaghetti.

title: mounds candy
directions: Melt oleo, remove from heat and add milk and sugar. Gradually add coconut, kneading in well with hands. Form into bars and place on waxed paper. Refrigerate for 30 minutes. Melt together 3/4 cake paraffin and 13 oz. chocolate chips. Dip bars in chocolate/wax mix and place on wax paper until set.

title: best beans in the west
directions: Brown ground beef, breaking into small pieces.
Drain off fat.
Add onion; cook until tender.
Brown bacon; drain off fat and cut in pieces.

title: green chili casserole
directions: Saute meat and onion; drain.
Combine soup, chilies and evaporated milk.
Cut tortillas to bite size chunks.
Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Beginning with tortillas, layer tortillas, meat, soup and cheese.
Repeat 3 or 4 times.
End with cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, until hot and bubbly.
Double or triple recipe.
Great for a crowd.
Prepare ahead.

title: cream cheese brownies
directions: Mix together cake mix, melted margarine and 1 egg with spoon. Pres into jelly roll pan.
Using mixer, beat together sugar and cream cheese.
Add 2 eggs and mix well.
Pour over cake mixture. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Let cool before cutting.

title: super submarine
directions: Combine cabbage and enough mayonnaise to moisten; mix lightly. Season to taste with salt and pepper; chill.
Cut bread in half lengthwise.
Spread bottom half of loaf with butter; cover with lettuce, ham, cheese, cabbage mixture, onions and top half of loaf. Garnish with stuffed green olives, if desired.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: grandma tessie's maraschino cherry cake
directions: Pour cherry juice into cup, fill with milk to measure 1 cup. Cut up cherries, mix with nut pieces and sift 1/4 cup flour over them.
Cream butter and sugar, add egg yolks one at a time, beating well.
Add cherry-nut mixture.
Sift baking soda, baking powder and the 3 cups flour together and add alternately with liquid to the butter mixture.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Bake in large, greased tube pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: ham n' cheddar casserole
directions: Prepare rice according to package.
Prepare mixed vegetables according to package directions omitting margarine and salt.
In a large skillet, saute mushrooms and onion in butter until tender. Mix soup and milk. Stir into skillet.
Add ham and cooked vegetables. Simmer until thoroughly heated. Serve over warm rice. Serves 6 to 8.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix all ingredients in a pot.
Bring to a boil.
Boil 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir a few minutes, until thick. Pour into 8 x 8-inch pan.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Boil chicken until tender and set aside to cool.
Into a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish, pour about 4 cups of chicken broth. Sprinkle rice into broth.
Remove skin and bones from chicken and pull into bite size pieces.
Place chicken over rice.
Mix soup and sour cream; spoon over chicken.
(I add a small amount of chicken broth to my soup/sour cream mixture.)
Mix crackers and oleo. Sprinkle over soup mixture.
Bake 1 hour at 350° (uncovered).

title: coca cola barbecue chicken
directions: Boil chicken in coke until done.
Take 1 cup of juice from chicken and mix with sauce.
Bake in oven at 350 degrees for about 30 minutes.
Cover with foil.

title: beef rolls(rinderrouladen)
directions: Pound beef slices and rub with salt and pepper.
Cut up bacon, chop onion and parsley and mix all with mustard.
Spread this on beef slices and roll up tightly.
Tie with string and dip rolls in 1 tablespoon flour and fry in butter to brown all sides.
Add water and stew for 30 minutes.
When water has evaporated, turn rolls once again.
Remove, untie and place on hot platter.
In pan, add flour, cream, seasonings and beef stock to make gravy.
Pour over meat.
Serves 4.

title: e z dip
directions: Soften cream cheese and spread in bottom of baking dish. Spread chili, then onion and then cheese.
Slice peppers and place on top of cheese.
Bake for 20 minutes at 300° or until dip is bubbly.

title: stuffed pepper with barbecue sauce
directions: Cut top from pepper and clean inside.
Place in dish half filled with water and microwave for 2 minutes.
Turn and microwave for another 2 minutes.
Remove and drain.
Mix turkey, bread, onion and 1/2 Barbecue Sauce recipe.
Stuff pepper with mixture.
Preheat oven to 350° and bake for 45 minutes.
Pour rest of barbecue sauce over pepper and bake 15 minutes longer.

title: quick casserole
directions: Brown ground beef.
Shred cabbage.
Layer beef, cabbage and cheese in a casserole dish.
Season to taste.
Pour tomato paste over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter a 2-quart casserole.
Make a roux of butter and flour.
(Cook and stir butter and flour in a heavy saucepan for a couple of minutes.
Do not brown flour.)
Gradually add milk, stirring constantly until thick as to coat spoon.
Remove saucepan from heat and add seasoning.
Let sauce cool slightly. Gradually stir in cheese, starting with a cup, adding as much as 3 cups, tasting as you go.
(Use less than 3 cups if you want a creamier sauce.)
Put cooked macaroni in casserole and pour sauce over it.
Shake and mix until cheese coats the macaroni.
Top with reserved cheese.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes in 350° oven.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.
You can freeze this before it is baked.
Only allow to thaw and then heat oven to 350° and bake 45 minutes.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Cook broccoli according to package.
Mix all together; pour into greased pan.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: lisa's sweet & tangy barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together until well blended.
Brush on chicken, ribs or meat for that sweet and tangy flavor.

title: easy chicken pot pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°. Mix vegetables, chicken and soup in ungreased 9-inch pie plate.
Mix Bisquick, milk and egg together and pour on top of vegetables with chicken and soup.
Bake about 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes approximately 6 servings. High altitude: Heat oven to 425°.

title: breakfast souffle
directions: Butter bread; place butter side down in casserole.
Beat eggs. Add salt, dry mustard and milk; beat well.
Pour over bread.
Top with cheese; cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.
Do not preheat oven.
Cooked sausage, bacon, crab or vegetables may be added under cheese.

title: chicken pie 2
directions: Melt butter in saucepan. Add diced onion.
Saute 1 minute. Add Bisquick and pepper.
Cook over medium heat until bubbly.
Add milk and chicken broth until desired thickness.
Cook and stir until thick and boils.
Boil 1 minute.
Reduce heat to low.
Add chicken and vegetables.
Heat until both are warm.
Pour into pie crust.
Top with second pie crust.
Cut slits in top crust.
Cook at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: almond cookies
directions: Cream lard with granulated sugar and brown sugar until fluffy. Add egg and almond extract and beat until well blended.
Sift flour with salt and baking powder, then add to creamed mixture and blend well.

title: baked beans
directions: Cube and brown the bacon.
Remove from the pan and drain. Brown the beef.
Add the onion, sugar, molasses, mustard, vinegar and catsup.
Mix well.
Add the bacon and beans.
Mix well and pour into a baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: slim vegetable soup
directions: Place water, bouillon cubes and tomatoes in kettle. Bring to a boil.
Add sugar and remaining ingredients. Bring to a boil again. Cover, reduce heat and simmer until vegetables are tender.
Makes about 12 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: jalapeno corn casserole
directions: Cook rice according to package directions and set aside. Saute onion, green pepper and celery in butter until tender. Combine rice, sauteed vegetables and remaining ingredients, stirring well.
Spoon mixture into a lightly greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Garnish with green pepper rings, cherry tomatoes and parsley, if desired.

title: chicken wiggle
directions: Cook onions and peppers in 1 cup of chicken broth until tender.
Boil noodles in broth.
Mix all in a large baking dish. Bake slowly about 25 minutes at low temperature, about 325°.

title: bean casserole
directions: Drain all beans, except pork and beans. Saute celery and onions with sausage; drain well. Add all ingredients and put in casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours. Cover last 15 minutes if it is getting too brown.

title: honeybear brownies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar in small mixing bowl.
Blend in honey or syrup and vanilla.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine flour, cocoa and salt gradually; add to creamed mixture.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into 9 x 9 x 1 3/4-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes until begins to pull away from edge of pan.
Cool.
Frost with chocolate frosting.
It makes 16 brownies.

title: chili
directions: Brown beef in large pot.
Drain and remove from pot.
Chop onion and pepper; cook in oil until tender.
Add beef and all ingredients, except beans.
Cook for 2 hours.
Add beans; cook for additional 15 minutes.
Let sit overnight in refrigerator.

title: pear mincemeat
directions: Grate or grind pears and apples, drain off juice and add other ingredients.
Cook
to 45 minutes slow.
Stir to keep from sticking.
Fill jars and seal.

title: lettuce and cauliflower salad
directions: Mix lettuce and cauliflower together, then spread peas on top. Spread the Hellmann's on top of peas, then sprinkle bacon. Sprinkle Good Seasons Zesty Italian dry mix, then sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.
Cover and set in refrigerator overnight. Mix together when you are ready to eat.

title: muffins
directions: Place first 4 ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Place remaining ingredients in a small mixing bowl and mix until well blended.
Blend all ingredients together.
Pour batter into greased muffin tins.
Bake for 20 minutes at 400°.
If desired, slice muffins lengthwise and top with fruit and whipped cream.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Blend in applesauce and egg.
Dissolve soda in boiling water and add alternately with dry ingredients.
Bake in 8 x 12 x 1 1/2-inch oblong pan at 350° for 1 hour.
Good with maple flavored frosting or may be dusted with confectioners sugar.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: In mixing bowl, stir together oats, sugar, butter and flour. Fold in egg white until well blended.
Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake in 350° oven until golden, about 12 minutes.
Remove to wire rack to cool.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: leslie's fantastic holiday cheese ball
directions: Fry bacon.
Melt cream cheese and Cheddar together until Cheddar melts.
Add Worcestershire and smoke flavoring.
Blend in bacon that has been crumbled and let cool.
Shape into a ball in Saran Wrap.
Chill.
Roll in chopped parsley until covered.
Serve with crackers.

title: reese's cups
directions: Melt butter and peanut butter together until creamy.
Mix sugar into peanut butter.
Pat onto cookie sheet.
Melt chocolate chips and pour on top.
Let cool and cut into squares.

title: cloud nine salad
directions: Leave cream cheese out of refrigerator overnight.
Beat cheese until creamy; add pineapple juice, a little at a time.
Fold in Cool Whip; add other ingredients.
Let set overnight before serving.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni.
Mix all other ingredients and sprinkle with paprika.

title: tater tots casserole
directions: Grease oblong baking dish and press meat into bottom of it. Cover with thinly sliced onions. Spread soup over onions; top with Tater Tots and bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes or until Tater Tots are nicely browned.

title: marinated beef kabobs
directions: Combine lemon juice, chopped onion, mustard, garlic salt, salt and pepper.
Add oil and mix.
Place beef cubes and marinade in a plastic bag; tie bag securely and place in pan in fridge several hours or overnight.
Pour off marinade and save.
Thread beef, vegies and pickles (alternating) on skewers.

Brush with marinade. Place kabobs on grill 3 to 4 inches from heat and broil to moderate temperature, turning and brushing with marinade occasionally, for 12 to 18 minutes, depending on how well done you desire.

title: apple crunch
directions: Pour pie filling in pan.
Put dry cake mix on top.
Melt butter; pour on
top
of cake mix.
Sprinkle nuts on top.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: red apple inn rolls
directions: Pour boiling water over butter, sugar and salt.
Let cool. Dissolve yeast in warm water; beat in eggs.
Add to the cooled butter mixture.
Add flour, mixing well.
Let stand overnight, covered, in refrigerator.
Shape the rolls 2 hours before baking. Bake at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: clara's chicken "n" dumplings
directions: Selecting the Chicken and the Kettle:
The first difference between great dumplings and mediocre dumplings is fresh ingredients.
Ideally, purchase a fresh "young fat baking hen" from your local butcher or from the grocer.
If you shop where they are not generally in stock, you can call ahead and they can order you one.
Using a frozen baking hen can be done, but absolutely do not use a "fryer" they are mostly bone and do not have the flavor of a young hen.
The size of the hen should be determined by the size of the kettle you will be boiling it in..it should be just big enough to fit the hen in breast up and at least 8 inches deep in a a soup kettle.
For a kettle which is about 12 inches wide, select an 8-10 pound hen.
The kettle should be of a heavy grade aluminum, iron, or stainless steel.
Using a thin kettle will result fast cooking which dries out the meat and dumplings sticking to the bottom or the sides and burning.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients for 4 minutes; add pineapple and pecans.
Pour into 2 graham cracker crumb crusts.
Chill.

title: apple cake
directions: In large bowl combine apples, sugar, oil and eggs.
Sift together flour, soda, salt, baking powder and cinnamon.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Bake in 9 x 13 pan or loaf pan for 1 hour at 250°.

title: potato cake
directions: Cream sugar, butter and eggs.
Add milk, sifted flour, cocoa, baking powder and spices; mix well.
Add mashed potatoes.
Pour in loaf pan and bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: lemon cheese pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs, flour, juice of 2 lemons and grated lemon rind.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: company tuna bake
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
With electric mixer, blend cheese and soup.
Stir in tuna, chopped onion, mustard and milk.
Turn into a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Mix crumbs and margarine.
Sprinkle over tuna mixture.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: fillets of sole tarragon
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brush fillets with 1/4 cup butter. Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Arrange in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Cover dish with foil.
Bake 20 minutes or until fish flakes easily when tested with fork.
Combine rest of butter with tarragon, chives and salt; heat slightly.
To serve, put fillets on platter; pour warm herb butter combined with cooking liquid over them.

title: creamy spinach curried soup
directions: Saute onions and garlic in oil until tender; add chicken broth and bring to a boil.
Stir in spinach; cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Pour mixture into blender; puree.
Return pureed mixture to saucepan; add milk, seasonings and rice.
Heat thoroughly. Serve with a twist of lemon.

title: west texas fried venison
directions: Mix flour, salt and pepper and coat venison.
Heat bacon fat and brown meat on both sides.
Add remaining ingredients and cook, covered, for 1 to 2 hours in electric frypan.
Serve with noodles.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix flour and margarine, then add nuts.
Spread in a 2 x 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Bake at 300° for 20 to 25 minutes until light brown.
Let cool completely.

title: mini cream horns
directions: Place oil in palms and rub clothes pins, saturating them thoroughly (will be unable to use clothes pins for anything else in future, just keep stored in Ziploc bag for later use.

title: stuffed angel food cake
directions: Bake angel food cake according to directions.
Let cool and slice cake into 2 sections with a top and bottom.
Set top aside. Pull out center of bottom half so that you have a "boat" to put the pudding mixture in.

title: play dough
directions: Mix oil and water with a few drops of food coloring.
Add flour and salt.
Cook for 3 minutes and add cream of tartar. Knead when cool.
Stays moist if you keep in the refrigerator in closed container.

title: shrimp and wild rice casserole
directions: Cook rice according to directions on box.
Mix all other ingredients and put into a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: mile high zucchini bread
directions: Beat sugar, oil, eggs and vanilla in a mixing bowl until fluffy.
In a separate bowl, mix flour, salt, baking powder and cinnamon.
Add to egg mixture and mix on medium speed until blended.
Stir in zucchini and nuts.
Pour into a greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool before wrapping.

title: baked chocolate pie
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Pour
into
deep 10-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes or until almost set.
Do not overbake.
Remove from
oven while still a little soft in center.

title: coconut refrigerator cookies
directions: Sift flour; measure and add soda and salt.
Sift again.
Cream butter; add sugars and cream.
Add eggs, flour, rolled oats, nuts and coconut.
Mix thoroughly.
Shape into 2-inch rolls.
Wrap each roll in plastic wrap or wax paper.
Refrigerate.
Cut into 1/8-inch slices and bake at 375° for about 10 minutes.

title: burried burritos
directions: Place pinto beans in skillet; mash and cook slow on low to medium heat until smooth, but not sticky thick.
Remove from heat. Place hot dog sauce in pan and warm.
Shred cheese.
Place 1 to 2 tablespoons pinto beans in the center of a tortilla.
Add layer of hot dog sauce and top with cheese.
Fold in half and roll up tightly.

title: yum-yum cake
directions: Mix together the first 3 ingredients until it is crumbly. Gently press into bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: broiled short ribs
directions: Trim excess fat from ribs.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Place ribs in a Dutch oven.
Add water to cover.
Simmer, covered about 2 hours or until meat is tender.
Drain.
Place ribs on an unheated rack in a broiler pan.
Combine catsup, molasses, lemon juice, mustard, chili powder and garlic powder.
Brush some over the ribs.
Broil 4-5 inches from heat for 10-15 minutes, turning often and basting with catsup mixture.
Makes 6 servings.

title: easy chicken stew
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Mix all ingredients in a casserole; cover and bake for 3 hours.
Makes 6 servings.

title: potato soup
directions: Cut potatoes in bite size pieces.
Cut bacon in small pieces. Brown and drain.
Add all ingredients together.
Cover with water. Simmer for an hour and a half.
Add a little flour paste (if needed).

title: sherry's famous meat loaf
directions: Put ground beef in bowl.
Blend in the bread crumbs
or bread done in a blender, egg, ketchup to taste, salt and pepper.
Mix all ingredients together until well blended.
Put meat in a loaf pan and spread ketchup over the top.
Put in oven for 60 minutes at 350° or until brown.
Cut and serve.

title: lime pickles
directions: Mix powdered lime with 1 gallon water.
Add sliced cucumbers. Soak 24 hours.
Rinse well.
Place in cold water and soak 2 hours. Bring to boil remaining ingredients.
Drop cucumbers in solution and boil 1 1/2 hours.
Pack and seal in jars.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Mix liquid from blueberries and pineapple. Add enough water to make 1 3/4 cups. Dissolve gelatin in boiling water and add to fruit juices and water. Chill until slightly thick. Fold in fruit. Chill until firm. Combine cream cheese, sour cream, sugar and vanilla. Beat well. Spread over gelatin. Sprinkle with pecans. Chill until firm.
Serve.

title: steak marinade
directions: Combine ingredients, mix and pour over steak.
Marinate overnight.

title: tallerina
directions: Brown meat, pepper and onion; add everything else, except noodles and cheese.
Cook noodles until tender.
Into 2 casseroles, spread a layer of noodles, layer of mixture and cheese.
This amount allows 2 layers in each dish.

title: no fuss beef lasagna
directions: Brown meat (8 to 10 minutes).
Mix spaghetti sauce, tomatoes, salt and pepper.
In medium bowl, beat egg.
Add Ricotta and Parmesan cheeses.
Spread 2 cups of meat and sauce on 13 x 9-inch pan.
Arrange 5 noodles one at a time, pressing into meat mixture. Spread cheese mixture on noodles.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese and top with 1 1/2 cups meat sauce.
Arrange another layer of noodles, pressing into meat.
Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese on top. Tent foil lightly.
Bake 45 minutes at approximately 350°. Remove from oven and let sit 15 minutes.
Cut into 3-inch squares. Serve.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: You will need a 2-quart baking dish.
In 6 cups boiling hot water, place macaroni plus broccoli and boil for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Drain, but don't rinse.
Return to pan. Empty tuna fish in and add powdered onion and garlic powder to taste.
Mix with the directions of box.
Place in baking dish. Place cheese slices to cover top of mixture.
Bake in preheated oven, 350°, for 1/2 hour or until golden brown.
Serves four.

title: pickled watermelon rind
directions: Trim dark green and pink parts from the watermelon rind; cut in 1-inch cubes.
Soak overnight in salt water (1/4 cup salt to 1 quart water; it may take more to cover).
Drain, rinse and cover with cold water.
Cook until just tender; drain.

title: tom's fantastic veggies
directions: Cook your cauliflower or broccoli until tender.
Add your salt. When tender, drain cauliflower and add your butter and cheese until melted.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mix dressing and seasonings.
Pour over the other combined ingredients.
Mix and refrigerate.
Makes 12 servings.

title: chocolate balls
directions: Melt in top of double boiler over boiling water.
Dip balls into mixture.

title: potato soup
directions: Combine first 9 ingredients and cook until tender.
Don't drain.
Mix flour and 1/4 cup of the milk to make a paste and put in soup.
Add cheese and rest of milk.
Cook until cheese is completely melted.

title: au gratin potatoes
directions: Combine all ingredients, except corn flakes and butter.
Spray 9 x 13-inch baking dish with Pam.
Pour potato mixture into pan. Top with corn flakes and drizzle with butter.
Bake at 450° for 45 minutes.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour hot water over oatmeal and set aside to cool.

title: chicken tarts
directions: Prepare pie crust according to directions; roll dough and press into mini muffin tin.
Put half chicken spread, then small amount of cheese to each.
Beat eggs; stir in cream and pepper.
Fill cups with about 1 1/2 teaspoon of egg mixture.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Makes 24.

title: dilly brussels sprouts
directions: Cook sprouts until tender.
Drain and pour ingredients over sprouts and chill overnight.

title: lime salad
directions: Stir Jell-O in boiling water and add cream cheese and marshmallows.
Stir and cook until dissolved.
Cool slightly; add pineapple, whipped cream, nuts and salt.
Mix well, refrigerate until firm.

title: broccoli-cheese delight
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions; drain.
Arrange broccoli in an 8-inch square baking pan that has been sprayed with a nonstick cooking spray.

title: vanilla frosting
directions: Cream the sugar and butter well. Add liquid slowly and turn beater to high. Add vanilla or other flavoring.
It turns out real fluffy like whipped cream. Don't over add the liquid.
Beat as you add the liquid.

title: sandra's veg-all casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients (except oleo and cracker crumbs) and put in a casserole dish.
Top with Ritz cracker crumbs and pour melted oleo or butter on top of crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: dude dip
directions: Brown meat.
Drain fat.
Mix, melt and serve with tortilla chips.

title: mustard soup(serves 6)
directions: Melt butter and make a roux with flour in a heavy saucepan. Add chicken broth, cream and milk.
Add salt and white pepper to taste.
Add onion juice.
Simmer over low heat 10 minutes until milk is scalded.
Do not boil.
In separate bowl, beat egg yolks and 3 tablespoons cream until smooth.
Slowly add approximately 1 cup of the hot soup mixture to egg mixture, whisking constantly. Pour this liaison into the pan with the rest of the soup, whisking constantly.
Reheat.
Stir all the time for a smooth consistency. Never boil.
Add mustard last, stirring it in.
Serve soup in small portions.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: jess's corn bread
directions: Add buttermilk to desired consistency.
Bake in 400° oven in iron skillet until done.

title: strawberry banana salad
directions: Pour half of the mixture in a glass dish.
"Sink" one sliced banana in it and chill until set.
Spread with a pint of sour cream.
Pour remaining half of mixture over sour cream.
"Sink" another sliced banana over this and chill until ready to serve.

title: whole wheat banana bread
directions: Combine flours, soda, cinnamon and nutmeg in a small bowl and set aside.
In a large bowl, mix applesauce, sugar, egg whites and bananas until well blended.
Add flour mixture and walnuts, stirring until just blended.

title: dirt pie
directions: Must put in large bowl in this order.
Put 3/4 of chopped Oreo cookies in bottom of bowl.
In large mixing bowl, soften butter with cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Mix until fluffy.
Pour into large bowl on top of cookies.
In large mixing bowl, combine vanilla pudding with milk and blend until well mixed.
Fold in the Cool Whip.
Pour mixture on top of cream cheese in bowl.
Sprinkle remaining chopped Oreo cookies on top of whip cream mixture.
Keep refrigerated.

title: homestyle cabbage
directions: Bring water to a boil.
Add all ingredients.
Cover and stir occasionally.
Cook until cabbage is tender.
Additional water may be added if needed.
Cook over low heat, approximately 25 minutes. Serves 4 to 6.

title: extra moist chocolate cake
directions: Melt margarine in medium size saucepan.
Add cocoa and stir until dissolved.
Add water and bring to boil.
Remove from heat. Add flour and sugar, stirring well to mix.
Add buttermilk, eggs and vanilla.
Mix well.

title: mexican chocolate cake
directions: Combine oleo, oil, chocolate and water in pan and heat until melted.
Combine flour, soda, sugar, milk, eggs, cinnamon, and vanilla in a large bowl.
Add first mixture.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes until done.

title: cheesy cabbage roll-ups
directions: Pour boiling water over cabbage leaves to cover; allow to stand for 10 minutes.
Combine ground chuck, 1 cup cheese, corn, onion, salt and pepper, just until blended.
Remove cabbage leaves from water.
Place 2/3 cup of meat mixture in each leaf, fold in sides and roll lengthwise.
Fasten with wood toothpicks.

title: spinach balls(makes 5 dozen)
directions: Beat eggs.
Add other ingredients to blend.
If too soft to handle, refrigerate for a while.
Roll into small balls; place on cookie sheet.
Bake for 20 minutes in a 350° oven.
Cool and serve.

title: easy banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding with milk until thick.
Add sour cream and Cool Whip.
Layer, starting with wafers, bananas and pudding mix, ending with pudding mix.
Refrigerate until ready to eat.

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Place contents of vegetables, seasoning packet from stuffing mix and butter in a bowl.
Add hot water; stir well, add stuffing crumbs, stir gently to mix.
Mix soup and milk in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Stir in chicken, vegetables and thyme.
Spoon stuffing over chicken mixture.
Bake for 45 to 60 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: marinated carrots *
directions: Cook carrots until almost tender, drain.
Bring to boil soup, vinegar, sugar, pepper, onion and celery.
Pour over carrots. Cool and refrigerate overnight.
Keeps 7 to 10 days.

title: coconut penuche
directions: Line an 8 x 4 x 2-inch loaf pan with foil, extending foil over edges of pan.
Butter the foil.
Set pan aside.

title: when times are hard
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Prepare Jiffy cornbread mix as directed on box.
Pour 1/2 of the mix into pan. Combine all other ingredients and pour over cornbread mixture.
Add the remaining 1/2 of the cornbread mix over the top.
Bake at 350° until golden brown, approximately 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: jenn's open-face bacon, tomato and cheese sandwich
directions: Lay tomato slices on toast.
Add bacon and top with cheese. Place sandwich on napkin.
Place sandwich and napkin on foil in microwave oven.
Microwave at High for 15 to 35 seconds or until cheese melts.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in saucepan; cook for 20 minutes.

title: microwave zucchini parmesan
directions: In 8-inch baking dish, combine zucchini, Parmesan cheese and tomato sauce; heat, covered, on High for 8 to 9 minutes or until zucchini is tender, stirring once.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese and let stand, covered, 5 minutes before serving.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Mix meat and onion.
Roll into small balls and fry.
Drain well.
Mix jelly and chili sauce.
Add meatballs.

title: mexican black-eyed peas
directions: Cover peas with water; soak overnight.
Brown sausage; to crumble, add onion.
Cook until tender.
Drain.
Drain peas well; stir in sausage and remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat.
Simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Add water, if needed.

title: confetti waldorf salad(servings:  8)
directions: Combine fruit and nuts.
Blend wet ingredients and salt in measuring cup.
Pour the wet mixture onto the carrot mixture, tossing to mix well.

title: jalapeno jelly
directions: Combine green pepper, jalapeno pepper, vinegar and sugar in large saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Boil 4 minutes.
Remove from heat and let cool 1 minute.
Add pectin and a few drops of green food coloring (if desired).
Pour into hot sterilized jelly glasses and seal.
Makes about five 6 ounce glasses of jelly.

title: baked custard
directions: Beat eggs slightly to mix.
Add sugar and salt and beat to mix. Scald milk (crinkly film forms on top).
Stir into egg mixture. Add vanilla.
Pour into a baking dish (1 1/2-quart).
Set in a pan of hot water.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes, just until silver knife inserted 1-inch from edge comes out clean.
Immediately remove from heat.
Center sets as it stands.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Drain juice from pineapple.
Beat egg in juice and cook until thick with sugar and flour.
Pour over all ingredients.

title: meat ball stew
directions: Combine ground beef, bread crumbs, Worcestershire sauce, salt, onions and dash of pepper.
Shape into 16 balls and brown in
2 tablespoons
of vegetable oil in large skillet.
Quarter the carrots,
potatoes,
large
onion and green beans or peas. Stir in
2 cans Hunt's tomato sauce (8 ounce size) and 1/2 cup water. Cover and simmer until vegetables are tender (about 1/2 hour).
If desired
substitute tomato sauce for cream of mushroom soup. Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: caramel turtle brownies
directions: Mix cake mix, melted butter and all but 2 tablespoons of evaporated milk until well blended.
Spread 1/2 batter in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Mixture will form thin layer.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Reserve remaining batter.
Melt caramels with 2 tablespoons evaporated milk.
Remove cake from oven.
Sprinkle with chips and drizzle with caramels.
Drop remaining batter by teaspoon over caramel until covered.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Cut while warm. Press pecan halves on each square.

title: ham 'n cheese roll-ups
directions: In small bowl, combine Cheddar cheese, cream cheese and Blue Bonnet margarine until well blended.
Spread 1/4 of mixture on 1 ham slice.
Repeat with remaining cheese mixture and ham slices. Roll up from short sides.
Chill for several hours or wrap and freeze, if desired.

title: italian sausage soup
directions: In a 5-quart kettle, brown sausage on medium heat.
Drain fat. Add garlic and onions.
Cook until limp.
Stir in and break up tomatoes. Add broth, wine, basil, thyme and parsley.
Simmer uncovered for 30 minutes.
Add veggies and noodles.
Cover and simmer 25 minutes more. Sprinkle each serving with Parmesan cheese.

title: dutch refrigerator cookies
directions: Cream together shortening and sugars.
Add egg and beat well. Sift together dry ingredients; stir into creamed mixture.
Add nuts.
Shape into rolls about 2 1/2 inches across.
Wrap in waxed paper and chill thoroughly.

title: crab cutlet
directions: Melt margarine in pan, remove from heat and add flour, salt, pepper and parsley.
Blend well.
Gradually stir in milk.
Return to heat and cook, stirring constantly until mixture is very thick. Add beaten egg and Worcestershire sauce.
Cool.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Make 4 hours to one day ahead and mix or turn upside down to mix.

title: fry bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and roll dough the size of a tennis ball.
Mash them flat, about 1/8-inch thick, then fry them in around 350° skillet (make sure grease is hot).
Fry until brown.

title: deep dish pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour together in baking dish.
Pour milk into dish slowly, while stirring constantly.
(If you dump the milk in without stirring, it will be lumpy.)
Add drained fruit.
Pour melted butter (or oleo) gently over top of other ingredients. Bake at about 350° until browned on top, about 30 to 45 minutes. Pie should be juicy and "gooey" on the bottom and crusty on top.

title: great meat casserole
directions: Mix beef with chopped onion.
Grease a large casserole.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour into casserole.
Top with bread crumbs. Bake 2 hours at 350°.

title: sand tartsgroves, texas
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add flour, nuts and vanilla, mix well.
Pinch off pieces the size of a marble and roll about finger size.
Shape into crescents.
Bake on an ungreased cookie sheet at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Do not brown.
Roll in powdered sugar while warm.

title: easy divinity
directions: Mix together sugar, corn syrup, water and salt in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Cook in microwave on full power for 15 minutes. Stir once during cooking.
While syrup cooks, beat egg whites until stiff peaks form in large bowl.
Gradually pour hot syrup over egg whites while beating at high speed until mixture is thickened and candy starts to lose its gloss.
Beating may require about 12 minutes.
Add vanilla to beaten mixture.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper.

title: stove top smoked sausage casserole
directions: Boil potatoes, sausage and onion until they are almost done. Add noodles and cook until done.
Drain well.
Add soup, peas, butter, salt and pepper.
Cook until hot.
Add cheese on top.
Cook until melted.

title: chocolate spice cake
directions: Combine flour and sugar in bowl.
Combine and bring to a boil butter, oil, cocoa and water.
Add to flour/sugar mixture, then add remaining ingredients.
Bake in ungreased cake pan at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: stuffed bell peppers
directions: Spray baking dish (Pyrex or Corning Ware) with Pam.
Mix together meat, rice, salt, pepper, crackers, onions, egg, chili powder, water, 1/2 of tomato sauce, sugar, parsley flakes and catsup.
Stuff bell pepper pieces with meat mixture.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Mix and press into bottom of 9 x 13-inch buttered pan.

title: spinach quiche
directions: Bring this mixture to a boil.
First
add to boiling mixture 6 quarts of cup up okra.
Then boil okra until it changes color. Pack okra in jars; cover with some of the mixture and seal jars.

title: fruit salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add pineapple, bananas, chopped fruit of choice to Jell-O.
Pour 1/2 mixture in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spoon sour cream over Jell-O mixture.
Pour remaining Jell-O over sour cream.

title: sloppy joe sandwiches
directions: Brown ground beef and onions; pour off fat.
Add next 7 ingredients.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Serve over buns.
Serves 20.

title: cherry orange chicken
directions: Place chicken in baking pan.
Pour melted butter over. Combine brown sugar, orange peel, ginger and orange juice.
Pour over chicken.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 45 minutes.
Remove and add drained cherries.
Return to oven; bake 30 minutes or until chicken is tender and golden brown.
Makes 8 servings.

title: apple pancakes
directions: Sprinkle the lemon juice over the apples to prevent browning; set aside.
Sift flour, salt and sugar into a bowl.
Beat eggs in with the milk.
Stir the egg mixture into the flour mixture, blending well.
Fold in the apples.
Heat the butter in a saute pan over medium-high heat.
Spoon the batter into the pan, in 2-ounce portions.
Cook the pancakes, turning once, until golden brown on both sides.
Dust with powdered sugar and cinnamon and serve immediately.

title: garlic hominy grits
directions: Cook grits in boiling water and salt.
Add all other ingredients, except American cheese.
Bake in moderate oven (375°) for 45 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Cover with American cheese. Return to oven and bake until cheese is brown.
